INSERT INTO `recipe` VALUES (7,'Apple Cinnamon Muffin','<ul>\r\n    <li>1/4 cup ground walnuts</li>\r\n    <li>&nbsp;3/4 cup granulated sugar</li>\r\n    <li>1-2 tsp ground cinnamon</li>\r\n    <li>1/4 cup butter - melted &amp; cooled</li>\r\n    <li>1 large egg - beaten</li>\r\n    <li>1/2 cup milk</li>\r\n    <li>1-1/2 cups flour</li>\r\n    <li>1 tbsp baking powder</li>\r\n    <li>1/2 tsp salt</li>\r\n    <li>1 cup peeled and grated apples</li>\r\n</ul>','<p>Preheat oven to 375 Bake 15 to 20 minutes Mix walnuts, 1/4 sugar and 1 tsp cinnamon and set aside. Combine butter, sugar, and egg. Stir in milk. Combine flour, baking powder,1 tsp cinnamon and salt. Add to butter mixture. Stir together, should be lumpy. Fold in apples. Put a little batter in the tins. Sprinkle with most of the sugar and nut mix. Fill tins. Sprinkle with remaining sugar and nut mix.</p>','<p>170 calories per muffin</p>',5),(8,'Banana Muffins','1/2 cup margarine\r\n1/2 cup white sugar\r\n1 egg\r\n1-3/4 cups flour\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1 tsp baking powder\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n1/4 cup milk\r\n1 cup mashed bananas','350 for 30 minutes\r\nMakes 12 large muffins\r\n\r\nBeat margarine and sugar well.  Add eggs.  Add dry ingredients and milk.  Lastly add bananas','I usually put in approx. 2 cups of bananas.  The muffins are moister.  I also put a little brown sugar on the top of each muffin.  You can add nuts if you want or chocolate chips.',5),(9,'Blueberry Strudel Muffins','2-1/2 cups flour\r\n1-1/4 cup sugar\r\n1 tbsp baking powder\r\n1 cup butter\r\n1/2 tsp cinnamon\r\n\r\n3/4 cup milk\r\n2 eggs\r\n1-1/2 tsp vanilla\r\n2 cups blueberries\r\n','350 for 30 minutes\r\n\r\nMix together the first 5 ingredients and set aside 3/4 of a cup.\r\n\r\nCombine the next 3 ingredients and add to the flour mixture.  Add the berries last.\r\n\r\nPut in muffin tins and put the reserved mixture on the top ','I don\'t usually use butter I use margarine.  You can mix it half and half to make the muffins richer.  I also put a little more than 2 cups of berries.  It depends on how fruity you want them to be.',5),(10,'Butter Dominoes','1/2 cup butter (margarine)\r\n1/4 cup sugar\r\n1/2 cup cocoa\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n1 egg 2 cup graham wafer crumbs\r\n1 cup coconut\r\n1/2 cup chopped walnuts (pecans)\r\n\r\n1/4 cup butter\r\n2 tbsp vanilla instant pudding\r\n3 tbsp milk\r\n2 cup icing sugar\r\n\r\n3 oz semi sweet chocolate\r\n1 tbsp butter','Melt 1/2 cup butter. Combine sugar, cocoa, vanilla eggs, crumbs, coconut, nuts and melted butter.  Press in 9x9 pan. Put in fridge to cool.  \r\n\r\nCream 1/4 cup butter, blend in pudding, milk and icing sugar.  Spread over crumbs and cool.\r\n\r\nMelt chocolate with 1 tbsp butter.  Spread over chilled mix.  Chill','When you are making the base you can substitute margarine for butter but not when you are making the filling or the chocolate topping.\r\n\r\nWhen you are cutting the squares dip the knife in hot water so that it slices through the chocolate on top without cracking it.',6),(11,'Hello Dolly\'s','1/2 cup butter\r\n1 cup graham crumbs\r\n1 cup flaked coconut\r\n1 cup semi sweet chocolate chips\r\n1 cup walnuts\r\n1/2 cup cut green or red cherries\r\n1 - 15 oz tin eagle brand','8x8 greased pan    350 for 30 minutes\r\n\r\nMelt butter.  Mix together the graham crumbs and butter and press into the bottom of the pan.\r\n\r\nAdd the other ingredients in the order given.','For the base I use margarine instead of butter.  It usually takes longer to bake than 30 minutes.  Keep an eye on it.  When it is bubbling and lightly browned on the top it is ready.  Make sure you don\'t cook it too long or the edges will be overcooked and too chewy to eat.\r\n',6),(12,'Fudge Brownies - Bushka\'s Recipe','1/2 cup margarine\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n1 egg\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n2 oz unsweetened chocolate \r\n1/2 cup flour\r\n1/2 cup pecans/walnuts','325   8x8 pan   30-35 minutes\r\n\r\nMelt chocolate. Mix together the margarine and sugar.  Add the egg and vanilla and melted chocolate and flour.  Mix in the nuts.  Put in Pan and bake.','Make sure that you don\'t overbake these.  They should be moist and fudgy in the middle.  After 20 minutes use a toothpick and check them.\r\n\r\nBushka used to put a chocolate glaze on top.  I think she just heated up a little cream or milk and added in chocolate and mixed them together well and poured it on top.',6),(13,'Chocolate Amaretto Cheesecake','Crust.....\r\n1-1/4 cups chocolate wafer crumbs (oreo)\r\n2 tbsp white sugar\r\n1/4 melted margarine\r\n\r\nFilling....\r\n500 grams (1 lb) cream cheese\r\n1/2 cup white sugar\r\n2 large eggs\r\n6 oz semi sweet chocolate melted and cooled\r\n1/2 tsp almond flavoring\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n1/3 cup amaretto\r\n2/3 cup sour cream\r\n\r\nTopping.....\r\n2 oz semi sweet chocolate\r\n1 tsp margarine','Springform cheesecake pan  300 1 hr\r\n\r\nCombine crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.  Press into the bottom and 1/2 way up sides of pan.  Chill\r\n\r\nBeat cream cheese well, until smooth.  Gradually beat in sugar.  Beat in eggs one at a time at low speed.  Add cooled chocolate, flavorings, amaretto and sour cream.  Beat at low speed until thoroughly blended.  Pour into prepared pan.\r\n\r\nBake in 300 oven for 1 hour.  Turn off the heat and leave cake in oven 1 hour longer.  Cool in pan at room temperature and then chill in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.\r\n\r\nMelt chocolate with margarine and pour over top of cheesecake.\r\n\r\n','If you don\'t have any amaretto you can add a little extra almond flavoring and sour cream.\r\n\r\nWhen you cut it use a knife dipped in hot chocolate to avoid cracking the chocolate on top.  You can also garnish with whipped cream and almond slices but I figure it\'s great without it.',7),(14,'Double Chocolate Bomb !!','White Mousse .......\r\n1 square semi-sweet chocolate melted\r\n1 tsp unflavoured gelatine\r\n2/3 cup whipping cream\r\n6 squares white chocolate\r\n2 tbsp butter\r\n2 eggs, separated\r\n1/4 cup sugar\r\n\r\nDark Mousse.......\r\n1/3 cup whipping cream\r\n5 squares semi-sweet chocolate\r\n2 tbsp butter\r\n2 eggs, separated\r\n1/4 cup sugar\r\n','Line a 6 cup (1.5 L) mixing bowl with plastic wrap and drizzle inner surface with melted chocolate.  Freeze.\r\n\r\nWhite Mousse.....\r\nIn saucepan sprinkle gelatin over cream.  Let stand 5 minutes.  Bring cream to a boil; remove from heat. Add white chocolate and butter, stir until melted. Blend in egg yolks.  Beat egg whites until frothy; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.  Fold into chocolate mixtures; pour into prepared bowl.  Freeze 30 min.\r\n\r\nDark Mousse......\r\nPrepared dark mousse layer following white mousse directions, omitting gelatine step.  Freeze until set, at least 8 hours.  Unmould onto serving plate, remove plastic wrap.','When you put the plastic wrap in the bowl spray the inside of the bowl with pam and then press the plastic wrap to it, I find this makes it easier.....and then the wrap slips out of the bowl easier when you\'re unmolding it.  If it doesn\'t blow a hairdryer all over it for a second or put in a bowl of warm water for just a few seconds.',7),(15,'Mini Sugar Cones - Marc Dumais recipe','1/3 cup corn syrup\r\n2 cups brown sugar\r\n1/4 cup butter\r\n1 can eagle brand\r\n2 cups white mini marshmallows\r\n\r\n','Mix all the ingredients in a bowl and heat in microwave for 8 minutes (use an 8 cup bowl)stirring every 2 minutes\r\n\r\nPlace in tiny cones which you have standing up.   Let set. Stores in airtight container.','I have never made these,but I love them, so to stand the cones up I would take a box and put holes in it the size of the cones.(I\'m not sure but you might actually be able to buy something made specifically for this purpose)',7),(16,'Lemon Coconut Angel Foodcake','1 pkg angel food cake mix\r\n1 pkg lemon pie filling\r\n2 tbsp lemon juice\r\n1 tbsp grated lemon peel\r\n2-1/2 cup whipping cream\r\ncoconut','Prepare the cake as directed and cool.  Meanwhile prepare the pie filling with 2 cups water.  Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and peel.  Put in a bowl and cool in the fridge. Split the cake into 5 layers.  Whip the cream and take out approx. 1/3 and fold in the coconut.  Place the filling in the cake and frost the rest of the cake with the remaining whipped cream.  Sprinkle with coconute and refrigerate.','I usually don\'t add in the extra lemon juice or peel.  But if you have it add it in for a fuller lemon flavor.  I put a fair bit of coconut into the filling because I like coconut, but it is up to you.  When I put the coconut outside of the cake I often used food coloring to make it yellow just to make the cake look different.\r\n\r\nGrampas favorite cake.',8),(17,'Carol\'s Chocolate Chip Cake','1 cup dates or raisins\r\n1 tsp baking soda       \r\n1 cup hot water        \r\n\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n1 cup margarine\r\n2 eggs \r\n1/2 cup pecans\r\n1-3/4 cups flour\r\n1 tbsp cocoa\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n6 oz chocolate chips\r\n','13x9 pan    350 for 35-40 minutes\r\n\r\nPut baking soda in hot water and add dates/raisins.  Set aside and cool.\r\n\r\nCream margarine and sugar together. Add eggs and dry ingredients.  Add date mix and 1/2of the nuts and chocolate chips.  Pour into greased pan, sprinkle with rest of the nuts and chocolate chips.','We are not real fans of cooked raisins so I always used dates. ',8),(18,'Red Velvet Cake','1/2 margarine\r\n1-1/2 cups sugar\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 cup buttermilk\r\n2-1/2 cups flour\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n2 oz red food colouring (2 bottles)\r\n2 tsp cocoa\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n1 tsp vinegar\r\n\r\nFrosting.....\r\n1 cup milk\r\n2 tsp flour\r\n1 cup icing sugar\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n1/2 cup margarine\r\n1 tsp vanilla','350  2 layer pans\r\n\r\nMake a paste with the food coloring and cocoa and set aside\r\n\r\nCream the sugar and margarine together and add the eggs. Add the cocoa and food coloring paste and mix well.  Add buttermilk alternately with flour and salt.  Add vanilla.  Combine the baking soda with the vinegar and fold into the cake batter.  Do not beat.  Cook.\r\n\r\nFrosting......\r\nCombine the milk and the flour and cook over medium heat stirring constantly until thick.  Cool\r\n\r\nCream the icing sugar and butter and margarine until smooth and add in vanilla.  Add to the cooled mixture\r\n\r\nFrost cake and put in fridge to set.','It will take a few minutes to combine the food coloring and cocoa...take the time.....\r\n\r\nIf you don\'t have buttermilk use one cup of milk and add in 1 tbsp of vinegar and let it sit for a few minutes.....using real buttermilk is better though.\r\n\r\nWhen I make the icing I alway make a little more than they say....we do like our icing!!!',8),(19,'Ultimate Chocolate Cake','butter and flour to coat cake pan\r\n\r\n400 grams semi sweek chocolate\r\n1 cup whipping cream\r\n2 tbsp Kirsch\r\n2 tbsp Grand Marnier\r\n1 tsp ground cinnamon\r\n6 large eggs\r\n1/2 brown sugar\r\n','350 approx. 1 hour\r\n\r\nButter a 23 cm cake pan.  Place wax paper on top and flour.\r\n\r\nWarm a large basin by filling with boiling water.\r\n\r\nMelt the chocolate.  Set aside.  Whisk the cream until soft peaks and stir in Kirsch, Grand Marnier and cinnamon.\r\n\r\nBreak the egss into the heated basig and add the sugar.  Beat until thick and fluffy.  Add the melted chocolate a little at a time.  Once this mixture is cooled add the cream.  Pour into the tin.  Put the tin in a baking dish and add boiling water half way up the sides.  Bake for 1 hour or until set on the outside and soft in the center.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','This is a great rich chocolate cake with no flour in it.  Serve it with a little whipped cream and fresh fruit, I like raspberries with it. To dress it up sift a little icing sugar on the plate and put a slice of cake on top.\r\n\r\nThis recipe came from Auntie June',8),(20,'Lazy Daisy Oatmeal Cake','1-1/2 cups boiling water\r\n1 cup oatmeal\r\n1/2 cup soft butter\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n1 cup brown sugar\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n2 eggs\r\n1-1/3 cups flour\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n3/4 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/4 tsp nutmeg\r\n\r\nFrosting......\r\n1/4 cup melted butter\r\n1/2 cup brown sugar\r\n3 tbsp cream \r\n1/2 cup pecans\r\n3/4 cup coconut','9x9 pan   350  50-55 minutes\r\n\r\nPour boiling water over oatmeal, cover and let stand for 20 minutes.  Beat butter until it\'s creamy and gradually add in sugar and beat til stiff.  Blend in vanilla and eggs.  Add oatmeal and mix well.  Add dry ingredients.\r\n\r\nFrosting.....\r\n\r\nMix all ingredients together in pot and mix over medium heat until boiling.  Spread over warm cake.','Auntie Joanne gave me this recipe.  It is a nice heavy cake.  If I don\'t have cream for the icing I have used carnation milk or just plain milk.',8),(21,'Sourdough Cookies','2 eggs\r\n1 cup sour cream\r\n4 cups flour\r\n1 cup margarine\r\n1-1/2 cup white sugar\r\n2 tsp baking soda\r\n','350   10 minutes\r\n\r\nCream butter and sugar together.  Add eggs and beat well.  Add dry ingredients.  You can either roll these cookies out and cut into shapes or drop onto sheet','These are the cookies that we always made at the manor for Valentines day or St. Patricks day.  You can make a simple icing to go on them, or between them if you want.  I also made them for your class Halloween parties.',9),(22,'Marshmallow Guck','30 coloured marshmallows \r\n2 cups graham crumbs\r\n1/2 cup marachino cherries\r\n15 oz eagle brand (1-1/2 cans approx)\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n2-1/2 cups sweetened coconut','Mix together all the ingredients except for the coconut.  Make sure it is well mixed.  \r\n\r\nDrop and roll in coconut.','I use the miniature marshmallows.  Take approx. 3/4 of a bag.  I usually add more cherries just because I like them.\r\n\r\nInstead of ending up with 1/2 can of eagle brand left over you can either add extra of everything else and use 2 cans or cut back on things and just use one can.  Don\'t put all the graham crumbs in at once, add them after you put in the eagle brand and go by texture if you are just going to use one can.\r\n\r\nI also don\'t drop them and roll them in the coconut.  I use a pan.  I put half the coconut on the bottom of the pan and press the guck into the pan and then press the rest of the coconut on top.  Just cut it into pieces and roll the raw edges in the coconut left behind in the pan.',9),(23,'Peanut Butter Balls','1 cup peanut butter\r\n1 cup icing sugar\r\n1/2 cup chopped glace cherries\r\n2 tbsp butter\r\n1/2 to 1 cup chopped pecan\r\n\r\nMilk chocolate bars','Mix the peanut butter and butter together.  Add in the icing sugar and mix well.  Add in the cherries and nuts.  Roll into balls.  Chill and dip in melted milk chocolate.  Cool on wax paper.','For the milk chocolate you can either use plain milk chocolate bars or you can use the milk chocolate chips.  I usually put the dough in the fridge for about 1/2 an hour before I roll it into balls to firm up the dough.  Once I roll the balls I freeze them before I dip them in chocolate.  I use 2 spoons to dip the balls with.',9),(24,'Shortbread Cookies','1 lb. butter\r\n1/2 cup corn starch\r\n1/2 cup icing sugar\r\n3-1/2 cups flour','350  approx. 7-8 minutes\r\n\r\nCream butter.  Sift dry ingredients together.  Blend butter and dry ingredients together.','I make these with a cookie press.  You could probably roll them out with icing sugar and cut them out but I have never tried this.\r\n\r\nThis recipe makes lots of cookies.  You would probably have enough if you cut the recipe in half.  Watch them while they are baking because you don\'t want them to get brown.  \r\n\r\nYou can add food coloring to color the cookies.  I also put cherries on the top or candies to decorate for the holidays.',9),(25,'Chow Mein Noodle Chocolate  Cookies','6 oz. semi-sweet chocolate chips\r\n6 oz. butterscotch chips\r\n1 can chow mein noodles\r\ncoconut','Mix all the ingredients together and drop with a spoon onto a wax paper lined cookie sheet.  Chill.','The amount of coconut is up to you.  Add it in last to see how loose the cookies are.',9),(26,'Oatmeal Cookies with Jam','2 cups margarine\r\n1-1/2 cups white sugar\r\n2 eggs\r\n2 cups flour\r\n2 tsp baking soda\r\n2 tsp cream of tartar\r\n4 cups oatmeal','350   8-10 minutes\r\n\r\nCream together the margarine and butter until light and fluffy.  Add the eggs and the rest of the dry ingredients adding in the oatmeal last.\r\n\r\nPut raspberry jam in between the cookies while they are still warm.','This was your dad\'s favorite cookie.  The first time I made them for him I didn\'t put any flour in.  Needless to say they just spread all over the cookie sheet and made a mess.  I was not impressed....your dad just laughed......once I realized that I did not have flour written on the recipe everything was ok......',9),(27,'Peanut Butter Cookies','1 cup margarine\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n1 cup brown sugar\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n2 beaten eggs\r\n1 cup peanut butter\r\n3 cups flour\r\n2 tsp baking soda\r\npinch salt','375   10 minutes   \r\n\r\nCream the margarine and sugar together with vanilla.  Add the eggs and beat thoroughly. Stir in the peanut butter.  Add dry ingredients.  Roll dough into balls and place on ungreased pan.  Press with fork.','I think this is Bushkas recipe, although I don\'t think I have ever been able to make them as good as she does......must be a grammas magic touch that makes the difference.',9),(28,'Chocolate Chip Oatmeal Cookies','1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n1/2 tap salt\r\n1 tsp cinnamon\r\n1 cup margarine\r\n3/4 cup brown sugar\r\n1/2 cup white sugar\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n2 eggs\r\n2 cups oatmeal\r\n2 cups chocolate chips','375    10-12 minutes\r\n\r\nCream together the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.  Add in the vanilla and eggs and mix well.  Add the dry ingredients and mix well adding in the oatmeal and chocolate chips last.\r\n\r\nDrop onto greased cookie sheet.','If you want to make these cookies really rich you can use butter or mix half butter half margarine and of course you can always put in extra chocolate chips.  If your Dad and Auntie Joanne were mad at Nana and they were making these cookies they would always put in twice as many chocolate chips thinking it was a way to get back at their mom.......hahah good joke she loves chocolate.....',9),(29,'Danish Pastry','1-1/2 cups soft butter\r\n4-1/2 cups four\r\n2 pkgs yeast (2 tbsps)\r\n1/4 cup warm water\r\n1 cup cold milk\r\n1 egg\r\n3 tbsp sugar\r\n1/2 tsp salt','375  8-12 minutes\r\n\r\nMix butter and 1/2 cup flour til well blended.  Refrigerate while preparing yeast dough.  \r\n\r\nIn mixing bowl dissolve yeast in water.  Add milk, egg, sugar and salt.  Mix til blended.  Stir in enough flour until the dough is stiff.  Turn onto floured counter and knead til smooth.  Roll into rectangle 6&quot;x12&quot; (approx.)  Take the butter and flour mixture and cover the top of the yeast dough.  Fold over from one end of the dough to the other.  Roll and pound lightly on the dough.  Roll doll into rectangle 12&quot;x16&quot;.  Fold in 3rds and cover and put in fridge to chill for 30 minutes.Remove from the fridge and pound the dough and roll into a 16&quot; square and fold in 3rds again .  Chill again for 30 minutes.  Repeat the same process 3 more times.  After final pounding roll dough into 24&quot;x36&quot;.  But into desired shapes.  Let rise in a cool place for 45 minutes.','I don\'t follow the rules as to the size it is to be rolled out.  Take a guess because it really doesn\'t matter all that much.  You do have to do the process 5 times though so that the butter gets spread in between the layers of dough so you have the light flaky pastry in the end.\r\n\r\nBefore I cook them I put a little indentation in the middle and put a spoonful of raspberry jam.\r\n\r\nWhen you are cooking them keep an eye on them.  You don\'t want them too brown.\r\n\r\nOnce they are out of the oven let them cool and them drizzle with a little icing made up of icing sugar and water and almond flavoring.\r\n\r\nThis is a recipe that Gramma got from her friend Elli Kivi.',10),(30,'Butter Tart Filling','1 cup raisins\r\n1/2 cup brown sugar\r\n1/2 cup corn syrup\r\n2 tbsp butter\r\n1 beaten egg\r\n1/2 tsp vanilla','Put the raisin in a bowl and cover with bowling water.  Drain.  While the raisins are still warm add all the other ingredients and mix well.  Put spoonful in each tart shell.','This recipe does not make the sticky run down your arm type of butter tarts.  This is grammas recipe.  I personally have never been very successful in making butter tarts......but I will keep trying.',10),(31,'Marzinar Tarts','Pastry......\r\n1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1 tsp baking powder\r\n1/4 cup white sugar\r\n1/2 cup soft butter\r\n1 egg\r\n\r\nFilling......\r\n1 cup ground almonds\r\n2/3 cup white sugar\r\n2 eggs\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n1/2 tsp almond extract\r\nraspberry jam','greased tart pan  300    30-35 minutes\r\n\r\nPastry.....\r\nSift flour, baking powder and sugar together.  Cut in the butter and add the egg.  Knead in bowl and chill.\r\n\r\nFilling......\r\nBlend the butter and sugar.  Add the egg and beat well.  Add almond extract and the ground almonds.\r\n\r\nRoll out the pastry and put into tin tart shells which have been greased.  Put a spoonful of raspberry jam in the bottom of each tart and top with the almond mixture.   Bake.','This dough can be rolled out more than once but the more times you roll it out the tougher the pastry will get.  I usually make more of the almond filling, I probably make about 1-1/2 recipes.  I found what the recipe calls for is just not enough.  Keep an eye on them while they are baking because you don\'t want them to get too brown.  \r\n\r\nAfter you take them out of the oven let them cool slightly and then take them out of the pans and cool on a rack.',10),(32,'Bushka\'s Refrigerator Rolls','1/3 lb tender flake\r\n1 cup boiling water\r\n1 cup cold water\r\n6 cups flour\r\n3/4 cups white sugar\r\n2 tsp yeast + 1/2 cup warm water+1 tsp sugar\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n1 tsp almond flavor (optional)','350-375   20 minutes\r\n\r\nCream tender flake and sugar, add boiling water and cool.  Add yeast into 1/2 cup warm water with 1 tsp sugar.  Add yeast to tender flake mixture and add cold water.  Add eggs and mix well.  Add flour and salt.  Knead well.  Place in refrigerator overnight or until wanted. Roll into desired shapes and let rise for 1 hour.  Bake in hot oven for 20 minutes.\r\n\r\nThe dough may be kept for several days.','These are the dinner rolls that Bushka always made into flowers, birds, slip knots and twists.  She used to brush them with an egg wash and sometimes put sesame seeds on the top.  They are similar to egg bread rolls.',5),(33,'Barbecue Sauce','1 cup ketchup\r\n8 tbsp chili sauce\r\n4 tbsp brown sugar\r\n4 tbsp butter\r\n4 tbsp chopped onion\r\n8 tsp mustard\r\n4 tsp worcheshire sauce\r\ndash garlic powder\r\n8 slices of lemon (1 lemon)','Put all the ingredients in a pot and bring to boil.  Allow to simmer for 30 minutes.','This is the recipe that I got from Auntie June.  I used it for years....but to be honest....I have found a PC extra spicy bottled sauce that I like better......',11),(34,'Veal Parmesan Sauce','2 large cans tomatoes - drained\r\n1 medium onion\r\n1 green pepper\r\n2 cloves garlic\r\n1 lge can tomato paste\r\n1 small can tomato paste\r\n1 tsp oregano\r\n1 tsp salt \r\n1 tbsp white sugar\r\n\r\n','Put all the ingredients in the blender and blend.  Put on the stove and let simmer for about 30 minutes.','Put one can of tomatoes in the blender, add the onion and green pepper and blend.  Put the second can in and add the tomato paste and seasonings then add to the first batch.  It is too much to put in the blender all at once and you have to mix the wet and dry so the blender will work.',11),(35,'Cinnamon Buns','1/4 cup white sugar\r\n1/2 cup warm water\r\n1 pkg yeast (1 tbsp)\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n1/4 cup butter\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n2 eggs - beaten\r\n4 cups all purpose flour (approx)\r\n\r\nFilling.....\r\n1 cup butter\r\n1-1/2 cups packed brown sugar\r\n1 cup chopped pecan\r\n1 tbsp cinnamon\r\n','Dissolve 1 tsp of the sugar in warm water; sprinkle in yeast.  Let stand for 10 minutes.  Meanwhile in small saucepan, heat milk, remaining sugar, butter and salt until butter has melted; let cool to lukewarm.  In large bowl combine eggs, milk mixture and yeast mixture.\r\n\r\nUsing electric mixer, gradually beat in 1-1/2 cups of the flour; beat for 2 minutes or until smooth.  With wooden spoon gradually stir in enough flour to make soft, slightly sticky dough that comes away from the sides of the bowl. On lightly floured surface knead dough for 7-10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.  Place in large greased bowl, turning to grease all over; cover with plastic. Let rise in warm place for 1 to 2 hours (or in fridge over night) or until double in bulk and impression remains when fingertips are pressed into dough.  PUnch down the dough\r\n\r\nFilling.....\r\nIn a saucepan over medium heat, melt 3/4 cup of the butter with 3/4 cup of the sugar whisking until smooth.  Pour into greased 13x9 baking dish.  Sprinkle with half the pecans and set aside.  Combine remaining sugar, pecans and cinnamon, set aside.\r\n\r\nOn lightly floured surface, roll out dough into 18x14 rectangle (approx)   Brush will all but 2 tbsp melted butter leaving 1/2 inch border uncovered; sprinkle with sugar mixture.  Staring at long side, tighly roll up, pinching seam to seal.  Brush with remaining butter.  Cut into 15 pieces; place cut sides down in pan.  Cover and let rise for 1 hour or until doubled.\r\n\r\nBake in 375 oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until crusts are golden and tops sound hollow when tapped.  Let stand in pan for 3 minutes. Invert onto serving platter, scrapping off any remaining filling in pan to drizzle over buns.','This is the recipe for our favorite cinnamon buns.  As usual however, we like them sweeter and stickier so I usually make 1 and 1/2 times the sauce.  I also put marachino cherries in the bottom of the pan and in the buns.  ',5),(36,'Graham Cream Pie','Crumb Crust....\r\n300 ml graham crumbs\r\n50 ml white sugar\r\n100 ml melted margarine\r\n\r\nFilling.....\r\n125 ml granulated sugar\r\n30 ml cornstarch\r\n15 ml flour\r\n1 ml salt\r\n500 ml milk\r\n3 egg yolks slightly beaten (keep egg whites)\r\n15 ml butter\r\n5 ml vanilla ','Crust....\r\nCombine graham crumbs, sugar and butter.  Press into bottom and sides of 9&quot; pie plate.  Bake in 375 oven for 8 minutes\r\n\r\nFilling.....\r\nIn saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.  Stir in milk (use a wisk)  Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixtrue thickens and comes to a boil; boil 2 minutes.  Blend a little of the hot mixture into the egg yolks, then stir yolks back into remaining hot mixture cook 1 minute longer stirring constantly.  Blend in butter and vanilla.  Cool 10 minutes; pour into crumb crust.  Cool to room temperature.\r\n\r\nMeringue.....\r\nBeat 3 egg whites until soft peaks form.  Gradually add 50 ml white sugar beating until stiff and shiny.  Spreak meringue over cooled filling to meet edge of crust.  Bake at 425 for 5 minutes or until lightly brown.  Cool at room temperature 3 hours before serving.','When you are making the filling whisk all the flour into the milk so there are  no lumps so you will have a nice smooth custard.',25),(37,'Curried Chicken','4-6 chicken breasts\r\n1/2 cup flour\r\n2 tsp salt\r\n1 tsp curry powder\r\n1/2 tsp paprika\r\n1/4 tsp ground ginger\r\n1/4 tsp pepper\r\n1/4 cup margarine\r\n2 cups chopped apples\r\n1 small onion chopped\r\n1/2 cup sweetened coconut\r\n2 cups chicken broth\r\n1/2 cup light cream','Combine flour, salt, curry powder,paprika, ginger and pepper.  Coat chicken with mixture.  Melt butter, brown chicken, cook 20 minutes and set aside.  Add apples, onion, and coconut to drippings.  Cook 5 minutes.  Blend 1/4 flour (mixed with spices) to chicken broth and stir until smooth.  Add to ingredients in the skillet.  Cook until thickened about 5 minutes.  Add cream.  Replace chicken.\r\n\r\nServe with rice.','I always use much more curry powder but it depends on how curry you like it (4 tbsp approx.)  I also add a can of pineapple to the sauce just before I put the cream in, I also add in the juice.\r\n\r\nThis sauce freezes nicely.',23),(38,'Lasagna','9 or 10 lasagna noodles\r\n1 tbsp oil\r\n1/2 cup chopped onion\r\n1-1/2 to 2 lbs. ground chuck\r\n1 tsp garlic salt\r\n1 (10 oz) can tomato soup\r\n2 small cans tomato paste\r\n1/2 to 3/4 cup coffee\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n1/4 tsp pepper\r\n1/2 cup sliced mushrooms\r\n1/4 tsp oregano\r\n16 oz creamed cottage cheese\r\n12-16 oz mozzarella cheese - grated\r\n1/2 cup parmesan cheese\r\n','Cook noodles.\r\nHeat oil and add onion and ground beef.  Cook until meat is browned. Drain fat.  Add next 8 ingredients.  Simmer 10 minutes.  Oil dish and spread bottom of pan with 1/3 of the sauce, noodles, 1/2 motz, 1/2 parmesan, 1/2 cottage cheese.  Repeat layers ending with noodles.  \r\n\r\nCover and bake at 350 for 20 and then uncover and bake until bubbling.','This is grammas recipe. I think the secret ingredient is the coffee so don\'t forget it!',13),(39,'Honey Garlic Chicken Wings','3/4 cup packed brown sugar\r\n3 tbsp soya sauce\r\n1 cup hot water\r\n1 clove garlic - I would put 3\r\n1/4 tsp dry ginger\r\nsalt and pepper\r\n','350  1-2 hours\r\n\r\nCombine all the ingredients and dissolve sugar. ','I usually put my wings in the oven for a couple of minutes without the sauce to dry them off so the sauce sticks to them better.  I also put more garlic than the recipe calls for.  One clove is not garlicky enough.\r\n\r\nIf you are in a hurry and don\'t have the time to cook them in the oven you can put them in an electric frying pan.  Put them on high without the top on and let it boil.  It will take about 1 hr.\r\n\r\nYou can also use this sauce on chicken thighs if you don\'t want the hassle of little wings.  (remove the skin from the thighs)',23),(40,'Pork Tenderloin Marinade','2 lbs pork tenderloin (2 tenderloins)\r\n2 tbsp soya sauce\r\n2 tbsp white sugar\r\n1 tbsp sherry (you can also use wine)\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/2 tsp cinnamon','Combine all the ingredients together and rub on the pork.  Let stand for approx. 2 hours to marinate turning often.\r\n\r\nCook the meat slowly under the broiler turning often.  Put on the lowest rack in the oven and leave the door slightly open.','This can be made and kept wrapped in the fridge for 1 week or so.',11),(41,'Penne a la Vodka','1 tbsp vegetable oil\r\n1 small onion chopped\r\n3 cloves garlic finely chopped\r\n1/2 tsp hot pepper flakes (or to your taste)\r\n28 oz. can tomatoes, undrained, chopped\r\n1 cup whipping cream\r\n1/4 cup vodka\r\nsalt and pepper\r\npenne noodles\r\n1/4 cup parmesan cheese\r\n2 tbsp fresh parsley chopped (optional)','Heat the oil in a large pot over medium heat.  Stir in onion, garlic and hot pepper flakes and cook approx. 4 minutes or until softened but not brown.  Add in the tomatoes and bring to a boil.  Reduce the heat and simmer approx. 10 minutes or until thickened.  Add cream, vodka, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.  Reduce the heat and simmer 5 min.\r\n\r\nCook penne noodles.  Stir pasta into sauce and turn heat off and let stand on element approx. 5 minutes.  Serve topped with parmesan cheese and parsley.','I cook the tomato sauce on the stove longer than the 10 minutes to allow it to thicken and the flavor to enhance.  It will depend on how liquid the tomatoes are.  \r\n\r\nThis is a recipe from Auntie Paula.',14),(42,'Lazy Man Perogies','9 lasagne noodles\r\n\r\n2 cups cottage cheese\r\n1 egg\r\ndash onion salt\r\n\r\n1 cup shredded cheddar cheese\r\n2 cups mashed potatoes\r\npepper\r\n\r\n1 cup butter\r\n1 cup chopped onion\r\n','350   30 minutes\r\n\r\nCook lasagne noodles\r\n\r\nMix together the cottage cheese, egg, salt.\r\n\r\nCook potatoes and mash adding in the cheddar cheese\r\n\r\nIn frying pan cook the onions in the butter.\r\n\r\nTo put together begin with lasagne noodles onthe bottom.  Add a layer of the cottage cheese mixture and then put another layer of noodles. On top of the noodles put a layer of the mashed potato mixture and then finish with a layer of lasagne noodles.  On the top put the onions and butter.','I think these are really good when you need a perogy fix but don\'t have the time or the inclination to make real ones.',15),(43,'Perogies','10-20 lbs of potatoes\r\nvelveeta cheese\r\n\r\nDough........\r\n2 cups flour\r\n1 cup mashed potatoes\r\n2 eggs\r\npinch salt','Peel and boil potatoes.  Mash until very smooth and add in velveeta cheese and whip until melted and to desired flavor.\r\n\r\nDough......\r\nMix the flour, mashed potatoes, eggs and salt together.  Knead until smooth.  Let relax for 30 minutes.\r\n\r\nEither use a perogy maker or cut squares of desired size and put the potato mixture in the middle and seal shut.\r\n\r\nTo cook...bring water to a boil and gently add in perogies.  Cook until they float on the top and are soft to touch.','This is bushkas recipe.  When I make the dough I use the mashed potatoes that have the cheese in them..I find it makes a more tender dough and of course makes it tastier.  The amount of cheese that you put in depends on your.  Taste the potatoes as you add the cheese until you get the taste you want.  We like our cheesy so I put in quite a bit of cheese. If they aren\'t cheesy enough they are pretty tasteless.\r\n\r\nYou can also fry them after they are boiled if you like them a little crispy.  \r\n\r\nFry up either onions and butter or some bacon and put on the top of them to serve.',15),(44,'Baileys Irish Cream','3 eggs\r\n1 can eagle brand\r\n2 - large containers whipping cream\r\n1-3/4 cups rye (whisky)\r\n1-1/2 tsp chocolate syrup','Combine all the ingredients and refrigerate.  \r\n\r\nCan be keep in the fridge for 6 weeks.','',22),(45,'Caramel Sauce','1-1/2 cups packed brown sugar\r\n2/3 cup corn syrup\r\n1/4 cup butter\r\n\r\n1/2 cup whipping cream','Put all the ingredients except the whipping cream into a large pot and bring to a boil stirring to be sure the sugar is dissolved.  Boil for approx. 30 minutes (soft ball stage)\r\n\r\nPour into a bowl, add the whipping cream and whip until creamy.','Yummy.....this is Nanas recipe that we put on chocolate cake.  ',11),(46,'Almond Filled Buns','<ol>\r\n    <li>4-1/2 to 5 cups flour</li>\r\n    <li>1/2 cup white sugar</li>\r\n    <li>1/2 tsp ground cardamom</li>\r\n    <li>1/4 tsp salt 1 pkg active dry yeast (1 tbsp)</li>\r\n    <li>1-1/4 cups milk</li>\r\n    <li>1/2 cup butter</li>\r\n    <li>1 egg Almond Filling......</li>\r\n    <li>2 cups icing sugar</li>\r\n    <li>2 tbsp butter</li>\r\n    <li>2 tbsp ground almonds</li>\r\n    <li>1 - 2 tbsps milk</li>\r\n    <li>1/2 tsp almond extract</li>\r\n</ol>','<ol>\r\n    <li>Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, cardamom, salt and yeast. Over low heat, heat milk, butter and 1/4 cup water until very warm but not hot. With mixer on low speed, gradually pour liquid into dry ingredients and beat until just mixed. Beat 2 minutes (yeast should be completely dissolved). Beat in egg, 1 cup flour or enough to make a thick batter. Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough (2 cups)</li>\r\n    <li>On well floured surface knead the dough until smooth and elastic about 10 mins adding more flour if needed. Form dough into a ball and place in a greased bowl. Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size (approx. 1-1/2 hrs.)</li>\r\n    <li>Punch down dough by pushing the centre of dough with fist then pushing edges of dough into the centre. Turn dough onto slightly floured surface. Cover with towel and let rest for 15 minutes.</li>\r\n    <li>Grease 2 lge cookie sheets. With lightly floured rolling pin roll dough 1&quot; thick. Cut dough into rounds. Place 2&quot; apart (makes approx.. 24) Cover with a towel and let rise in a warm place until double (approx. 40 min)</li>\r\n    <li>Preheat the oven to 350. Bake approx. 20 minutes or until lightly browned.</li>\r\n    <li>Prepare filling. Add all ingredients and whip together to make light and fluffy.</li>\r\n    <li>Put filling in buns once they have cooled.</li>\r\n</ol>','<p>This is a recipe that I got from Gramma. I believe it is a Swedish recipe. I had written this recipe on a piece of paper...hand written and at the bottom your dad had put a note.... From: Rene Mick My Way of Cooking...hahahah what a joke...but he loved these buns. So I don\'t think that I really need to tell you that we are all icing freaks so you need to at least double the recipe for the filling. I also put in more of the ground almonds than they call for because I prefer it that way. When you bake the buns keep an eye on them because on the second and third batches they will cook quicker usually because the oven is hotter. Check the bottom of a bun to make sure that it is brown.</p>',5),(47,'Buffalo Chicken Dip','1 (10 oz) can chunk chicken drained\r\n1 (8 oz) pkg. cream cheese softened\r\n1/2 cup ranch dressing\r\n1/4 cup franks hot sauce\r\n3/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese','Heat the chicken and hot saucein a skillet over medium heat, heat through.  Stir in the cream cheese and ranch dressing.  Cook, stirring until well blended and warm.  Mix in half of the shredded cheese, and transfer the mixture to an oven proof dish.  Sprinkle the remaining cheese on the top and put in a 325 oven until bubbly.  Can be served with either crackers or celery.','',18),(48,'Sucre a la Creme','4 cups packed brown sugar\r\n1 cup whipping cream\r\n4 tbsps butter\r\n4 tbsps flour\r\n2 tsps baking powder\r\n1/2 cup nuts (optional)','Mix everything in a deep bowl and microwave on high for 12 minutes mixing every 3 minutes.  \r\n\r\nUsing an electric mixer mix for approx 10 minutes on high until thickened and starts to firm up.\r\n\r\nPlace in a greased pan and put in the fridge.','I have never been able to make sucre a la creme in the tradition french method. This recipe was given to me by a woman I worked with who said it works for &quot;everyone&quot;......and it does....',19),(49,'Basic Belgian Waffles','Makes approx. 20 4 inch waffles so you might want to cut the recipe down......\r\n\r\n4 cups all purpose flour\r\n4 tbsps white sugar\r\n2 tbsps baking powder\r\n1-1/2 tsp salt\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n3-1/2 cups milk\r\n2/3 cup vegetable oil\r\n4 large eggs','Place ingredients in a large mixing bowl and combine until well blended and smooth.  Let the batter sit for 5 minutes before using.','Wonderful either for breakfast just with maple syrup or for dessert with ice cream, cream, chocolate sauce, maple syrup and fruit.  You can pretty much put anything you want on them.',17),(50,'Chocolate Pecan Tart','<p>Crust.... 1-1/2 cups four 3 tbsps white sugar 1/2 cup crisco shortening 1 egg yolk 1/4 cup milk 1 egg white lightly beaten 2 squares semi sweet chocolate (2 oz) Filling... 3 eggs 2/3 cup white sugar 1 cup corn syrup 1/2 cup crisco shortening melted 2 cups pecan halves Decoration.... 2 squares semi sweet chocolate 1 tsp crisco</p>','<p>Crust.... Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Beat egg yolk and milk together. Add to dry ingredients, mixing to a smooth pastry with a fork. RESERVE 1 tbsp dough. Press remainder into bottom and sides of 10&quot; flan pan. Prick pastry with fork; brush with egg white. Chill 15 minutes. Bake at 450 for 8 minutes (no longer) Pastry should still be soft. Romove from oven and use reserved dough to press into any cracks that have formed. Cook slightly, then spread melted chocolate evenly over bottom of crust. Filling.... Beat eggs, sugar, corn syrup and melted shortening together thoroughly. Stir in pecans. Pour into crust and bake at 350 for 35 to 40 minutes or just until set and golden. Cool. Decoration..... Melt chocolate squares and shortening together until smooth. Drizzle over tart.</p>','<p>This is a recipe that I made a couple of times and it had a nicer flavor with the chocolate than just a regular pecan pie.</p>',25),(51,'Chocolate Dipped Coconut Candies','1 cup smooth mashed potatoes\r\n1 lb icing sugar\r\n4 cups shredded coconut\r\n2 tsp vanilla extract\r\n1/8 tap salt\r\n\r\n5 squares unsweetened chocolate\r\n','In a large bowl, combine poatoes and sugar.  Stir in coconut, vanilla and salt.  Freeze 30 minutes until firm.  Shape candies into 1&quot; squares or into triangles.  Place on baking sheet lined with wax paper.  Freeze 30 minutes until firm.  \r\n\r\nMelt chocolate and dip part of candy.  Chill until firm.  Store in the fridge.','I have never made these but Gramma used to make these and I loved them.  They are very sweet and coconutty.',19),(52,'Triple Chocolate Raspberry Fantasy','Brownie Layer.....\r\n3 squares unsweetened chocolate\r\n2 squares bittersweet chocolate\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n2 eggs\r\n1-1/4 lightly packed brown sugar\r\n3/4 cup flour\r\n1/4 tsp baking powder\r\n\r\nWhite Chocolate Layer.....\r\n1 - 250 gram pkg. cream cheese\r\n2/3 cup icing sugar\r\n2 tbsps raspberry liqueur (optional)\r\n3 squares white chocolate, melted and cooled\r\n1 egg\r\n\r\nTopping.....\r\n1/2 cup raspberry jam\r\n1/2 cup whipping cream\r\n4 squares bittersweet chocolate, chopped\r\nwhite chocolate curls and raspberries for garnish','Brownie Layer.....\r\nMelt chocolates and butter over hto water or in microwave; stir until completely melted.  Beat eggs and brown sugar on high speed of electric mixer for 5 minutes or until thick and lemon coloured.  Fold in chocolate mixture, flour and baking powder.  Pour into greased and floured 10&quot; pie plate or springform pan.\r\n\r\nWhite Chocolate Layer....\r\nBeat cream cheese, icing sugar, liqueur, chocolate and egg in meadium bowl with electric mixer until smoothly blended.  Randomly spoon white mixture onto brownie layer leaving space between each spoonful.  Bake at 325 for 45-55 minutes or until set and toothpick comes out almost clean.  Cool\r\n\r\nTopping.....\r\nSpread jam evenly over entire surface of pie.  Heat cream with chocolate over hot water or in microwave, stir  until melted and smooth.  Pour over top of pie spreading evenly.  Chill and set glaze.  ','This is a really nice variation on a brownie.  Elegant enough for company especially with the curls and raspberries on top.',6),(53,'Peanut Butter Bars....like Reeses','2 cups graham cracker crumbs\r\n1-1/2 cups icing sugar\r\n1 cup chunky peanut butter\r\n1/2 cup margarine, melted\r\n1/2 cup chopped salted peanuts\r\n1-1/2 cups milk chocolate chips','Lighlty grease 11&quot;x7&quot; baking pan.  In large mixing bowl combine all ingredients except for the chips.  Press mixture evenly in prepared pan.\r\n\r\nMelt chips over heat or in microwave stirring constatnly.  Spread chocolate over bars.  Chill until set before cutting.','When you\'re craving peanut butter and chocolate this is a quick and easy &quot;fix&quot;.',6),(54,'Valentine Berries and Cream','8 squares semi sweet chocolate\r\n1 tbsp shortening\r\n2 pkgs cream cheese (3 oz each)\r\n1/2 cup butter or margarine\r\n1-1/2 cups icing sugar\r\n1/3 cup cocoa\r\n2 tbsps milk\r\n1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n2-1/2 cups whipping cream whipped, divided\r\n1-1/2 cups fresh strawberries','Line a 9&quot; heart shaped or square baking pan with foil; set aside.  In a heavy saucepan over low heat melt chocolate and shortening; stir until smooth.  Pour into prepared pan, swirling to coat the bottom and 1-1/2&quot; up the sides.  Refirgerate for 1 minute, then swirl the chocolate to reinforce sides of pan.  Refirgerate for 30 min or until firm.  Using foil ift from pan, remove foil and place on serving plate.\r\n\r\nIn a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and butter until smooth.  Combine icing sugar and cocoa; add to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.  Beat until smooth.  Gently fold in 2/3 of the whipped cream into the cream cheese mixture.  Spoon into heart.  Use a pastry bag to pipe the remaining cream on the top.  Garnish with the berries.','This is the recipe for the chocolate mousse that you girls like. The first time I made it I made the chocolate box which I thought was alot of work....so...after that I would just buy premade chocolate shells and fill them with the mousse...much much easier, quicker and just as good...no one will know the difference.\r\n\r\nInstead of the fresh fruit I would make a coulis of raspberries and drizzle it over the top.  To make a coulis mix together raspberries and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil....place in blender and puree.',7),(55,'Apple Stuffed Chicken Breast','2 tbsps + 1/4 cup pecan halves divided, and toasted if desired\r\n4 tbsp butter divided\r\n1 granny smith apple cored, diced about 2 cups\r\n1 medium onion chopped\r\n1 tbsp + 1 tsp chopped fresh parsley divided\r\n3/4 tsp dried marjoran, divided\r\n3/4 tsp garlic powder, divided\r\n1 tsp salt, divided\r\n1/2 tsp pepper, divided\r\n2 tbsps + 1/2 cup white riesling, divided\r\n3 tbsps plain dry breadcrumbs\r\n4 chicken breasts\r\n1/2 cup chicken broth\r\n1 tbsp flour\r\n1/2 cup whipping cream\r\n','Preheat oven to 375.  Chop 2 tbsps of pecans.  In nonstick skillet melt 1 tbsp butter over hedium heat.  Add apple, onion, 1 tbsp parsley, 1/2 tsp marjoram, 1/2 tsp garlic powder, 1/2 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper.  Cook until apple is tender, 4 min.  Stirin 2 tbsps wine; cook until absorbed.  Remove from the heat; stir in breadcrumbs and reserved pecans. Remove from skillet and cool 10 minutes.  Place each breast skin side down on surface.  Cut pocketin breasts.  Turn skin side up; fill with 1/4 of apple mixture.  Combine remaining parsley, marjoram, garlic powder, salt and pepper.  Set aside 1 tsp mixture; sprinkle remaining over chicken.  In nonstick skillet melt 1 tbsp butter.  Add chicken skin side down; cook until chicken is lightly browned.  Transfer to ungreased baking sheet; bake until meat juices run clear, about 30 minutes.  \r\n\r\nIn same skillet melt remaining butter.  Stir in reserved parsley mixture and wine; cook until blubbly about 2 min. Combine broth and flour until smooth; stir into skillet and boil.  Cook, stirring, one minute; stir in cream and remaining pecans.  Heat thoroughly','I made this when we had the grandparents all over for dinner.  It was a huge success.',23),(56,'Apple-of-Your-Eye Cheesecake','Crust......\r\n1 cup graham crumbs\r\n3 tbsps sugar\r\n1/2 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/4 cup butter melted\r\n2 tbsps finely chopped pecans\r\n\r\nFilling...\r\n3 pkgs (8 oz each) cream cheese\r\n3/4 cup white sugar\r\n3 eggs\r\n3/4 tsp vanilla extract\r\n\r\nTopping.....\r\n1-1/2 cups chopped peeled apples\r\n1 tbsp lemon juice\r\n1/4 cup white sugar\r\n1/2 tsp cinnamon\r\ncaramel ice cream topping ','Combine the first five ingredients;press onto the bottom of a lightly greased 9&quot; springform pan.  Bake at 350 for 10 minutes, cool.\r\n\r\nIn mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.  Add eggs; beat on low just until combines.  Stir in vanilla.  Pour over crust.\r\n\r\nToss apples with lemon juice, sugar and cinnamon; spoon over filling.  Bake at 350 for 55-60 minutes or until center is almost set.  Cool on rack for 10 min.  Carefully run a knife around edge of pan to loosen.  Drizzle with 4 tbsps caramel topping.  Cool for 1 hour.  Chill overnight.  Just before serving drizzle with more caramel sauce.  Store in the fridge.','I think besides the chocolate amaretto cheesecake this is the best one I have ever had....easy to make but everyone thinks it was hard to do.  ',7),(57,'Layered Vegetable Loaf','1st Layer\r\n\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 cup broccoli flowerettes, cook and finely chopped\r\n1 tbsp butter or margarine, softened\r\n1/2 grated cheddar cheese\r\n1/4 tsp onion salt\r\n\r\n2nd Layer\r\n\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 cup cooked rice\r\n1/4 finely chopped red pepper\r\n1 tbsp butter or margarine, softened\r\n1/2 cup grated mozzarella cheese\r\n1/4 tsp onion salt\r\n\r\n3rd Layer\r\n\r\n2 eggs \r\n1 cup cooked mashed carrots\r\n1 tbsp margarine or butter, softened\r\n1/2 cup grated cheddar cheese\r\n1/4 tsp onion salt','1st Layer\r\n\r\nSpoon beat eggs in bowl.  Measure broccoli after it has been cooked and chopped . Add to eggs along with next 3 ingredients.  Pack into well greased gread pan.\r\n\r\n2nd Layer\r\n\r\nSpoon beat eggs.  Add next 5 ingredients.  Spoon over broccoli layer.\r\n\r\n3rd Layer\r\n\r\nSpoon beat eggs.  Mix in next 4 ingredients.  Spread over rice layer.  Bake in 325 degree oven for about an hour or until an inserted knife comes out clean.  Unmold\r\n\r\n\r\n','This is a recipe that was made at our gourment club.  \r\n\r\nThere is a Cream Sauce that goes with this.  I don\'t usually make it because I don\'t think it is needed but here it is anyways.....\r\n\r\nCream Sauce\r\n\r\n2 tbsp butter or margarine\r\n2 tbsp all purpose flour\r\n1/4 tsp salt\r\nlight sprinkle of pepper\r\n1 cup milk\r\n\r\nMelt butter in saucepan.  Mix in flour, salt and pepper.  Add milk.  Stir until it boils and thickens.  Makes about 1 cup.\r\n\r\n',21),(58,'Spoom - Palate cleanser','1 cup sugar\r\n1/2 cup water\r\n4 egg whites, at room temp\r\n1 qt. lemon sherbet, softened','Early in day, or up to 1 week before serving, combine in a medium saucepan the sugar and the water.  Cook over medium heat just until the temp reaches 238 degrees F (114 C) on candy thermometer or until syrup forms thin threads when dropped from a spoon onto waxed paper.  Meanwhile, in a large bowl, with mixer beat the egg whites until soft peaks form.  Continue beating pouring hot syrup in a thin thread into whites.  Stir in the lemon sherbet.  Spoon into 12 freezer proof stemmed glasses or dessert dishes to about 3/4 full.  Cover and freeze.  To serve, at the table, pour a few tablespoons (30 ml) rose, white wine or champagne on top of each serving.','Obviously this was served at the &quot;gourment club&quot;  A little too upper scale to serve at a regular dinner......but when you are serving a nice meal and having a special evening it really is nice in between the courses.',17),(59,'Jezebel.....cracker spread','6 oz. jar pineapple preserves  170 g\r\n6 oz. jar orange marmalade     170 g\r\n4 oz. white horseradish        115 g\r\n1/2 tsp curry powder\r\n16 oz cream cheese','Combine first 4 ingredients. Chill.  spread pineapple mixture on top of cream cheese.  Serve as a spread with plain crackers.','Gourmet club recipe',18),(60,'Pumpernickel Bread Dip','1 pumpernickel bread\r\n10 oz chopped spinach\r\n1-1/2 cup sour cream\r\n1 cup mayonaise\r\n1 pkg. Knorr vegetable soup mix\r\n3 green onions chopped\r\n1 can water chestnuts, chopped','Cook spinach, and drain (although if you buy frozen spinach you don\'t need to take this step).  Squeeze spinach until it is dry.  Place spinach in bowl and combine with all other ingredients until well blended.\r\n\r\nHollow out the bread by cutting the top layer of the bread.  Then tear out all the bread in chunks.  These will be used later for dipping.\r\n\r\nPlace the spinach imixture in the hollow bread.  Cover and chill at least 2 hours.','First had this at our gourmet club.  Starting making this whenever we were doing a road trip.  Your dad and I liked the chunks but Lyndz and April would &quot;gingerly&quot; dab at the sauce and wouldn\'t eat any of the chunks....but now that you are &quot;mature&quot; adults you eat the chunks......',18),(61,'Strawberry Spinach Salad','2 bunches fresh spinach, washed, torn\r\n2 cups strawberries, halved\r\n\r\nDressing\r\n\r\n1/2 cup sugar\r\n2 tbsp sesame seeds\r\n1 tbsp poppy seeds\r\n1-1/2 tbsp minced onion\r\n1/4 cup worcestershire sauce\r\n1/4 tsp paprika\r\n1/2 cup vegetable oi\r\n1/4 cup cider vinegar','Toss spinach and strawberries.  Prepare dressing by combining all ingredients.  Mix well.  Pour over salad and serve.  Serves 10-12 ','Gourmet Club recipe.  Nice in the summer when nice ripe, tasty strawberries are in season.',16),(62,'Strawberry Delight','1 cup fresh strawberries (frozen can be used.\r\n2 oz. triple sec or strawberry liqueur\r\n2 oz vodka\r\n2 scoops vanilla or strawberry icecream\r\n1 cup chopped ice','Put alll ingredients into blender and blend well.  Pour into your favorite stenned glasses.  Garnish with small mint sprig.  \r\n\r\nFor children replace liquors with 7-Up.','Gourmet Club.  The name says it all...a delightful drink.  You can also just put it in a punch bowl for people to serve themselves.',22),(63,'Coffee Meringue Roll with Chocolate Sauce','4 egg whites\r\n3/4 cup white sugar\r\n1 tbsp ground roasted hazelnuts\r\n1 tbsp white sugar, extra\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\n3/4 cup whipping cream\r\n2 tsp instant coffee powder\r\n1 tbsp Kahlua or Tia Maria\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\nChocolate Sauce\r\n\r\n125 g semi sweet chocolate melted\r\n1/4 cup icing sugar\r\n300 ml carton whipping cream\r\n2 tbsp Kahlua or Tia Maria\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n','Prepare a cookie sheet, with sides, 25 cm x 30 cm by greasing, lining with parchment paper, greasing then dusting with cornstarch, shake tin to remove excess cornflour.\r\n\r\nBeat egg whites in small bowl until soft peaks form gradually adding sugar, beat until sugar is dissolved.  Spread mixture evenly in tin.  Sprinkle meringue evenly with combined hazelnuts and extra sugar.  Bake in moderate oven (350) for 10 minutes or until meringue is firm to touch.  Remove from oven, turn onto sheet of parchement paper, remove paper carefully and cool flat to room temp.  Spread meringue with filling, roll up carefully, serve roll sliced with sauce.\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\nBeat cream with combined coffee, kahlua and vanilla until firm peaks form, refrigerate until required.\r\n\r\nChocolate Sauce\r\n\r\nPlace chocolate in flowl stirn in sifted icing sugar, cfeam, kahlua and vanilla; stir until smooth','This is from an Australian cookbook.  Grampa who never really likes sweet rich desserts loves this one.  He always had more than one piece.\r\n\r\nFor your Dad, who didn\'t like coffee, I used to substitute more kahlua instead of the coffee, made it more of a chocolate flavor than coffee.',7),(64,'Layered Mocha Cake  ','375 g butter, softened\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n1-1/2 cups white sugar\r\n6 eggs\r\n2-1/4 cup self raising flour (1 cup flour with 2 tsp baking powder)\r\n1/3 cup corn starch\r\n1/3 cup cocoa\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n1 cup flaked almonds\r\n1/2 cup rum\r\n\r\nCoffee Cream\r\n\r\n1/2 cup custard powder\r\n1/2 cup white sugar\r\n2 cups milk\r\n2 tbsp instant coffee powder\r\n1/4 cup hot water\r\n500 g unsalted butter\r\n1/2 cup white sugar, extra\r\n\r\nChocolate Icing\r\n\r\n180 g semi sweet chocolate, chopped\r\n180 g unsalted butter\r\n','Step 1\r\n\r\nCream butter, vanilla and sugar until ight and fluffy, add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.  Combine sifted flour, corn starch and cocoa with milk, in 2 batches.  Divide cake mixture into 6 equal portions.  Spread 1 portion onto greased and floured tin 25 cm x 30 cm.  Bake in 350 degree oven for 10 min or until lightly browned.  Turn onto wire rack to cool.  Repeat until you have 6 layers.  Brush each layer with rum.\r\n\r\nCoffee Cream\r\n\r\nCombine custard pwder and sugar in pot, blend in milk, stir constantly over heat until mixture boils and thickens, cover surfance of mixture with plastic wrap to prevent skin forming, cool, refrigerate.  Combine coffe and water, cool.  Beat butter and extra sugar in lge bowl until light and fluffy, gradually beat in the cold custard and coffee mixture\r\n\r\nPlace one cake layer on serving platter and cover with 1/2 cup of coffee cream.  Continue layering with coffee cream until all cakes are used; do not spread coffee cream on top of cake.\r\n\r\nChocolate Icing\r\n  \r\nMelt chocolate and butter over hot water, cool to room temperature, beat with wwoocden spoon until thick and spreadable.\r\n\r\nSpread top of cake evenly with chocoalte icing.  Reserve about 1-1/2 cups of coffee cream for piping and writing.  Spread remaining coffee cream around sides of cake.  Press toasted almonds evenly over sides of cake.','This was your dads favorite cake.  I used to make this for him once a year on his birthday.....It seemed that the longer this cake stayed in the fridge the better it got so I would always try to make it a day ahead.  I made some changes to the recipe.  Since your dad didn\'t like coffee I would just add a little kahlua or melted chocolate to the coffee cream, either is good.  I also added some raspberry jam to each layer of the cake.  I would take raspberry jam and put it through a strainer to get out most of the seeds and then after I brushed the rum, or I would use amaretto, to each cake layer I would put a thin layer of raspberry on top.  Your Dad also believed that in some cases &quot;more is better&quot; so I would usually make 1-1/2 recipes of the butter cream.\r\n\r\nI never did put the almonds on.  I didn\'t think they were really necessary.  ',8),(65,'Asparagus Chicken','4 chicken breasts\r\n2 rashers bacon\r\n1 small onion\r\n15 g butter\r\n1/2 x 310 g asparagus cuts\r\nsalt &amp; pepper\r\n1 egg\r\n2 tbsp milk\r\ndry breadcrumbs\r\n60 g butter, extra\r\n2 tbsp oil\r\n\r\nParsley Butter\r\n\r\n125 g butter\r\n1 tbsp chopped parsley\r\n1 tbsp chopped shallots \r\nsalt, pepper','Remove skin from chicken breasts.  Carefully remove chicken meat from the bones, 8 individual pieces.  Gently and lightly pound each chicken breast.  Chop bacon finely; peel onion, chop finely.  Saute onion and bacon in butter until onion is transparent, add drained and finely chopped asparagus, salt and pepper, remove from the heat, cool.  Cut a pocket in each chicken breast, fill with asparagus mixture.  Coat chicken lightly with flour, dip in combined beaten egg and milk, coat well with bread crumbs.  Heat extra butter and oil in frying pan, add chicken, cook until golden brown on each side and cooked through.  Allow approximately 3 min. cooking time on each side.  Serve immediately with parsley butter.\r\n\r\nParsley Butter\r\n\r\nBeat butter until smooth and cramy, add parsley, shallots, salt and pepper, beat well.  Spoon mixture in a rough log shape about a quarter of the way down a sheet of greaseproof paper.  Fold paper over roll, then with ruler push against the butter so that the mixture forms a smooth roll.  Roll in the greaseproof paper.  Refrigerate until firm.  Cut into slices.','From one of my favorite Aussie cookbooks.  This became a regular at home.....and always a crowd pleaser.',23),(66,'Cauliflower au Gratin','1 small cauliflower\r\n45 g butter\r\n3 tbsp flour\r\n1-1/2 cups milk\r\n60 g cheddar cheese\r\nsalt, pepper\r\n1/2 cup fresh breadcrumbs\r\n30 g cheddar cheese extra\r\n15 g butter, extra','Step 1\r\n\r\nRemove stalk from cauliflower, cut into large flowerets.  Cook in boiling water until tender, remove from heat, drain.\r\n\r\nStep 2\r\n\r\nPut butter in pan, stir over medium heat until melted.  Add flour, stir until smooth, cook 1 minute.  Add milk gradually, stir until smooth, stir until sauce boils and thickens.  Remove from heat, add grated cheese, salt and pepper, stir until cheese melts.\r\n\r\nStep 3\r\n\r\nSpread half cheese sauce over base of ovenpoof dish, arrange cauliflower on top of suace, spread remaining sauce over cauliflower.\r\n\r\nStep 4\r\n\r\nCombine breadcrumbs, extra grated cheese and extra melted butter.  Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of cauliflower.  Bake in moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.\r\n\r\n','Nice dish to make when you have a gang, or not.  you can make it up until the point that you put it in the oven and put it aside until your company is there then put it in the oven for the final 20 minutes.',21),(67,'Paskha','2 tsp white sugar\r\n5 cups warm water\r\n3 tsp yeast\r\nMix those three ingredients together and let stand 15 minutes for the yeast to rise\r\n\r\nAdd 5 cups flour.  Let rise approx. 3/4 of an hour in a warm place covered.  After it has risen put 6 large eggs in bowl and whip until light and frothy.  \r\n\r\nRemove dough from heat.  Add 1/3 lb of tender flake and 3/4 cup white sugar, 1 tbsp salt and egg mixture together and mix well.  Add 10 cups of flour.  Mix together well.\r\n\r\nLet rise approx. 2.5 hours.  Punch down and let rise again.  Put dough into greased pan, not too thick.  Decorate .  Let rise, brush egg on top and sprinkle with seeds.\r\n\r\n5 cups flour','Bake at 300 for approx 30 minutes then turn down to 250 and bake for an addition 30 minutes.','Bushka always made Paskha for Easter and Xmas.  There is also a tradition wedding cake made from Paskha that is on the table with a tradition wedding cake at Ukranian weddings.',5),(68,'Orange Pearls in Chocolate Shells','1 (12 oz) Pkg semi sweet chocolate chips\r\n1 tbsp shortening\r\n1 envelope unflavored gelatin\r\n1/2 cup cold water\r\n1 (8 oz) container light cream cheese\r\n1/4 cup white sugar\r\n1/2 cup orange juice\r\n1 tsp grated orange peel\r\n2 cups cool whip','- Cover outside of 12 seashells with foil, smoothing until tight.\r\n- Melt chocolate chips with shortening over low heat stirring constantly.\r\n- Spread chocolate mixture thinkly over each seashell with brush.  Chill 10 min. keeping remaining choc mixture  warm.  Apply second coat.  Chill until set.\r\n- Remove chocolate covered foil from shell; carefully peel foil from choc.  Chill shells until ready to serve.  If chocolate shells crack brush crack with melted chocolate and refrig until firm.\r\n-  Soften gelatin in water in saucepan.  Stir over low heat until dissolved.\r\n-  Beat cream cheese and sugar in lge mixing bowl at med speed until well blended.  Stir in gelatin and orange juice and peel.  Chill until thickened but not set.\r\n-  Beat cream cheese mixture until ight and fluffy; fold in cool whip.\r\n-  Spoon approx. 1/3 cup cream cheese mixture into each shell.  Garnish with chocl lace, orange segments and fresh mint.','From the gourmet club.  A nice light desset after a big meal.  You can always just buy chocolate cups already made to make life easier, which is what I would do!',7),(69,'Bocconne Dolce - meringue dessert','Meringues\r\n\r\n6 egg whites at room temp\r\n1/4 tsp cream of tartar\r\n1-1/2 cups white sugar\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\n1 cup semi sweet chocolate chips\r\n3 tbsp water\r\n\r\n3 cups whipping cream\r\n5 tbsp white sugar\r\n2 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\n3 cups fresh strawberries slice lengthwise (save a few for garnish)','Meringue\r\n\r\nBeat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.  Beat in sugar gradually, beating until stiff and glossy.  Line 3 round 8 inch pans with foil .  Very lightly grease the foil.  Divide and spread the meringue evenly among the pans.  Bake in 250 degree oven for about 45 min. until dry and crispy firm.  Cool on racks.  Peel off foil.\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\nIn heavy saucepan melt chips with water over low heat.  Spread over 2 meringue shells.\r\n\r\nWhip cream, sugar and vanilla until stiff.  Spread over all 3 meringue layers.  Place 1 layer with choc on serving plate.  Spoon 1/2 strawberries over top.  Place second layer with choc over first on plate.  Spoon second f1/2 straberries on top.  Add third layer.  Garnish with whole berries.  Chill 2 or 3 hours before serving.','I love meringue desserts and this is a nice light dessert that looks great.\r\n\r\nGourmet Club recipe.',7),(70,'Tiger Prawns Duxelle','30 g butter\r\n2 tbsp shallots, minced\r\n85 g button mushrooms  (6 tbsp) finely chopped\r\nsalt pepper\r\n1/4 tsp chopped fresh thyme\r\n1/2 tbsp brandy\r\n4 tiger pawns, peeled and deveined\r\n4 slices smoked salmon','To make Mushroom Duxelle, melt butter, add shallots and cook until transparent.  Add mushrooms and cook for 4-6 min. stirring occasionally.  Add seasonings.  Add brandy to mushrooms and flambe.  Cool.\r\n\r\nDraw a knife down the bakc of the prawns to make a butterfly incision.  Add 1 slice of smoked salmon to each prawn.  Place 1/4 of the Mushroom Duxelle over each salmon slice.  Bake in a 350 degree oven for 5 minutes.  Serve hot.  Serve with Lemon butter sauce.\r\n\r\nLemon Butter Sauce.\r\n\r\n2 tbsp butter\r\n2 tbsp flour\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/8 tsp pepper\r\n1/8 tsp onion powder\r\n1 cup milk\r\n2 tbsp lemon juice\r\n2 tbsp butter\r\n1 egg\r\n\r\nMelt first amount of butter.  Mix in flour, salt, pepper and onion powder.\r\n\r\nAdd milk and lemon juice.  Heat and stir until it boils and thickens.  May be served now or add remaining ingredients.\r\n\r\nPut sauce in blender.  Add second amount of butter and egg.  Blend until smooth.  Return to saucepan.  Heat and whisk until it starts to boil.  If sauce curdles run through blender.  Makes 1 cup','This was made on Men\'s Night of the gourmet club.  I\'m sure you girls will remember this....\r\n\r\n&quot;On a cold and rainy summer day, if you have nothing else to do but &quot;fool around&quot;......buy a bunch of coconuts, put them on the radial saw, empty them, get some ribbon, grass skirst and Hawiian music and Hoola the night away&quot;.......  Needless to say the neighbors were entertained......as were our husbands.......hahahahhhahah',24),(71,'Mandarin Orange Salad','1/2 cup oil\r\n3 tbsp red wine vinegar\r\n1 tbsp lemon juice\r\n2 tsp sugar\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/2 tsp dry mustard\r\n1 clove crushed garlic\r\n1/2 cup sunflower seeds\r\n1/2 cup slivered almonds\r\n1 head leaf lettuce\r\n2 green onions finely chopped\r\n10 oz can mandarin oranges or 2 lge oranges peeled and sliced\r\n1 ripe avocado peeled and sliced.','Combine first 7 ingredients in a jar.  Shake to blend.  Prepare remaining ingredients.  Toss with dressing just before serving.....serves 4-6','Lovely and refreshing....',16),(72,'Strawberry Cheesecake Supreme','Crust\r\n\r\n250 ml vanilla wafer crumbs\r\n125 ml angel flake coconut\r\n75 ml melted butter\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\n1 litre fresh strawberries cleaned\r\n3 - 250 g cream cheese softened\r\n250 ml sugar\r\n125 ml orange juice\r\n15 ml lemon juice\r\n2 envelopes unflavored gelatin\r\n125 ml cold water\r\n250 ml whipping cream\r\n\r\nGarnish\r\n\r\nwhipped cream\r\nmint leaves','Combine crumbs, coconut and butter; press onto bottom of a 9 inch springform pan.  Grease pan sides and like with a strip of wax paper wide enough to reach top of pan.\r\n\r\nReserve several strawberries for garnish.  Cut two 1/4&quot; slices from centre part of enough strawberries to press a single row of slices around base edge of pan.  Cut up remaining strawberries to make 2 cups.\r\n\r\nBlend or mash prepared strawberries.  IN a lge bowl beat crfeam cheese, sugar, juice and lemon juice until very smooth.  Beat in berries.  Soften gelatin in cold water; stir over low heat until dissolved.  Beat into cheese mixture.  Refrigerate until mixture just begins to mound.  Fold in whipped cream; pour into prepared pan.  Refrigerate serveral hours or overnight.  Remove cake from the pan.  Remove wax paper and garnish cake with whipped cream, strawberry slices and fresh mint.','The filling can be made in a food processor.  Makes 12 servings.\r\n\r\nA gourmet club recipe.',7),(73,'Surprise Angel Pecan Pie','3 egg whites, room temp\r\n1/8tsp salt\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n3/4 cup chopped pecans\r\n3/4 cup crushed soda crackers\r\n1 tsp double acting baking powder\r\n1 cup whipping cream','1.  Preheat oven to 350 degrees.  Grease a 9&quot; pie plate; line with foil and greast.\r\n2.  Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.  Gradually sprinkle in sugar 2 tbsp at a time beating well after each addition continue until whites stand in stiff glossy peaks.  Lightly beat in 1 tsp vanilla.\r\n3.  Into egg whites, fold pecans, crackers and baking powder.  Spread evenly in pie plate.  Bake 35 min or until light golden but not brown.  Cool on rack 2 hrs.  Using foil, lift pie from plate; refrigerate until pie is thoroughly chilled.\r\n4.  To serve remove foil; place pie on plate.  Beat cream with 2 tbsp sugar and 1 tsp vanilla until stiff peaks form.  Spread mixture over pie.\r\n','Gourmet Club....a very light pie.',25),(74,'Irish Cream Dessert','1 envelope unflavored gelatin\r\n3 tbsps cold water\r\n2 cups whipping cream\r\n1/2 cup Irish Cream liqueur\r\n1/2 cup white sugar\r\n1/2 cup finelly chopped semisweet chocolate, reserving 2 tbsp for garnish','In a heat proof bowl combine gelatin and water.  Allow to sit 5 min to soften.  Place bowl in a saucepan of water over low heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.  Remove from the heat and cool to room temp.\r\n\r\nIn a large bow, whip cream until soft peaks form.  Gradually beat gelatin into cream until stiff peaks form.  Blend in liqueur and sugar. Fold in chocolate.  Spoon into individual glasses and chill at least 1 hour.  Before serving, sprinkled reserved chocolate over tops of desserts.\r\n\r\nMakes about 8 servings.','Gourmet Club ......\r\n',7),(75,'White Chocolate Mousse with Raspberry Sauce','Raspberry Sauce\r\n\r\n300 g frozen unsweetened raspberries\r\n1/2 cup sugar\r\n1 tbsp frozen orange juice concentrate\r\n\r\nMousse\r\n6 squares white chocolate cut into pieces\r\n2 cups whipping cream\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\nDrizzle\r\n\r\n1 square semi sweet chocolate\r\n1 tsp vegetable oil\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Sauce\r\n\r\nIn blender or food processor, combine raspberries, sugar and juice concentrate.  blend until smooth.  Sieve to remove seeds.  Refrigerate.\r\n\r\nMousse\r\n\r\nMelt white chocolate with cream until smooth, stirring constantly.  Add vanilla.  Pour into bowl and cover.  Refrigerate overnight or until very cold and thickened.  Beat mixture on high with mixer until fluffy and light.  Do not over beat.\r\n\r\nMake into nice clouds using large spoons and place ontop of rasberry sauce.  Drizzle with chocolate.','A very light and flavorful dessert........nice after a large meal and pretty on the plate.',7),(76,'Southwest Appetizer Cheesecake','2/3 cup finely crushed tortilla chips\r\n2 tbsp melted margarine\r\n1 cup cottage cheese\r\n24 oz cream cheese softened\r\n4 eggs\r\n2-1/2 cups grated sharp cheddar cheese\r\n4 oz chopped green chilies, drained\r\n8 oz sour cream\r\n8 oz jalapeno cheddar gourmet dip\r\n1 cup chopped tomatoes\r\n1/2 cup chopped green onions\r\n1/4 cup sliced ripe olives','Preheat oven to 325 degrees.  Combine tortilla chips and margarine; press into bottom of 9&quot; springform pan.  Bake 15 min.  Meanwhile, place cottage cheese in food processor and process until smooth.  IN bowl combine cottage cheese and cream cheese, mixing until well blended.  Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each.  Blend in cheddar cheese and chilies.  Pour mixture over baked crust.  Return to oven and bake 60 min.\r\n\r\nCombine sour cream and dip.  Mix thoroughly.  Spread mixture over hot cheesecake; return to oven and continue cooking 10 min.  Remove from oven and coll slightly.  Loosen cake from rim of pan.  Cool completely before removing rim.  Refrigerate chesecake until ready to serve.  Top with tomatoes, green onions and olives before serving.',' Makes alot....so good for a big crowd',18),(77,'Mushrooms with Curried Crab','8 large flat mushrooms\r\n30 g butter\r\n3 green shallots, finely chopped\r\n2 tbsp plain flour\r\n2 tsp curry powder\r\n3/4 cup cream\r\n1 tbsp lemon juice\r\n180 g can crb , drained\r\npaprika\r\n\r\nTopping\r\n\r\n30 g butter\r\n1 cup stale breadcrumbs\r\n1/2 cup grated tasty cheese (cheddar)','Remove stems from mushrooms.  Heat butter in pan, add shallots, stir in flour and curry powder, stir constantly over heat 1 minute.  Gradually add cream, stir constantly over heat until mixture boils and thickens.  Remove from the heat and stir in lemon juice and flaked crab.  Fill mushroom caps with crab mixture, sprinkle with topping and paprika; place on oven tray, bake in moderatley hot oven for 10 minutes\r\n\r\nTopping\r\n\r\nMelt butter in pan, add breadcrumbs, stir over heat until breadcrumbs are golden brown, remove from heat; mix in cheese.','I have made these many times......very tasty.....nice on an appetizer plate....',18),(78,'Triple Chocolate Terrine with Rasberry Sauce','Dark Chocolate Layer\r\n\r\n6 oz. semi sweet chcolate\r\n3 tbsp butter\r\n2 tbsp raspberry flavored liqueur\r\n2 cups whipping cream divided\r\n\r\nWhite Layer\r\n\r\n1-1/2 tsp unflavored gelatin\r\n6 oz white chocolate broken up\r\n1/2 cup toasted chopped hazelnuts cooled\r\n\r\nMilk Chocolate Layer\r\n\r\n11.5 oz milk chocolate chips\r\n1/4 cup butter\r\n\r\nRaspberry Sauce\r\n\r\n10 oz package frozen rasberries thawed\r\n1/2 cup water\r\n2 tbsp cornstarch','Dark Chocolate Layer\r\n\r\nGrease a loaf pan; line with plastic wrap, allowing extra wrap to hang over sides.  Melt semi sweet chips and butter, stirring until smooth.  Stir in liqueur; refrigerate 20 min.  Beat 1-1/2 cups cream until stiff peaks form.  Fold 1 cup of whipped cream onto chocolate mixture; pourinto prepared pan.  Freeze 20 min or until firm but not hard.  Refrigerate remaining whipped cream.\r\n\r\nWhite Layer\r\n\r\nIn 2 quart heavy gauge saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over remaining 1/2 cup cream; let stand 5 min.  Add white chocolate.  Cook over low heat; stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and gelatin is completely dissolved; refrigerate 20 min.  Fold in 1 cup reserved whipped cream and hazelnuts.  Pour over dark choc layer; freeze 20 min or until firm but not hard.\r\n\r\nMilk Chocolate Layer\r\n\r\nIn 2 quart heavy gauge saucepan over low heat, melt milk chocolate and butter, stirring until smooth.  Refrigerate 20 min .  Fold in remaining 1 cup whipped cream.  Pour over white layer.   Cover with plastic wrap.  Refrigerate until firm about 2 hours.\r\n\r\nRaspberry Sauce\r\n\r\nIn blender puree 10 oz pkg of frozen raspberries, thawed until smooth.  Press through fine sieve to remove seeds.  In small saucepan, combine 1/2 cup water and 2 tbsps cornstarch.  Stir in puree. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.  Boi 1 min., stirring constantly.  Cool completely.','Perfect for chocolate lovers, rich but light.',7),(79,'Scallops a la Schaller','1 lb bacon, cut in half crosswise\r\n2 lbs small sea scallops\r\n1/2 cup olive oil\r\n1/2 cup dry vermouth\r\n2 tbsps chopped parsley\r\n1 tsp garlic powder\r\n1 tsp black pepper\r\n1/2 tsp onion powder\r\ndash or oregano','Wrap 1 bacon piece around each scallop; if necessary secure with wooden toothpick.  Place wrapped scallopsin baking dish.  Combine olive oil, vemouth, parsley, garlic powder, pepper, onion pwoder and oregano.  Pour over scallops.  Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.\r\n\r\nRemove scallops from marinade.  Arrange on broiler pan.  Broil 4&quot; from heat, 7 to 10 minutes or until bacon is brown.  Turn over nad brown other side for about 5 min.  Remove toothpicks.  Arrange on platter line with greens.....','Love scallops that are well done.....don\'t over cook or they will be like rubber ......',24),(80,'Celery Crunch','1 litre celery sliced in 1&quot; lengths (4 cups)\r\nsalted water\r\n\r\n50 ml butter\r\n50 ml flour\r\n250 ml water\r\n125 ml table cream\r\n\r\n15 ml chicken bouillon powder\r\n75 ml sliced mushrooms drained\r\n125 ml sliced water chestnuts\r\n125 ml slivered almonds\r\n\r\n50 ml grated parmesan cheese\r\n\r\n50 ml butter\r\n125 ml cracker crumbs','Cook celery in salted water until tender and place in casserole.\r\n\r\nMelt butter in saucepan.  Mix in flour water and cream and cook until it boils and thickens stirring.\r\n\r\nAdd chicken boullion, mushrooms,water chestnuts and almonds.  Stir and pour over celery.\r\n\r\nSprinkle with cheese.\r\n\r\nMelt butter in small saucepan.  Add cracker crumbs.  Stir until mixed.  Spread over all.  Baked uncovered for 350 degrees  for 30 to 35 minutes until golden and celery is tender.','Sounds like a strange dish but it tastes pretty good.....your dad liked this one.',21),(81,'Stuffed Breasts of Chicken','2 boneless chicken breasts\r\n\r\n2 tbsps butter\r\n2 tbsps chopped onion\r\n2 tbsps chopped celery\r\n\r\n1 cup dry breadcrumbs\r\n1 tbsp chives\r\n1/4 tsp poultry seasoning\r\n1/16 tsp salt\r\npinch pepper\r\n1-1/2 tbsps milk','Remove skin from chicken breasts.\r\n\r\nMelt butter in pan.  Add onion and celery.  Saute until onion is soft and clear.  Remove from heat.\r\n\r\nAdd breadcrumbs, chives, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.  Stir well to mix.  Add more milk if needed to make dressing cling together.  Divide between breasts to make a mound along the center length.  Close and secure with picks.  Place in baking dish.  Spoon some marmalade orange sauce over top.  Bake uncoveredin 325 degree oven until tender, about 45 min.  slice and arrange on plates.  Spoon additional sauce over slices.  Serves 2 generously.\r\n\r\nMarmalade Orange Sauce\r\n\r\n1/2 cup orange marmalade\r\n1 tbsp concentrated orange juice\r\n\r\nStir marmalade and concentratedjuice together in saucepan over low heat.  Spoon some over chicken breasts to bake.  Spoon rest of sauce over top before serving.\r\n','Simple but tasty.....',23),(82,'Crab and Goat Cheese Kisses','1/2 lb flaked crabmeat\r\n1/2 lb soft mild goat cheese\r\n1 shallot very finely chopped\r\n2 tbsps finely chopped parsley\r\n1/4 tsp black pepper\r\n6 sheets phyllo dough\r\n1/2 cup butter melted\r\n','1.  Blend the crabmeat, goat cheese, shallt, parsley and pepper, reserve.\r\n2.  Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.  Lightly grease baking sheets.  Spread out the layered sheets of phyllo dough and cover with a damp cloth.\r\n3.  Quickly and carefully transfer a sheet of dough onto the work surface and brush lightly but completely with melted butter.  spread the second sheet of phyllo smoothly over the first sheet and brush with additional butter; repeat with the third sheet.\r\n4.  Cut the layered phyllo into 20 squares and place a tsp of the filling in the centre of each square.  Gather the corners of the phyllo up over the fillinga nd twist them together, forming a kiss. Brush the kisses lightly with additional butter and palce them on the baking sheets about 1&quot; apart.\r\n5.  Repeat steps 3 and 4.  Place the baking sheets in the oven and bake until the phyllo is nicely browned about 10 minutes.  Transfer the kisses to serving plate.','If you love goat cheese and crab you will enjoy these.',18),(83,'Spinach and Cauliflower Soup','Cauliflower Soup\r\n\r\n1/2 small cauliflower\r\n15 g butter\r\n1 small onion\r\n3 cups chicken stock\r\nsalt, pepper\r\n2 tbsps cream\r\n\r\nSpinach Soup\r\n\r\n250 g pkt frozen chopped spinach\r\n1 tbsp pinenuts\r\n15 g butter\r\n1 clove garlic\r\n1 small onion\r\n2 cups chicken stock\r\nfew sprigs of parsley\r\n3 tsps cornstarch\r\n1 tbsp water\r\nsalt, pepper\r\n','Cauliflower Soup\r\n\r\nCut cauliflower into small flowerets.  Melt butter in pan add peeled and chopped onion, cook until transparent.  Add cauliflower, mix well, cook 2 min; stir to prevent browning.  Add stock, bring to boil, reduce heat, simmer covered 20 min.  Puree soup in blender in batches, push through sieve. Return soup to pan, season with salt and pepper; when soupd reboils, add cream.  Heat through without boiling.\r\n\r\nSpinach Soup\r\n\r\nPlace pinenuts in pan, stir over low heat until light golden brown; remove from pan immediately.  Add butter, crushed garlic and peeled and chopped onion to pan; cook until onion is transparent.  Add unthawed spinach and stock bring to boil, reduce heat, simmer gently covered 15 min. stirring occasionally.  Pour soup into blender, add pinenuts and parsley, blend until pureed.  PUsh mixture through sieve.  Return to pan, add combined cornstarch and water.  Stir over medium heat until soup boils, season with sale and pepper.\r\n\r\nPour soups into two separate jugs.  With one jug in each hand, pour soup into individual bowls at the same time, then swirl soups gently with handle of spoon.','I am not a girl who really loves soup but I love this one....and if I do say so myself it looks wonderful in a bowl...all of your guests will be sooo impressed and it is soooo simple to do.',26),(84,'Veal Cordon Bleu','8 small veal steaks\r\n4 slices ham\r\n4 slices gruyere cheese\r\nplain flour\r\n2 eggs, lightly beaten\r\n1/4 cup milk\r\n1 tbsp grated lemon rind\r\n2 cups fresh breadcrumbs\r\n2 cups stale breadcrumbs\r\n60 g butter\r\n1/4 cup oil','1.  Trim veal of any membrane.  Use a meat mallet or rolling pin to pound veal thinly, trim edges neatly.\r\n2.  Place a slice of ham and cheese over 4 of the steaks; filling should come to within 1 cm of the edge of the steaks.  Cover with remaining steaks, press edges firmly together.\r\n3.  Dust steaks lightly with flour, then dip in combined eggs and milk and lemon rind; coat with combined breadcrumbs, press crumbs on firmly.  Refrigerate steaks 1 hour.  Heat butter and oil in large frying pan, add steaks, cook over medium heat for about 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown; drain on paper.','The steaks can be filled and crumbed the day before serving; cover loosely, store in the fridge.\r\n\r\nServes 4',27),(85,'Chocolate Fudge Cake','90 g unsalted butter\r\n90 g dark chocolate, chopped \r\n4 eggs, separated\r\n2 tsp vanilla extract\r\n1/4 tsp almond extract\r\n2/3 cup white sugar\r\n2 tbsps rum\r\n1/2 cup ground almonds\r\n1/2 cup flour\r\n1/2 cup cocoa\r\n1/4 cup white sugar, extra\r\n\r\nGlaze\r\n\r\n1/3 cup light corn syrup\r\n30 g unsalted butter\r\n2 tbsps water\r\n100 g dark chocolate\r\n\r\n','1.  Grease a deep 23 cm round cake pan (9&quot;), line base with paper; greease paper.  Melt butter and chocolate in heatproof bowl over hot water; cool to room temp.\r\n\r\n    Beat egg yolks, extracts and sugar until pale and thick.  Transfer mixture to lge bowl, stir in rum and chocolate mixture, then almonds and sifted flour and cocoa.\r\n\r\n2.  Beat egg whites until soft peaks form, gradually add extra sugar, beat until dissolved between each addition, fold into chocolate mixture.  Spreadinto prepared pan,bake in moderate oven for about 30 min.  Stand 5 min before turning onto wire rack.  leave cake upside down.\r\n\r\n3.  Glaze:  Combine corn syrup, butter and water in saucepan, stir over heat until mixture comes to the boil,remove from heat.  Stir in chocolate stir until smooth.  Stand until bubbles subside, stain, spoon warm glze over cold cake.  Stand at room temperature until set.','A very rich dense chocolate cake.  It is nice served with a little whipped cream and fruit.',8),(86,'Creme Brulee','600 mls whipping cream\r\n6 egg yolks\r\n1/4 cup white sugar\r\n2 tsp vanilla extract\r\n1/4 cup white sugar','1.  Pour cream into a saucepan, bring to the boil.  Combine egg yolks, sugar and vanilla in top half of double boiler, beat with electric mixer until pale and thick.  Gradually pour in hot cream while motor is operating.  Place mixture over simmering water, stir constantly until mixture thickly coats the wooden spoon.  Spoon into 4 ovenproof dishes.  Refrigerate until set.\r\n\r\n2.  Sprinkle sugar over set custards about 1 hour before serving.  Place dishes in pan.\r\n\r\n3.  Pack ice cubes around dishes, place under preheated grill, grill until sugar is lightly browned.  Refrigerate until ready to serve.','My absolute most favorite dessert of all time.....if it is on the menu I must have it.  It is really nice served with a little fresh fruit on the side....',7),(87,'Chicken with Avocado','8 small chicken fillets\r\n1 large ripe avocado\r\n1 tbsp lemon juice\r\nsalt, pepper\r\n2 tbsps oil\r\n2 tbsps ground hazelnuts\r\n\r\nSauce\r\n\r\n15 g butter\r\n2 tsp oil\r\n1 stick celery\r\n1 small onion\r\n1/2 tsp thyme\r\n2 tbsps dry sherry\r\n30 g extra butter\r\n1 tbsp flour\r\n1 beef stock cube\r\n1 cup hot water\r\n1 tomato\r\nsalt, pepper\r\n1/2 cup dry white wine\r\n1/2 cup cream','Heat oil in pan, fry chicken fillets on both sides until lightly browned and cooked in the centre; drain on absorbent towels.  Peel avocado, cut in half and remove stone.  Mash flesh with fork, add lemon juice, season with salt and pepper.  Spread avocado over top of each piece of chicken. Sprinkle hazelnutson top of avocado.  Place chicken on oven tray and bake in moderate oven for 5 minutes.  Spoon sauce over.\r\n\r\nSauce\r\n\r\nHeat butter and oil in saucepan, add peeled and chopped carrot, chopped celery, peeled and chopped onion, thyme, peeled and chopped tomato and sherry.  Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer covered, until vegetables are tender.  Puree in blender or push through sieve.  In separate saucepan, melt extra butter, add flour and cook 1 in.  Add crumbled stock cube, water and vegetable puree.\r\n\r\nStir until sauce boils, reduce heat, add wine and cream, salt and pepper, reheat gently.','I love the flavor of this chicken.  As usual though I mash more than one avocado otherwise there is very little for each piece.  I also make 1.5 times the recipe for the sauce....and at times I doubled it......recipes never seem to make enough for the way we like to eat....',23),(88,'Chicken with Crab','4 chicken breasts\r\n30 g butter\r\n2 tbsps oil\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\n30 g butter\r\n3 shallots\r\n1 clove garlic\r\n170 g can crab\r\n2 tsps lemon juice\r\n1 tbsp cream\r\nsalt, pepper\r\n\r\nSauce\r\n\r\n30 g butter\r\n3/4 cup water\r\n1/4 cup dry white wine\r\n1 chicken stock cube\r\n2 tsps french mustard\r\n2 tsps corn starch\r\n1 tbsp cream\r\nsalt, pepper\r\n\r\n\r\n','Cut a pocket in thickest side of each breast, without cutting right through to the other side.  Fill pockets with prepared filling.  Heat oil and butter in pan, add breasts and cook until golden brown on both sides.  Remove and place in greased overnproof dish. Cover, bake in moderate oven 20 minutes.  Spoon sauce over top.\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\nMelt butter in pan, add chopped shallots and crushed garlic, cook 1 min.  Add drained crab, lemon juice and cream, cook for a further 1 min.  Season with salt and pepper.\r\n\r\nSauce\r\n\r\nMelt butter in pan, add water, wine, crumbled chicken cube and mustard, mix well.  Combine cornstarch and cream, stir into pan, stir until sauce boils and thickens.  Season with salt and pepper, reduce heat, simmer uncovered 5 minutes.','Fairly mild tasting recipe.....but nice.....',23),(89,'Asparagus Crepes with Fresh Tomato Sauce ','Crepes\r\n\r\n1/2 cup flour\r\npinch salt\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 tbsp oil\r\n2/4 cup milk\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\n340 g can asparagus spears\r\n30 g butter\r\n3 tsps plain flour\r\n3/4 milk\r\nsalt, pepper\r\n1/2 tsp dry mustard\r\n1/2 cup grated cheese\r\n\r\nTomato Sauce\r\n\r\n500 g tomatoes\r\n30 g butter\r\nsalt, pepper\r\npinch sugar\r\n1/2 tsp basil','Crepes\r\n\r\nSift flour and salt into bowl, add eggs, oil and 2 tbsps milk.  Beat until smooth.  Beat in remainder of milk; refriderate 30 min.  Heat heavy pan, grease with butter.  Pour thin layer of pancake batter into pan.  Brown on both sides.  Repeat with remaining batter.  Place tbsp of filling into centre of crepe, fold sides in, then roll up.  Place crepes in greased shallow dish, cover, bake in moderate oven for 12-15 min or until heated through.  Serve with tomato sauce\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\nMelt butter in pan, add flour and cook 1 min.  Add milk, salt, pepper and mustard, stir until sauce boils and thickens.  Remove from heat, stir in cheese until well combined.  Drain asparagus and cut in 1&quot; length, stir into sauce.\r\n\r\nTomato Sauce\r\n\r\nChop tomatoes roughly.  Melt butter in pan, add tomatoes, season with saltand pepper, add sugar and basil.  Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer covered 15 min.  PUsh tomatoes through sieve into saucepan and reheat; discard skins.','I made these a few times for company...',28),(90,'Baked Stuffed Carrots','12 medium carrots, peeled\r\n1/4 cup mayonnaise\r\n4 tsps grated onion\r\n2 tsps prepared horseradish\r\n1/8 tsp ground nutmeg\r\nsalt and pepper to taste\r\n1/4 cup dry bread crumbs\r\n1 tbsps butter, melted, divided\r\n1/8 tsp paprika','Place carrots in a skillet; add 1&quot; of water.  Bring to a boil.  Reduce heat; covr and simmer for 10-15 min  or until crisp-tender.  Drain.  Cut a thin lengthwise slice out of each carrot.  Scoop out carrot, leaving a 1/4&quot; shell; set aside.  Process the removed carrot in a food processor or blender until finely chopped.  Transfer to a bowl; add mayo, onion, horseradish, nutmeg salt and pepper.  Spoon into carrot shells.  Place in a greased 13x9x2&quot; baking dish.  Combine crumbs, 1 tbsp butter and paprika; sprinkle over carrots.  Drizzle with remaining butter.  Bake, uncovered at 375 degrees for 20-25 min or until tender.','Although these are very good...they are very tedious to make.....but they look great on a plate and impress your company.',21),(91,'Prosciutto-Wrapped Goat Cheese','1 log 130 g firm goat cheese\r\n1 tbsp chopped fresh parsley\r\n1 tsp fresh sage\r\npinch pepper\r\n4 thin slices prosciutto','-  Using dental floss or thread, cut goat cheese into 8 rounds.  On small plate stir together parsley, sage and pepper; press rounds into herb mixture to coat all over.\r\n\r\n-  Cut prosciutto slices in half lengthwise; wrap 1 piece around each round, pressing in sides to cover completely and make equal size bundles (make ahead and refrigerate for up to 24 hours)\r\n\r\n-  In nonstick  skillet, brown rounds over medium high heat, turning once, about 1 min per side.  Let stand for 2 min. before serving.','Nice on a tray of appetizers.  I love both goat cheese and prosciutto so I liked these.',18),(92,'Mexican Spiced Pork Tenderloin with Sweet and Sour Sauce','3 pork tenderloins\r\n\r\nSweet and Sour Sauce\r\n\r\n1 tbsp olive oil\r\n1 jalapeno pepper (optional)\r\n2 cloves garlic minced\r\n2/3 cup ornge juice\r\n1/2 cup lime juice\r\n1/4 cup cider vinegar\r\n1/4 cup fancy molasses\r\n1/4 cup liquid honey\r\npinch salt and pepper\r\n\r\nCumin Rub\r\n\r\n1/4 cup cumin seeds\r\n2 tsp peppercorns\r\n1 tsp coarse salt (sea salt)\r\n2 tbsp vegetable oil','Sweet and Sour Sauce\r\n\r\nIn small saucepan, heat oil over medium  heat; fry jalapeno pepper and garlic, stirring, until aromatic, about 1 min.  Add orange and lime juices and vinegar; bring to boil.  Reduce heat and simmer until reduced to 3/4 cup about 10 minutes.  Remove from heat; stir in molasses honey and salt and pepper.\r\n\r\nCumin Rub\r\n\r\nIn a small skillet toast cumin seeds over medium low heat until aromatic and darkened, 2 min.  In clean coffee grinder or mortar with pestle. grind together cumin, pepper and salt until texture of instant coffee granules.\r\n\r\nBrush pork with oil; rub all over with cumin mixture.\r\n\r\nPlace pork on greased grill over medium heat and cook until med-rare.  Brush with 1/3 cup of the sauce while cooking.  Place on board and tent with foil and let stand for 5 min.  Serve with sauce','I make this recipe all the time. I don\'t however toast the cumin first.  I also use the jalapeno peppers because it adds some nice heat to the sauce.  This is good warm or cold......',29),(93,'Savoury Tomato Crumble','15 plum tomatoes\r\n2 tbsp olive oil\r\n2 tbsp fresh chopped thyme\r\n2 tbsp fresh chopped rosemary\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/2 tsp pepper\r\n2/3 cup fresh bread crumbs\r\n1/3 cup grated parmesan cheese\r\n1/4 cp flour\r\n1/3 cup butter','-  Core and cut tomatoes in half lengthwise.  Arrange, cut sides up and without touching, on large foil-lined rimmed baking sheet.  Brush with oil\'; sprinkle with thyme, rosemary, salt and pepper.  Roast in 350 degree oven until tops are shrivelled and bottoms are browned, about 2 hours.\r\n\r\n-  Arrange tomatoes, overlapping, in 8&quot; square glass baking dish.\r\n\r\n-  In bowl stir together bread crumbs, parmesan cheese and flour; drizzle with butter and toss until crumbly.  Sprinkle over tomatoes. Bake in 400 degree oven until golden and bubbly, about 25 minutes.','The intense flavor of the roasted tomatoes is great.  Serve with sour cream and chopped fresh chives.',21),(94,'Swiss Onion Bread Ring','2-1/2 tsps poppy seeds, divided\r\n1 tube refrigerated white bread dough (17.4 oz)\r\n1 cup gratted Swiss  cheese\r\n3/4 cup sliced green onions\r\n1/4 cup melted butter','Sprinkle 1/2 tsp poppy seeds in a greased 10&quot; fluted tube pan (angel food cake pan).   Cut the dough into 20 1&quot; pieces; place half in prepared pan.  Sprinkle with half of the cheese and onions.  Top with 1 tsp poppy seeds; drizzle with half the butter.  Repeat layers.  Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes or until golden brown.  Immediately invert onto a wire rack.  Serve warm.','Makes a nice addition to a meal. ',5),(95,'Chocolate Cheesecake','1 cup crushed chocolate wafer crumbs\r\n3 tbsps sugar\r\n3 tbsps melted butter\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\n2 cups (12 oz) semisweet chocolate chips\r\n2 pkgs (8 oz. each) cream cheese, softened\r\n3/4 cup sugar\r\n2 tbsps flour\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n','In a small bowl, combine cookie crumbs and sugar; stir in butter.  Press into bottom of a greased 9&quot; springform pan; set aside.  In saucepan over low heat, melt the choco chips; stir until smooth, set aside.\r\n\r\nIn a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.  Add flour and beat well.  Add eggs; beat on low just until combined.  Stir in vanill and melted choc. just until blended.  Pour over crust.\r\n\r\nBake at 350 degrees for 40-45 min or until center is almost set.  Cool on a wire rack for 10 min.  Carefully run a knife around edge of pan to loosen, cool 1 hour longer.  Chill overnight.  Garnish with slices of strawberries and chocolate shavings.','A very rich easy to make chocolate cheesecake.  Wonderful with any type of fruit on the side.',7),(96,'Broccoli Casserole','2 lbs fresh broccoli cut into florets\r\n1 can condensed cream of mushroom soup, undiluted\r\n1/2 cup mayonnaise\r\n1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese\r\n1 tbsp lemon juice\r\n1 cup crushed cheese flavored snack crackers','Cook broccoli until just crisp tender.  Drain and place in baking dish.  In a bowl combine the soup, mayo, cheese and lemon juice.  Pour over broccoli.  Sprinkle with crushed crackers.  BAke uncovered at 350 degrees for 25-30 min or until heated through.','Ahhhh ... one of the family favorites.',21),(97,'Mandarin Avocado Toss','1/2 cup sunflower kernels\r\n1/2 cup slivered almonds\r\n2 tbsps butter \r\n1/2 cup vegetable oil\r\n3 tbsps cider or red wine vinegar\r\n1 tbsp lemon juice\r\n2 tsp sugar\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/2 tsp ground mustard\r\n1 garlic cloved minced\r\n4 cups torn leaf lettuce\r\n1 can (11 oz) mandarin oranged drained\r\n1 ripe avocado peeled and cubed\r\n1 to 2 green onions chopped.','In a small skillet, saute sunfloer kernels and almonds in butter.  Cool.  Meanwhile, in jar with tight fitting lid, combine the oil, vinegar, lemon juice, sugar, salt, mustard and garlic; shake well.  In large bowl, toss the lettuce, oranges, avocado, onions and sunflower kernel mexture.  Drizzle with dressing. Serve immediately.','A refreshingly different salad.',16),(98,'Curried Pumpkin Soup','1/2 lb fresh mushrooms sliced\r\n1/2 cup chopped onion\r\n2 tbsps butter\r\n2 tbsps flour\r\n1/2 to 1 tsp curry powder\r\n3 cups vegetable broth\r\n1 can (15 oz) solid pack pumpkin\r\n1 can (12 oz) evaporated milk\r\n1 tbsp honey\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/4 tsp pepper\r\n1/4 tsp nutmeg\r\nFresh chives','In large saucepan, saute themushrooms and onion in butter until tender.  Stir in the flour and curry powder until blended.  Gradually add the broth.  Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 min  or until thickened.  Add the pumpkin, milk, honey, salt and pepper and nutmeg; heat through.  Garnish with chives if desired.\r\n\r\n','Makes 7 servings.\r\n\r\nI made this at Thanksgiving one year and it was a hit. Although I think at the time I probably changed the recipe just a bit as I was making it, I would taste it and add what I thought it needed.',26),(99,'Pork Loin with  Spinach Stuffing','1 pkg (10 oz) frozen chopped spinach, thawed and squeezed dry.\r\n1/2 cup chopped onion\r\n1 clove garlic minced\r\n3 tbsps butter\r\n1 cup soft bread crumbs\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1 boneless pork loin roast 3.5 lbs)\r\n1/4 cup orange juice\r\n2 tbsps soy sauce\r\n1 tbsp ketchup\r\n1 cup sour cream\r\n2 tbsps horseradish\r\n1 tsp dijon mustard\r\n1/2 tsp seasoned salt\r\n1/4 tsp dill weed\r\n','Sed aside 1/2 cup of spinach for sauce.\r\n\r\nIn skillet, saute onion, garlic and remaining spinach in butter until tender.  REmove from the heat; stir in bread crumbs and salt.  Separate roast into two pieces; spoon spinach mixture onto one piece of meat.  Top with the second piece; tie with kitchen string.  Place in a shallow roasting pan.  Combine the orangejuice, soy sauce and ketchup; pour half over the roast.  Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 hour.  Basete with remaining orange juice mixture.  Cover and bake 1 hour longer or utnil meat thermometer reads 160-170 degrees.  Let stand 10 min before slicing.\r\n\r\nIn a saucepan combine the sour cream, horseradish, mustard, seasoned salt, dill and reserved spinach.  Cook over medium heat just until heated through.  Do Not boi.  Serve warm with the pork','I love this roast.  I do make more sauce and dressing because I prefer it that way....and it seems that whenever I have made it people really like the sauce on the meat.',29),(100,'Two-Tone Baked Potatoes','6 medium russet potatoes\r\n6 medium sweet potatoes\r\n2/3 cup sour cream, divided\r\n1/3 cup milk\r\n3/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese\r\n4 tbsps minced chives, divided\r\n1-1/2 tsps salt, divided','Bake both sweet and russet potatoes until tender.  Set sweet potatoes aside.  Cut a third off the top of each russet potato; scoop out pulp, leaving skins intact.  Place pulpin bowl, mash with 1/3 cup sour cream, milk, cheese, 2 tbsps chives and 3/4 tsp salt.  Set aside.  Cut off the top of each sweet potato; scoop out pulp, leaving skins intact.  Mash pulp with remaining sour cream, chives and salt.  Stuff mixture into half of each potato skin; spoon russet potato fillinginto other half.  Place on baking sheet.  Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 min or until heated through.','Twice baked potatoes are good.  This way you get both choices.',30),(101,'Pear Stuffed Tenderloin','1 cup chopped peeled ripe pears\r\n1/4 cup chopped hazelnuts or almonds toasted\r\n1/4 cup soft bread crumbs\r\n1/4 cup finely shredded carrot\r\n2 tbsps chopped onion\r\n1/8 tsp ground ginger or 1/2 tsp minced fresh gingerroot\r\n1/4 tsp salt\r\n1/4 tsp pepper\r\nvegetable oil\r\n2 tbsps orange marmalade','In a bowl combine the first 8 ingredients; set aside.  Make a lengthwise cut 3/4 of the way through the tenderloin; open and flatted to 1/4&quot; thickness.  Spread pear mixture over tenderloin.  Roll up from a long side; tuck in ends.  Secure with toothpicks.  Place tenderloin on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.  Brush lightly with oil.  Bake, uncovered at 425 degrees for 20-25 min. Brush with marmalade bake 5-10 min longer or until done.  Let stand for 5 minutes.  Discard toothpicks and slice.','Very tasty hot or cold.',29),(102,'Stuffed Chops','4 centre-cut rib pork chops about 1 - 1-1/4&quot; thick about 2.5 lbs.\r\n3/4 tsp salt, divided\r\n1/4 tsp pepper, divided\r\n4 tbsps butter, divided\r\n2 leeks, white and light green parts only, coarsely chopped about 1.5 cups\r\n1 cup shredded carrots\r\n1 clove minced garlic\r\n3 tsp chopped fresh tarragon, divided\r\n1/2 cup white wine, divided\r\n1 pk (6 oz) baby spinach\r\n1/4 cup dry breadcrumbs, preferably garlic and herb seasoned\r\n3/4 cup no-fat reduced sodium chicken broth\r\n1 tbsp chopped fresh parsley\r\n\r\n','1.  Preheat oven to 400 degrees.  Sprinkle both sides of prok chops with 1/2 tsp salt and 1/8 tap pepper.  In a large skillet melt 1 tbsp butter over medium high heat. Add chops; cook until browned, 3-4 min per side.  Remove and reserve.\r\n\r\n2.  In the same skillet melt 1 tbsp butter over medium high heat.  Add leeks, carrots, garlic, 1 tsp tarragon and remaining salt and pepper; cook stirring, until softened, about 6 min.  Add 1/4 cup wine; cook until evaporated, 2 min.  Stir in spinach; remove from heat,  Stir in breadcrumbs.\r\n\r\n3.  Using kinfe cut 2.5&quot; wide pocket in each chop, cutting halfway through to bone.  Spoon 1/4 cup vegetable mixture into pocket of each chop; place in roasting pan.  Place remaining vegetable mixture in buttered 1 qt baking dish.  Bake chops until no longer pink near bone and the stuffing in the casseronle is heated through 15-18 min.\r\n\r\n4.  Meanwhile, in same skillet bring chicken broth and remaining wine to boil over high heat.  Add parsley, remaining butter and tarragon.  REduce heat to medium, simmer until reduced to about 2/3 cup, 10 min.  Add any meat juices from roasting pan; heat through, 1 min.  Serve sauce over chops.','Pork chops of this size are way too much for the averge person.  Count on one chop for 2 people and then make a couple extra depending on how big your crowd is.',29),(103,'Breaded Ranch Chicken','3/4 cup crushed cornflakes\r\n3/4 cup grated parmesan cheese\r\n1 envelope ranch salad dressing mix\r\n8 boneless skinless chicken breasts\r\n1/2 cup melted butter','In shallow bowl, combine the cornflakes, parmesan cheese and salad mix.  Dip chicken in butter, then roll in cornflake mixture to coat.  Place in a greased baking dish.  Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until chicken juice runs clear.','You made this for me on Mothers Day one year.  It was very tasty.',23),(104,'Roasted Garlic Mashed Potatoes','2 whole garlic heads\r\n1 tbsp olive oil\r\n6 medium baking potatoes peeled and cubed\r\n1 cup plus 2 tbsps milk\r\n2 tbsps butter\r\n1 tbsp minced fresh rosemary, or 1 tsp dried rosemary crushed\r\n1 tsp salt','Cut the top off the garlic heads so each clove is exposed.  Brush wit oil; wrap in foil.  Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until garlice is very soft.  Cool for 5 min.  Remove garlic from skins; mash and set aside.\r\n\r\nPlace potatoes in saucepan and cover with water.  Cook until very tender.  Drain well.  Add milk, butter, rosemary, salt and garlic; mash until light and fluffy.\r\n','You could leave the potato skins on to make it more rustic.',30),(105,'Pork Tenderloin Stuffed with Ginger and Dates','4 Pork tenderloins\r\n1 tbsp vegetable oil\r\n\r\nStuffing\r\n\r\n2 cups fresh bread crumbs\r\n1 tbsp vegetable oil\r\n1 onion chopped\r\n1 apple, peeled and diced\r\n2 tbsp minced gingerroot\r\n1/2 cup chopped dates\r\n1 tbsp grated lemon rind\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/4 tsp cinnamom\r\n1/4 tsp pepper','Stuffing\r\n\r\nSpread bread crumbs on baking sheet; bake in 350 degree oven for 10 -15 minutes or until golden brown; set aside.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile in skillet, heat oil over medium heat, cook onion, apple and ginger, stirring often, for about 8 min or until apples are tender.  Stir in bread crumbs, dates, lemon rind, salt, cinnamon and pepper until well combined.  Remove from heat and set aside.\r\n\r\nTrim any fat from tenderloins; cut in half lengthwise almost but not all the way through; open out flat.  Spoon stuffing lengthwise along centre of tenderloins and pat down.  Fold over to enclose stuffing.  Secure with skewers or string.\r\n\r\nIn a clean skillet, heat oil over medium high heat; brown tenderloins on all sides.  Transfer to rack in roasting pan; roast in 350 degree oven for about 40 minutes.  Ten for 10 min before cutting.','Another delicious tenderloin recipe that is good both warm or cold.',29),(106,'Cranberry Pork Medallions','1 pork tenderloin cut into 1/2&quot; slices\r\n3 tbsps oilive oil\r\n1 medium onion finely chopped\r\n1 minced garlic clove\r\n3 tbsps sugar\r\n3/4 cup apple juice\r\n1/2 cup cranberry juice\r\n1/2 cup fresh or frozen cranberries\r\n2 tsps dijon mustard\r\n1/2 tsp  minced fresh rosemary or 1/8 tsp dried rosemary crushed\r\n','In a nonstick skillet, cook pork in oil for 3-4 min on each sideor until golden brown.  Remove and set aside.  IN the same skillet, saute onion, garlic and sugar until onion is caramelized and tender.  Stir in the apple juice, cranberry juice, cranberries, mustard and rosemary.  Bring to a boil.  Reduce hat; simmer, uncovered for 5-6 min or until sauce is reduced by half.  Return pork to pan; heat through.  ','A different flavor but very nice.',29),(107,'Triple Chocolate Pizza','Chocolate Pastry\r\n\r\n2 cup flour\r\n1/3 cup cocoa\r\n2 lge eggs fork beaten\r\n1-1/4 cups sugar\r\n3/4 cup butter \r\n\r\nChocolate filling\r\n\r\n8 oz cream cheese\r\n1 lge egg\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n3/4 cup softened butter\r\n1/4 cup cocoa\r\n\r\nTopping\r\n\r\n1/3 cup semisweet chips\r\n1/3 cup white choc chips\r\n1/3 cup butterscotch chips\r\n1/3 cup drained and 1/4 maraschino cherries\r\n1/4 cup sliced almonds','Pastry\r\n\r\nMix flour, sugar and cocoa into bowl.  Add butter.  Cut in until crumbly.  Add eggs.  Mix well.  Press into pizza pan.  Bake in 350 degree oven for 15 minutes.\r\n\r\nChocolate Filling\r\n\r\nBeat all five ingredients together until smooth.  Spread over hot crust.  Return to oven for 10 min.\r\n\r\nTopping\r\n\r\nSprinkle with 3 kinds of chips.  Let stand until soft.  Draw knife back and forth over top to marble melted chips into topping.  If necessary, return to warm oven for a minute.  Place cherries and almonds here and there.  Cook','Not sure where you guys got this recipe.....but it is really really good...and really really simple......A lovely chocolate fix for any woman.',7),(108,'Chicken Mushroom Risotto','2 tbsp olive oil;\r\n1 onion, chopped;\r\n115g mushrooms, quartered;\r\n225g risotto rice such as arborio;\r\n600ml hot chicken stock;\r\n6 rashers smoked back bacon;\r\n25g freshly grated parmesan.  \r\n  \r\n',' \r\nHeat the oil in a large heavy-based pan and cook the onion until soft. Add the mushrooms and continue to cook for a further 3-4 minutes. \r\n\r\nAdd the risotto rice and stir well to coat the grains in the oil. Add about 150ml of the hot stock, stir well until the liquid as been absorbed. Add another 150ml and repeat the process until all the stock has been absorbed by the rice.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile grill the bacon and cut into pieces. Add the bacon and parmesan to the rice and stir through. \r\n\r\n \r\n','I love the flavor, and a perfect comfort food.',17),(109,'Barbecued Chicken with Honey Marinade and Plum Chutney',' 6 chicken breasts with the bone in \r\n 1 cup soy sauce \r\n 2 tablespoons honey \r\n 2 teaspoons chile flakes \r\n 2 tablespoons finely chopped ginger\r\n 2 tablespoons chopped scallions\r\n 1 tablespoon chopped garlic\r\n 1/2 cup peanut oil\r\n\r\nPlum Chutney\r\n\r\n 1 tablespoon peanut oil\r\n 1 medium red onion, diced\r\n 1/2 teaspoon salt\r\n 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\r\n 1/2 jalapeÃ±o, finely chopped\r\n 1 tablespoon brown sugar\r\n 2 tablespoons white wine vinegar\r\n 4 red flesh plums, pitted and chopped\r\n Juice of 1 orange\r\n 1 tablespoon hoisin sauce \r\n\r\n  ','\r\n In a mixing bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, honey, chile flakes, ginger, scallions and garlic.\r\n Place the chicken in a shallow pan or in a zipper plastic bag and cover with marinade.\r\n Let marinate for 3 hours.\r\n Preheat the grill to medium hot.\r\n Remove the chicken, pat dry, and drizzle with the peanut oil on both sides.\r\n Place chicken breasts on grill and cook for about 10 minutes per side.\r\n Serve with Asian cole slaw and plum chutney.\r\n\r\n\r\nPlum Chutney\r\n\r\n In a medium sautÃ© pan, heat the peanut oil.\r\n Add the onion and cook until tender, about 4 minutes.\r\n Add salt, pepper, jalapeno and brown sugar.\r\n When the sugar starts to caramelize, add the vinegar and boil for about 3 minutes.\r\n Add the plums, orange juice and hoisin sauce and cook until plums are tender.\r\n Remove from the heat and place in a stainless or glass bowl.\r\n Serve at room temperature with barbecued chicken with honey marinade and plum chutney. \r\n\r\n\r\n','I made this the first time for the bbq we had when Lyndz graduated. The sauce is hot but it is very tasty.  ',23),(110,'Apple Coffee Cake with Crumble Topping and Brown Sugar Glaze','\r\n\r\n 1 stick plus 2 teaspoons unsalted butter \r\n 1&amp;frac12; cups packed light brown sugar\r\n 2 large eggs \r\n 2 cups all purpose flour \r\n 1 teaspoon baking soda \r\n 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon \r\n &amp;frac12; teaspoon salt \r\n 1 cup sour cream \r\n 1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\r\n 2 cups peeled, cored and chopped apples \r\n\r\n\r\nCrumble Topping Ingredients: \r\n\r\n &amp;frac12; cup packed light brown sugar\r\n &amp;frac12; cup all purpose flour \r\n &amp;frac12; teaspoon ground cinnamon\r\n 4 tablespoons unsalted butter, softened \r\n\r\n\r\nBrown Sugar Glaze Ingredients: \r\n\r\n &amp;frac12; cup packed light brown sugar \r\n &amp;frac12; teaspoon vanilla extract \r\n 2 tablespoons water \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n','Preheat the oven to 350Â° F. Lightly grease a 13-by-9-inch glass baking dish with two teaspoons of the butter. \r\n\r\n In a large bowl, cream together the remaining stick of butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the eggs one at a time, beating after the addition of each. In a separate bowl or on a piece of parchment, sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. Add to the wet ingredients, alternating with the sour cream and vanilla. Fold in the apples. Pour into the prepared baking dish, spreading out to the edges. \r\n\r\n To make the topping, in a bowl, combine the sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter, and mix until it resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle the topping over the cake and bake until golden brown and set, 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from the oven and let cool on a wire rack for at least 10 minutes. \r\n\r\n To make the glaze, in a bowl, combine the sugar, vanilla and water, and mix until smooth. Drizzle the cake with the glaze and let harden slightly. Serve warm.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n ','This is a recipe that I saw on GMA and it looked really good. Sort of a take off on Apple crumble.',8),(111,'Huguenot Torte (apple)','  \r\n  \r\n   \r\n  Nonstick cooking spray  \r\n   \r\n4  large eggs  \r\n   \r\n3  cups sugar  \r\n   \r\n8  tablespoons all-purpose flour  \r\n   \r\n5  teaspoons baking powder  \r\n   \r\n1/2  teaspoon salt  \r\n   \r\n3  large Granny Smith apples, cored and cut into 1/2-inch pieces (about 2 cups)  \r\n   \r\n2  cups chopped pecans, plus more for garnish  \r\n   \r\n2  teaspoons pure vanilla extract  \r\n   \r\n  Whipped cream, for serving  \r\n  \r\n   \r\n  \r\n      \r\n  \r\n     \r\n      \r\n  \r\n \r\n  \r\n  \r\n  \r\n \r\n  \r\n   \r\n  \r\n        \r\n','1.   Preheat oven to 325Â° with racks in the upper and lower thirds of the oven. Spray two rimmed baking sheets (17 1/4-by-11 1/2&amp;#8211;by-1 inch) with cooking spray; set aside.  \r\n  \r\n  2.   In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, beat eggs on medium speed until pale yellow and thickened, about 4 minutes. Gradually add sugar, and beat until light and fluffy. Sift together flour, baking powder, and salt. With mixer on medium speed, gradually add flour mixture. Beat until incorporated, about 1 minute. Add apples, pecans, and vanilla; beat to combine.  \r\n  \r\n  3.   Divide mixture between prepared baking pans, spreading evenly. Bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes. Remove from oven, and let cool 20 minutes. Using a spatula, break into pieces, and stack on a large serving platter. Serve topped with whipped cream and nuts.  \r\n  \r\n      \r\n  \r\n         \r\n  \r\n \r\n','A recipe I saw on Martha Stewart that looked really good and simple.  ',8),(112,'Red Pepper Jelly','5 or 6 red bell peppers\r\n1 cup cider vinegar\r\n1/2 cup lemon juice\r\n1-1/2 cups sugar\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n1 tsp chili powder\r\n6 oz liquid pectin','Makes 8 - 8 oz jars\r\n\r\nWash and seed peppers; chop in food processor or grind in blender or meat grinder.  Add enough pepper pulp to the vinegar and lemon juice to make 4 cups.  Mix in a large pot with sugar, salt and chili powder.  Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.  Remove from heat and add liquid pectin.  Return to heat and boil hard for 1 minute; turn heat down to simmer.  Stir and skim off foam for 5 minutes more as mixture boils gently.  Pack in hot sterilized 8 oz jars; seal and let cool on counter top.','This is a really good recipe and of course it is great on crackers with cream cheese.',18),(113,'Spiced Mussels in White Wine','1 tbsp butter\r\n1 small onion finely chopped\r\n1 cloved garlic, chopped\r\n1 tsp curry powder\r\n1/2 tsp fennel seeds\r\n1 cup white wine\r\n1 lb (1kg) mussels\r\n1 cup whipping cream\r\n1 tbsp chopped fresh parsley\r\nsalt and pepper to taste','1.  Heat buter in large pot on medium heat.  Add onion, garlic, curry powder and fennel seeds.  Saute 1 minute. Add wine and bring to boil.  Stir in mussels, cover pan and cook until mussels open, shaking pan occassionally.\r\n\r\n2.  Remove mussels and reduce liquid by half.  Stir in cream and cook together for 3 minutes or until slightly thickened.  Add parsley and season.  Return mussels, stir  everything together and serve.\r\n\r\nServes 4','Love these mussels.  I add in mushrooms to add a little more to the mussels.  Chop them up and of course the amount is up to your own tastes.  I never have fresh parsley so I omit that.  Serve with nice crusty bread to soak up the sauce.',24),(114,'Almond Pistachio Chicken with Mustard Sauce','4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\r\nsalt and pepper\r\n1/3 cup chopped almonds\r\n1/3 cup chopped pecans\r\n1/3 cup chopped pistachios\r\n1/4 cup chopped parsley\r\n1 tbsp chopped fresh thyme\r\n3 tbsp dijon mustard\r\n1 tbsp white wine vinegar\r\n1 tbsp olive oil\r\n2 tbsp unsalted butter\r\n\r\nMustard Sauce\r\n\r\n1/2 cup dry white wine\r\n1 tbsp chopped shallots\r\n1 cup whipping cream\r\n1 tbsp grainy mustard\r\n1 tsp lemon juice\r\n1 tbsp cold butter\r\n','1.  Preheat oven to 350\r\n\r\n2.  Place chicken between two sheets of wax papper and flatten, until uniform thickness.  Season with salt and pepper.\r\n\r\n3.  combine almonds, pecans, pistachios, parsley and thyme on a plate.\r\n\r\n4.  Combine mustard and vinegar and brush one side of chicken with the mixture.  Set chicken, mustard side down, into nut mixture.  Pat chicken to coat evenly.  Brush other side of chicken with mustard mixture.  Turn chicken over in nut mixture, patting again.  Shake off any excess coating.  Place on wax or parchment paper.\r\n\r\n5.  Heat oil and butter in ovenproof skillet on medium heat.  When sizzling, add chicken breasts and fry until nuts are lightly browned on both sides, about 1 min per side.  Place skillet in oven and bake for 7 to 10 minutes or until juices are clear.\r\n\r\n6.  While chicken is baking, combine wine and shallots in pot.  Bring to boil and reduce by half.  Stir in whipping cream and mustard and reduce until slightly thickened, about 5 min.  Remove from heat and reheat when needed.\r\n\r\n7.  Before serving, whisk in lemon juice and butter.  Season with salt and pepper to taste.  Serve with chicken.','This is a recipe that I got out of one of the liquor store magazines.  It is from Woolfy\'s in St. Mary\'s (we had dinner there but weren\'t really impressed with the place although the food was fine)  I made this when we had company for dinner and it was very nice.  ',23),(115,'Garlic Mash','2 tsp olive oil\r\n15 garlic cloves, peeled\r\n1/3 cup white wine\r\nsalt\r\n1-1/2 lbs Yukon gold potatoes, peeled\r\n1/3 cup whipping cream\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\nsalt and pepper\r\n1/2 tsp nutmeg (or to taste)','1.  Heat oil in a small skillet on medium low heat.  Add garlic and brown the garlic cloves, turning them often, 3 to 4 min.  Add wine into pan, season with salt and gently simmer until garlic is very soft.  About 15- 20 min.  If you run out of liquid in the pan continue to add a little water until the garlic is very soft and becomes glazed with the reduced liquid.  Reserve.\r\n\r\n2.  Quarter potatoes and cover with salted cold water. Bring pot to boil on high heat, reduce to simmer and cook potatoes until fork tender.\r\n\r\n3.  While the potatoes are cooking add the cream and butter to another small pot and warm to melt the butter\r\n\r\n4.  Drain the cooked potatoes thoroughly.  Add the cream mixture a little at a time while roughly mashing the potatoes and finally fold in the braised garlic cloves.  Season to taste.\r\n\r\nServes 4','Very tasty.  I chopped up the garlic a little so that the pieces were smaller and was spread more through the potatoes.',30),(116,'Chicken Enchiladas','1 large flour tortillas\r\n\r\nTomato Sauce\r\n\r\n1 tbsp vegetable oil\r\n1 onion minced\r\n2 cloves garlic minced\r\n2 tbsp chili powder\r\n1 tsp ground coriander\r\n1 tsp dried oregano\r\n1/2 tsp ground cumin\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/4 tsp pepper\r\n1 can ground tomatoes (28 oz/796 ml)\r\n\r\nChicken Filling\r\n\r\n2 lbs chicken \r\n1 tbsp vegetable oil\r\n1 red pepper seeded and sliced\r\n1 jalapeno pepper minced\r\n1/4 tsp salt\r\n1/4 tsp pepper\r\n2 cups monterey jack cheese \r\n1/4 cup chopped fresh coriander\r\n','Tomato Sauce:\r\n\r\nIn large saucepan, heat oil; fry onion, garlic, chili powder, coriander, oregano, cumin, salt and pepper, stirring occassionally until softened, about 5 minutes.  Add tomatoes and bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer about 20 min , until spoon scraped across bottom of pan leaves gap that fill sin slowly.\r\n\r\nChicken Filling:\r\n\r\nTrim fat from chicken; cut crosswiseinto 1/4&quot; thick slices.  IN large skillet, heat oil over medium high heat; brown chicken, in batches.  Put in bowl.\r\n\r\nDrain fat from pan.  Add pepper and jalapeno peppers, salt and pepper; cook over medium high heat, stirring until tender crisp, 3 min.  Add to chicken; let cool.  Stir in one cup of the cheese and 2 tbsps of the coriander.\r\n\r\nSpread 1 cup of the tomato sauce in 13x9&quot; glass baking dish.  Spoon heaping 1/2 cup of the filling down centre of each tortilla; rollup tightly and place, seam side down, in baking dish.\r\n\r\nSpoon remaining tomato sauce over enchiladas.  Cover with foil; bake in 375 oven for 30 min.  Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake uncovered until tip of knife inserted in centre of enchiladas for 5 seconds comes out hot, about 10 minutes.  Sprinkle with remaining coriander.','Quick and easy to make and freeze well.  I have also made them using the ready cooked chicken from the store to save time and to use up left over chicken.  I think you could add any vegetables that you want to them just to change them up.',23),(117,'Strawberry-Mousse Cake','For the Mousse:\r\n\r\n1 pound strawberries, hulled and halved, plus 2 cups sliced strawberries\r\n2 tbsps fresh lemon juice\r\n8 oz white chocolate, chopped\r\n1-1/4 tsps unflavored gelatin\r\n2 cups whipping cream\r\n2 tbsps icing sugar\r\n\r\nFor the cake:\r\n\r\ncooking spray\r\n1 cup sifted cake flour + more for baking sheet\r\n5 large eggs plus 2 large egg yolks\r\n3/4 cup white sugar\r\npinch salt\r\n1 tbsp finely grated lemon zest\r\n6 tbsps unsalted butter, melted\r\n\r\nFor the ganache:\r\n\r\n2/3 cup whipping cream\r\n12 oz white chocolate chopped\r\npinch salt\r\n2 tbsps fresh lemon juice\r\nwhole and halves strawberries for garnish','1.  Make the mousse; Puree halved strawberries in a food processor.  Pass through a very fine sieve into a bowl (you should have about 1 cup of puree) Stir in 1 tbsp lemon juice; set aside.\r\n\r\n2.  Melt chocolate in heatproof bowl set over a pan of simmering water, stirring until smooth; set aside.\r\n\r\n3.  Put 1/4 cup cool water into a small bowl and sprinkled gelatin over the top; let stand until softened, about 5 min.  Stir 1/4 cup cream and the sugar in a small saucepan; bring to a simmer over medium heat.  Add gelatin mixture, and stir until gelatin has dissolved.  Pour into bowl with the melted chocolate, stir until smooth.  Whisk in 3/4 cup strawberry puree; reserve remaining 1/4 cup puree.\r\n\r\n4.  Put remaining 1-3/4 cup cream into the bowl of mixer and beat until medium peaks form.  Whisk one third of the whipped cream into the choc. mixture.  Fold in the remaining whipped cream using a large rubber spatula.  Refigerate 1 hour.  Stir 1 tbsp lemon juice into the sliced berries.  Fold berries into mousse; refridge 1 hour.\r\n\r\n5.  Preheat oven to 425.  Make the cake:  Coat a 12&quot;x18&quot;x1&quot; rimmed baking sheet with cooking spray (cookie sheet with sides).  Line bottom with parchment paper; and spray parchment.  Dust with flour, and tap out excess.\r\n\r\n6.  Put eggs, egg yolks, and sugar into the heatproof bowl and put over a pan of simmering water.  Whisk constantly until the mix is warm and the sugar has melted, about 2 min.  Beat on high speed until egg mixture is pale, thickened, and has cooled, about 6 min.\r\n\r\n7.Sift together flour and salt over the top of egg mixture, sprinkle with lemon zest.  Using large rubber spatula, carefully fold the flour mix into the egg mixture,cutting through center and lifting gently over sides.  When the flour is almost incorporated, pour butter down side of bowl, and gently fold in to incorporate.\r\n\r\n8.  Pour batter into prepared sheet; smooth top.  Bake until center springs back when lightly touches, 7 to 12 min.  Invert, and unmold cake onto a parchment-lined wire rack; peel parchment from cake, cool completely.\r\n\r\n9.  Assemble the cake.  Cut cake crosswise into 3 rectangles.  Set one layer, top side down, on a wire rack set over a rimmed baking sheet.  Brush with half the remaining strawberry puree.  Spread a 3/4&quot; thick layer of mousse over the top (about 2 cups)  Top with second caske layer, top side up.  Brush with remaining strawberry puree, and spread with a 3/4&quot; thick layer of mousse.  Place third cake layer on top, top side up.  Refrigerate at least 2 hours (preferable overnight)  Trim sides of cake to be straight.\r\n\r\n10.  Make the ganache:  Bring cream just to a boil in a small saucepan over medium high heat.  Pour hot cream over the choco; let stand 5 min.  Stir until smooth.  Stir in salt and lemon juice.  Let stand until ganache is pourable and has cooled slightly.  Pour ganache over top of cake, allowing it to drip down sides.  Refridgerate assemblied.  Decorate with remaining strawberries.','I made this cake for Fathers Day 2006. It is delicious!!  I found that the mousse needs to spend a little longer in the fridge firming up (and perhaps next time a little more gelatin)  When I put the cake in the fridge once it was layers I wrapped it tightly in plastic wrap and then with foil and put it into a loaf pan to help it hold it\'s shape.  And believe it or not for probably the first time ever I found that there was too much ganache to put on the cake.  However, if you make it all you can take the leftovers and make it into chocolate truffles.....coat in cocoa or chocolate.........yummmmmmyyyyyyy........\r\n\r\nIt is quite the process to make this cake but does not really take too much actual cooking time.........well worth the effort!',8),(118,'Chocolate Velvet Dessert','1-1/2 cup chocolate wafer crumbs\r\n2 tbsps sugar\r\n1/4 butter melted (no substitutes)\r\n2 cups semisweet choc chips\r\n6 egg yolks\r\n1-1/4 cups whipping cream\r\n1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n\r\nChocolate Buttercream Frosting:\r\n\r\n1/2 cup butter, softened\r\n3 cups icing sugar\r\n3 tbsps baking cocoa\r\n3 to 4 tbsps milk','In a small bowl, combine wafer crumbs and sugar; stir in butter.  Press onto the bottom and 1-1/2&quot; up the sides of a greased 9&quot; springform pan.  Bake at 350 for 10minutes.  Cool on a wire rack.\r\n\r\nIn a microwave or heavy saucepan melt chocolate chips; stir until smooth.  Cool.  IN a mixing bowl, combine egg yolks, cream and vanilla; beat well.  Gradually stir in 1/3 of the cream mixture into melted choc until blended.  Gradually stir in remaining cream mix.  Pour into crust.\r\n\r\nPlace pan on a baking sheet.  Bake at 350 for 40-45 min or until center is almost set.  Cool on wire rack for 10min.  Carefully run a knife around edge of pan to loosen; cool 1 hr longer.  Refrigerate overnight.\r\n\r\nFor frosting, in a mixing bowl, cream butter.  Combine sugar and cocoa; add to butter with enough milk to achieve frosting consistency.  Pipe into center of dessert.  Refrigerate leftovers.\r\n\r\n12-16 servings','This is a recipe from Taste of Home.  It won a grand prize and I want to try it (as of 10/01/06 I haven\'t)  I figure you can\'t go wrong with anything chocolate.',7),(119,'Warm Bacon Cheese Spread','<p>1 round loaf sourdough bread 1 pkg (8 oz) cream cheese, softened 1-1/2 cups sour cream 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese 1-1/2 tsp worcestershire sauce 3/4 lb bacon, cooked and crumbled 1/2 cup chopped green onions  Assorted crackers</p>','<p>Cut the top fourth off the loaf of bread; carefully hollow out the bottom, leaving a 1&quot; shell.  Cut the removed bread and top of loaf into cubes; set aside.  In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese.  Add the sour cream, cheddar cheese and Worcestershire sauce until combined; stir in bacon and onions.  Spoon into bread shell.  Wrap in heavy duty foil.  Bake at 325 for 1 hour or until heated through.  Serve with crackers and bread</p>','<p>always a crowd favorite.</p>',18),(120,'Southern Spiced Pecans','1/4 cup butter\r\n1-1/2 tsps ground cumin\r\n1/4 tsp cayenne pepper\r\n3 cups pecan halves\r\n2 tbsps sugar\r\n1 tsp salt','In a large skillet, melt butter.  Add the cumin and cayenne; cook and stir for 1 min.  Remove from the heat; stir in the pecans, sugar and salt until well coated.  Spread in a single layer in a greased baking pan.\r\n\r\nBake at 300 for 25-30 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.  Cool.  Store in an airtight container.\r\n\r\nMakes 3 cups','Auntie Dora used to make this type of nut.  They were really good!  I am looking for a recipe......haven\'t tried this yet (10/01/06) but will make them for Xmas this year.',19),(121,'Creamy Peppermint Patties','1 pkg (8 oz) cream cheese softened\r\n1 tsp peppermint extract\r\n9 cups icing sugar\r\n3/4 cup milk chocolate chips\r\n3/4 cup semi sweet chocolate chips\r\n3 tbsps shortening','In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and extract until smooth.  Gradually add sugar, beating well.  Shape into 1&quot; balls.  Place on waxed paper-lined sheets.  Flatten into patties.  Cover and refrigerate for 1 hr or until chilled.\r\n\r\nIn a microwave, melt chips and shortening; stir until smooth.  Coll slightly, dip patties in melted choc; place on waxed paper until firm.  Store in the fridge.  Makes about 4 doz.','Love mint patties and want to make them instead of buying them.  Will try this recipe at Xmas this year (2006)',19),(122,'Cappuccino Punch','1/2 cup sugar\r\n1/4 cup instant coffee granules\r\n1 cup boiling water\r\n2 quarts milk\r\n1 quart vanilla ice cream softened\r\n1 quart chocolate ice cream softened','In a small bowl, combine the sugar and coffee; stir in boiling water until dissolved.  Cover and refrige until chilled.  Just before serving, pour coffee mixture into a 1 gal punch bowl.  Stir in milk.  Add scoops of ice cream; stir until melted.','Sounds like a lovely non-alcoholic punch......especially for coffee lovers....',22),(123,'Molten Spiced Chocolate Cabernet Cakes','4 oz semi-sweet chocolate\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n1 tbsp cabernet sauvignon or other wine\r\n1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n1 cup icing sugar\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 egg yolk\r\n6 tbsps flour\r\n1/2 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/4 tsp ground ginger','Butter 4 custard cups (6 oz each).  Place on baking sheet.\r\n\r\nMicrowave choc and butter in large bowl on high 1 min or until butter melted.  Whisk until choc is completely melted.  Stir in wine, vanilla and sugar until blended.  Whisk in eggs and yolk.  Stir in remaining ingredients.  Spoon evenly into prepared dishes.\r\n\r\nBake in preheated 425 oven for 15 min or until sides are firm but centers are soft.  Let stand 1 min.  Loosen edges with knife.  Invert onto serving plates.  Sprinkles with icing sugar, if desired.','I hear these are great......never had one or made one......but will try this recipe soon (10/01/06)  I think some fruit on the side and perhaps a little whipped cream would also ve bery nice because these will be very chocolatey.',8),(124,'Feta and Chive Muffins','1-1/2 cups all purpose flour\r\n3 tsp baking powder\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 cup milk\r\n2 tbsps butter, melted\r\n1/2 cup crumbled feta cheese\r\n3 tbsps snipped chives','In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt.  In another bowl, whisky the eggs, milk and butter; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.  Fold in the feta cheese and chives.\r\n\r\nFill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two thirds full.  Bake at 400 for 18-22 min or until a toothpick comes out clean.  Cool for 5 mins before removing from pan.  Serve warm.. Regrigerate leftovers.\r\n\r\nMakes 12','These would be lovely as a side dish with a bbq',5),(125,'Italian Herb Muffins','2 cups all purpose flour\r\n2 tbsps grated parmesan cheese\r\n1 tbsp sugar\r\n1 tbsp italian seasoning\r\n3 tsps baking powder\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n1 egg\r\n3/4 cup milk\r\n1/2 cup vegetable oil\r\n1/4 cup softened butter\r\n1/2 tsp garlic powder','IN a bowl, combine the flour, parmesan, sugar, italian seasoning, baking powder and salt.  In another bowl whisky the egg, milk and oil; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.\r\n\r\nFill greased or paper lined muffin cups three fourths full.  Bake at 400 for 15-20 min or until toothpick comes out clean.  Cool for 5 min before removing.  \r\n\r\nIn a small bowl, combine the butter and garlic powder.  Servie with the warm muffins.\r\n\r\nMakes 10 muffins','I haven\'t tried these yet but I think they would be great with spaghetti or anything else you would eat garlic bread with.',5),(127,'Berry Cheesecake Muffins','1/3 cup softened butter\r\n3/4 cup sugar\r\n2 eggs\r\n1-1/2 cups all purpose flour\r\n1-1/2 tsps baking powder\r\n1 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/3 cup milk\r\n\r\nCream Cheese Filling:\r\n\r\n6 oz cream cheese softened\r\n1/3 cup sugar\r\n1 egg\r\n2/4 cup fresh raspberries\r\n3/4 cup fresh blueberries\r\n\r\nStreusel Topping:\r\n\r\n1/4 cup all purpose flour\r\n2 tbsps brown sugar\r\n1/2 tsp cinnamon\r\n1 tbsp cold butter','In a lge mixing bowl cream butter and sugar.  Add eggs; beat well.  Combine the flour, baking powder and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.  Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups half full.\r\n\r\nFor filling, in a small bowl beat cream cheese, sugar and egg until smooth.  Fold in the berries.  Drop a rounded tbsp into the center of each muffin.  For topping, combine the flour, brown sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl; cut in butter until crumbly.  Sprinkle over batter.\r\n\r\nBake at 375 for 25-30 min or until a toothpick comes out clean.  Cool for 5 min before removing from pan.  Serve warm.  Refrigerate leftovers.\r\n\r\nMakes 18','',5),(128,'White Chocolate Macadamia Muffins','1-2/4 cups all purpose flour\r\n3/4 cup sugar\r\n2-1/2 tsp baking powder\r\n1/2  salt\r\n1 egg\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n1/4 cup melted butter\r\n3/4 cup white chocolate chips\r\n3/4 cup chopped macadamia nuts\r\n\r\nGlaze:\r\n\r\n1/2 cup white choc chips\r\n2 tbsps whipping cream\r\n','In a bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.  In another bowl, whisky the egg, milk and buttwe; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.  Fold in chips and nuts.\r\n\r\nFill paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.  Bake at 400 for 15-18 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.  Cool for 5 min before removing from pan.\r\n\r\nFor glaze, in a small bowl melt chips with cream.  stir until smooth.  Drizzle over warm muffins.','How good do these sound!!!!!',5),(129,'Sweet Onion Corn Bake','2 large vidalia or sweet onions thinly sliced\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n1 cup sour cream\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n1/2 tsp dill weed\r\n1/4 tsp salt\r\n2 cups shredded cheddar cheese, divided\r\n1 egg, lightly beaten\r\n1 can (14.75 oz) creamed style corn\r\n1 pkg (8.5 oz) corn bread/muffin mix\r\n4 drops hot pepper sauce','In a large skillet saute onions in butter until tender.  In a small bowl, combine the sour cream, milk, dill and salt until blended; stir in 1 cup of cheese.  Stir into the onion mixture; remove from the heat and sset aside.\r\n\r\nIn a bowl. combine the egg, corn, corn bead mix and hot pepper sauce.  Pour into a greased 12x9&quot; baking dish.  Spoon onion mixture over top.  Sprinkle with remaining cheese.  Bake uncovered at 350 for 45-50 minutes or until the top is set and lightly browned.  Let stand for 10 min before cutting.\r\n\r\n12 to 15 servings.','Thinking about trying this for Thanksgving this year (2006)',21),(130,'Moroccan B\'Steeya','1 whole roaster chicken about 4 lbs, cut into 8 pieces\r\ncoarse salt\r\n1 medium onion finely chopped\r\n3 cloves garlic minced\r\n1/8 tsp crumbled saffrom\r\n1/2 tsp ground ginger\r\n1-1/2 tsp ground cinnamon plus more for sprinkling\r\n1 cup coarsely chopped fresh flat leaf parsley\r\n1/2 cup chopped fresh cilantro\r\n1/2 cup unsalted butter plus 1/2 cup melted\r\n6 lge eggs, lightly beaten\r\n1 tbsp fresh lemon juice\r\nground pepper\r\n1-2/4 cups blanched whole almonds, toasted and coarsely chopped\r\n3 tbsps icing sugar plus more for sprinkling\r\n1/2 cup orange flower water\r\n1 pkge (17 oz)phyllo dough','Season the chicken a day ahead so it has time to absorb the flavors\r\n\r\n1.  Put chicken and 1/3 cup salt in a medium bowl; toss to coat.  Refrigerate 1 hour.  Rinse chicken with cold water; pat dry.  Mix chicken, onion, garlic, saffron, ginger, 1 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 cup parsley. 1/4 cupcilantro in a large bowl; cover, and refrigerate overnight.\r\n\r\n2. Transfer chicken mixture to a medium heavy pot.  Add enough water to cover (about 4 cups).  Bring to boil; reduce heat to medium.  Add 1/4 cup butter; cover, and simmer until chicken is falling off the bone, 1 to 1-1/2 hours, adding water to cover if necessary.  Transfer chicken to plate; let cool.  Reserve poaching liquid.  Remove meat from bones and shred; discard skin and bones.  Set chicken aside.\r\n\r\n3.  Bring reserved poaching liquid to a boil over high heat; cook until reduced to 3/4 cup.  Reduce heat to medium high.  Slowly add eggs; whisk constantly until mixture is almost set, 4 to 6 minutes.  Stir in remaining 1/2 cup parsley, 1/4 cup cilantro, and the lemon juice.  Seasonwith salt and pepper, set aside.\r\n\r\n4.  Stir together almonds, sugar, and remaining 1/2tsp cinnamon in a small bowl; set aside.\r\n\r\n5.  Preheat oven to 375.  Brush a 13&quot; paella or pizza pan with 2 tbsps melted butter.  Stir together remaining melted butter and the orange-flower water in a small bowl. Assemble b\'steeya;  Brush a sheet of phyllo with butter mixture.  Put in pan, leaving 4&quot; overhang.  Repeat, adding and buttering 7 more sheets of phyllo, overlapping layers and fanninng out around pan (keep unbuttered phyllo covered with plastic wrap and a damp kitchen towel.)\r\n\r\n6.  Arrange chicken mixture over dough.  Pour in egg mixture.  Top with 5 layers phyllo brushed with butter mixture.  Sprinkle with almond mixture.  Fold up edges of phyllo to enclose.  Top with 5 layers phyllo brushed with butter mixture; tuck edges inside pan.  Slightly cirnkled 2 unbuttered phyllo over top.  Bake until golden brown 35 to 40 minutes.  Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.','When Lyndsay and I were in Morocco we had this dish and it was wonderful.  I think out of all the food we ate for the 3 weeks this was the best.  I am hoping that this recipe is as good as the one we had in Morocco.  Keep your fingers crossed........',23),(131,'Blue Cheese and Pear Tartlets','3 oz blue cheese, crumbled\r\n3/4 ripe pear - peeled and chopped\r\n1 tbsp + 1-2/4 tsp light cream\r\nground pepper to taste\r\n3/4 package mini phyllo tart shells','1.  prebake phyllo shells according to package directions.  Set aside to cool.\r\n\r\n2.  Mix together blue cheese, pear, and cream.  Season to taste with pepper.  Spoon mixture into cooled shells.\r\n\r\n3.  Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.  Serve warm.\r\n','A very nice appetizer.....I have made these a couple of times and everyone has liked them.',18),(132,'Coconut Shrimp with Pina Colada SAuce','1-1/2 cup corn starch divided\r\n2 cups plain bread crumbs\r\n2 cups sweetened coconut flakes\r\n1-1/2 cup liquid pina colada drink mix - divided\r\n2 tbsps icing sugar\r\n1/2 cup spiced rum\r\n1 lb raw jump shrimp, peeled, deveined and butterflied\r\n1/3 cup sour cream\r\n1/2 cup canned crushed pineapple - drained.','- Place 1 cup corn starch in a bowl; set aside.\r\n\r\n- Combine bread crumbs; 1/2 cup corn starch, and coconut flakes in a separate bowl; set aside.\r\n\r\n- Combine 1 cup pina colada drink mix, icing sugar and rum in a separate bowl; set aside\r\n\r\n- Coat shrimp in corn starch, then dip in pina colada mixture, then in coconut mixture, back into pina colada mixture, and back into coconut mixture.\r\n\r\n- To make sauce, combine 1/2 cup pina colada drink mix, sour cream, and pineapple.','I have made this fondu style.  If you would prefer you can just deep fry the shrimp in 375 degree oil until golden brown and then drain on paper.  \r\n\r\nThey are very good.',31),(133,'Figs with Goat Cheese, Pecans and Bacon','4-1/2 fresh figs, halved\r\n5 oz goat cheese\r\n1/2 cup and 2 tbsps toasted, chopped pecans\r\n1-1/4 slices bacon cut in half.','1.  Preheat the boiler.\r\n\r\n2.  Stuff fig halves with goat cheese.  Press pecans into the cheese.  Wrap each stuffed fig half with half a slice of bacon, securing with toothpicks.\r\n\r\n3.  Arrange on baking sheet.  Broil 5 minutes or until bacon is evenly brown and crisp and goat cheese is bubbly and lightly browned.','I made these for company and everyone liked them.  The second time I made them I partially cooked the bacon because I found they had to be under the broiler for too long for the bacon to cook.\r\n\r\nEasy to do and tasty.  Finding the fresh figs can be difficult at times but well worth the hunt.',18),(134,'Chocolate Turtle Cheesecake','1-1/2 cups toasted finely chopped pecans\r\n2 tbsps butter, melted\r\n3/4 cup plus 5 tbsp sugar divided\r\n32 caramels, chopped\r\n3 tbsp milk\r\n3 x 250 gram boxes cream cheese softened\r\n3 eggs\r\n8 oz semi sweet chocolate, melted cooled slightly\r\n1/2 cup pecan halves','Preheat oven to 350.  Cover bottom of 9&quot; springform pan with parchment paper.  Combine chopped pecans, the butter and 2 tbsps of the sugar; press firmly onto the bottom of the prepared pan.\r\n\r\nMicrowave caramels and milk in bowl until carmels are completely melted, stirring ocassionally.  Spread over crust to within 1&quot; of edge.  Beat cream cheese and 3/4 cup of sugar in large bowl with mixer until well blended.  Add eggs, 1 at a time mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended.  Stir in melted chocolate; pour over cooled caramel layer.\r\n\r\nBake 45 to 50 min or until centre is almost set.  Run knife around rim of pan to loosedn cake; cool completely.  Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, cook pecan halves with remaining 3 tbps sugar in small nonstick skillet on medium heat until sugar is completely melted and pecans are evenly coated, stirring constantly.  Spread into single layer on parchment paper; cool completely.  Sprinkled over cheesecake just before serving.','Debbie made this cheesecake for one of our family get togethers.....it was delicious.........and oh so decadent.',7),(135,'Yorkshire Pudding','7/8 cup flour\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n1/2 cup water\r\n2 eggs','Mix the dry ingredients together and then add in the milk and water and beat until fluffy and add the eggs.\r\n\r\nContinue to beat until large bubbles rise to the surface. Let stand covered and refrigerated at least 1 hour and beat again.\r\n\r\nPreheat oven to 400 degrees.Put a little vegetable oil into the bottom of each muffin tin and put in the oven to heat the oil up, approximately 5 min.  Pour pudding mixture into the hot oil, carefully, fill the cup about 1/3 full.  Put back in oven and bake for approx. 20 min or until they are puffed up and golden.','I don\'t mix the batter and set it aside for an hour.  I generally use it right away and have found that it actually works best that way.  This recipe makes approximately 9 or 10 muffins.',15),(136,'Marinated Pork Roast with Red Currant Sauce','1/2 cup soya sauce\r\n1/2 cup sherry\r\n2 cloves garlic, minced\r\n1 tbsp dry mustard\r\n1 tsp ground ginger\r\n1 tsp dried thyme, crushed\r\n1 4-5 lb pork loin roast boned, rolled and tied\r\n\r\nCurrant Sauce\r\n\r\n10 oz. jar currant jelly\r\n2 tbsps sherry\r\n1 tbsp soy sauce','Blend first 6 ingredients.  Place roast in plastic bag.  Pour marinade in bag and close.  Marinate 2 to 3 hours at room temperature of overnight in the fridge.  Occasionally press bag against meat to districute marinade.  Remove meat from marinade; place on rack in shallow roasting pan.  Roast uncovered at 325 for 2.5 to 3 hours.  Baste with marinade during last hour.  Serve with Red Currant Sauce.\r\n\r\nCurrant Sauce\r\n\r\nIn a small saucepan, heat one 10 oz jar currant jelly until melted; add 2 tbsps sherry and 1 tbsp soy sauce.  Stir and simmer 2 minutes.','When you cook the roast make sure that you don\'t overcook it or it will be dry.  In this day and age you can leave it &quot;slighty&quot; rare.\r\n\r\nThis is one of your grampa\'s favorite dishes.....',29),(137,'Cherry Squares','Crust\r\n\r\n2 cups crushed graham wafers\r\n1/2 cup melted butter\r\n1/2 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\n1 - 8oz pkg cream cheese\r\n1 cup icing sugar\r\n2 tbsp milk\r\n\r\n1 cup chopped pecans\r\n\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n2 tbsp wite sugar\r\n1 cup cream\r\n\r\n1 cup Cherry pie filling\r\n','Crust\r\n\r\nCombine the ingredients and pressinto a 9&quot;x11&quot; bake 10 minutes at 325...cool.\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\nBeat the next three ingredients together until smooth and add a little vanilla.  Spread over crumb mixture and spread chopped nuts.\r\n\r\nWhip cream with sugar and vanilla and spread over the nuts.\r\n\r\nAdd a little almond extract to the cherries and spread over the cream layer.\r\n\r\nChill over night.','Your Dad really liked this dessert. I like it but I never liked the whole cherries from the pie filling so I used to give them to your dad to eat...which always made him happy.',7),(138,'Pineapple Carrot Cake','Mix in bowl by hand:\r\n\r\n2/3 cup vegetable oil\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 cup fine grated carrots\r\n1/2 cup crushed pineapple\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\nAdd dry ingredients:\r\n\r\n1.5 cups flour\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n1 tsp baking powder\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n1 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n\r\nIcing\r\n\r\n3 oz cream cheese\r\n3 to 4 tbsp butter\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\ndash salt\r\n2.5 cups icing sugar','Mix all the ingredients together for 2 minutes at medium speed.  BAke in 9&quot;x9&quot; x 2 pans at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.  Cool Cake.\r\n\r\nIcing\r\n\r\nMix all the ingredients together until smooth.  You might need to add a little milk.  Spread on cooled cake.','This recipe came from Marion Johnson.',8),(139,'Sex in a Pan','1/2 cup butter\r\n1 cup flour\r\n1/2 cup chopped pecans\r\n1 8 oz pkg cream cheese\r\n1 cup icing sugar\r\n2 4 oz containers cool whip (2 small size)\r\n1 4 serving size pkg instant choc. pudding mix\r\n1 4 serving pkg instant butterscotch pudding mix\r\n1/4 cup tia maria\r\n2-3/4 cups milk','Cut butter into flour.  Stir in pecans.  Press into 13x9 pan.  Bake 350 for 20 minutes and cool.\r\n\r\nBeat cream cheese until fluffy.  Add sugar and 1 container cool whip.  Spread over crust and freeze.  Combine puddings, tia maris and milk.  Beat 2 minutes.  Spread over cheese layer.  Freeze til firm.  Top with remaining cool whip.  Sprinkle with grated chocolate and pecans.','One of gramma\'s favorite desserts.  The nice thing is that you can make it ahead and keep it in the freezer.  You can also put the left overs back into the freezer and save for another time.',7),(140,'White Xmas Cake','1 cup butter\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n2 cups flour\r\n1 lb white raisins\r\n1/2 lb citron peel\r\n1 lb cherries\r\n4 pineapple rings \r\ndash salt\r\n4 eggs\r\n1/4 tsp baking soda dissolved in 2 tsp warm water\r\n1/2 bottle almond flavor (small bottle)\r\n1/2 cup brandy\r\n1 cup flaked angel coconut\r\n','Cut up and put all the fruit into a bowl and cover with 1/2 of the brandy.  Cover and let sit over night.  \r\n\r\nMix as you would any other cake and add the other 1/2 of the brandy.\r\n\r\nPut in 2 small angel food pans and bake in 275 to 300 degree oven for approx. 1.5 hours check to be sure it is cooked.','This is gramma\'s recipe for Xmas cake.  I love it but when you girls were small you didn\'t really care for it.',8),(141,'Tea Biscuits','2 cups all purpose flour\r\n1 tbsp white sugar\r\n4 tsp baking powder\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/2 cup tenderflake shortening\r\n1 beaten egg\r\n2/3 cup milk','Sift together all the dry ingredients and cut in shortening until it resembles coarse crumbs.  Combine the beaten egg and milk and add to the flour mixture all at once.  Stir til the batter follows the fork around in the bowl.\r\n\r\nPut flour on counter and put dough on it and flatten to about 3/4&quot; in thickness.  Cut into rounds and place on ungreased cookie sheet.\r\n\r\nBake at 450 10 to 15 minutes','This is Bushka\'s recipe.  If you want to make it a little more buttery I believe you can get a buttery tenderflake which would make the dough yellower.',5),(142,'Play Dough','2 cups flour\r\n1 tbsp vegetable oil\r\n3 tbsps cream of tartar\r\n3/4 cup warm water\r\n1/2 cup salt','Put all ingredients into a pot on medium heat.  Stir until balls and follows spoon in the pot.  Take off the heat and knead on counter.  \r\n\r\nYou can put in food coloring to color','I used to make this when you were small.  We played with this all the time, better than the bought one because if the kids eat it, it won\'t make you sick and it is easier to get out of the carpet when it gets dropped on the floor.',17),(143,'Divinity Fudge','2 cups white sugar\r\n1/2 cup corn syrup\r\n1/2 cup water\r\ndash salt\r\n2 egg whites','Stir in cups sugar into 1/2 cup corn syrup, 1/2 cup water,dash salt til dissolved. Boil to medium ball stage (240 degrees)\r\n\r\nSlowly pour 1/3 over 2 stiff beaten egg whites, beating constantly.\r\n\r\nCook remaining syrup to very hard ball stage (265 degrees).  Beat syrup in candy mixture; continue beating.\r\n\r\nWhen mixture holds its shape when dropped from spoon add 1 tsp vanilla.  Drop from tsp onto greased cookie sheet.','Gramma used to make this and I loved it...and nice light fluffy fudge.',19),(144,'Chili Sauce','6 quarts tomatoes\r\n2 green pepper\r\n1 red pepper\r\n5 pears\r\n5 apples\r\n5 peeled peaches\r\n1 pt vinegar (2 cups)\r\n1/2 cup pickling spices\r\n3 cups white sugar\r\n1 tbsp salt\r\n1 stalk celery\r\n5 medium onions\r\n','Scald and peel tomatoes.  Chop all the fruit and vegetables  finely.\r\n\r\nBoil on the stove for 1.5 to 2 hours with the spices in a cheese cloth bag.\r\n\r\nCan as you normally would putting parafin wax on the top.','This is Bushka\'s recipe.  It is very similar to the Red Chow that we get at the grocery store.....but of course with alot more work......',11),(145,'Angle Food cake with Apricot filling','Make an angel food cake (or buy one to keep it simple)\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n\r\n1/4 pint whipping cream\r\n1 small jar strained apricots (baby food)\r\nrind of one orange grated very small\r\n\r\nOutside of cake\r\n\r\n1/2 pint whipping cream \r\n2tsp instant coffee\r\n3 tbsps cocoa','Filling\r\n\r\nWhip cream and stir in apricots and rind.  Cut cake into 3 layers and put filling in between\r\n\r\nOutside of Cake\r\n\r\nwhip cream with coffee and cocoa and cover outside of the cake.','Gramma used to make this cake.  It is really quite good and makes for a nice and easy party cake (especially if you buy the cake already made).  ',8),(146,'Carnation Five Minute Fudge','<p>2/3 cup undiluted carnation milk 1-2/3 cups granulated sugar 1/2 tsp salt 1-1/2 cups marshmallows 1-1/2 cups chocolate chips 1 tsp vanilla 1 cup chopped pecans</p>','<p>Mix milk, sugar, salt in saucepan over medium heat. Heat to boiling and cook 5 minutes stirring constantly. Remove from the heat and addremaining ingredients. Stir 1 - 3 minutes until marshmallows are melted. Pour into buttered 9&quot; pan. Cool and cut into squares.</p>','<p>Gramma used to make this at Xmas when I was a little girl. A tasty easy chocolate fudge recipe. It works every time.</p>',19),(147,'Cheese Balls','1/2 lb cream cheese\r\n1/3 cup white sugar\r\n10 cherries finely cut\r\n1/2 cup coconut\r\npinch of salt\r\nchopped pecans if desired.\r\n\r\n1/2 cup graham crumbs\r\n1 tbsp butter\r\npinch salt\r\n1 tbsp white sugar','Combine cheese with sugar, salt, cherries, coconut and pecans.  Mix well.  \r\n\r\nIn another bowl mix graham crumbs, butter, sugar and salt.\r\n\r\nRoll cheese mixture into balls, then roll in crumb mixture.\r\n\r\nRefrigerate on cookie sheet.\r\n\r\nCan be frozen.','This is a recipe that I got at my &quot;wedding shower&quot; and I make it at Xmas.',9),(148,'Never Fail Pie Crust','1 lb tenderflake lard\r\n5.5 cups flour\r\nsalt\r\n1 egg\r\n1 tbsp vinegar\r\n1 cup cold water','Mix lard, flour and salt together til crumbs the size of pea.  Beat egg and add to water and vinegar.  Add to flour mixture.','Standard pie crust recipe.',25),(149,'Caesar Salad Dressing','1 egg\r\n3/4 cup olive oil\r\n1/4 cup vinegar\r\n1 tbsp sugar\r\ndash worcheshire sauce\r\nparmesan cheese lots to taste\r\ngarlic....lots to taste','Place egg in blender....blend until frothy.  Add vinegar and blend.  Slowly drizzle in olive oil while blender is running til sauce is thick and creamy.  Add sugar, worcheshire and 1/2 parmesan cheese and garlic.  Blend.\r\n\r\nPour over romaine, put in croutons, sprinkle with parmesan.  Serve right away.','',16),(150,'Chipit Delight','12 oz butterscotch chips\r\n1 cup peanut butter\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n\r\n3 cups mini marshmallows\r\n1 cup chopped pecans\r\n','Put the first 3 ingredients over double boiler and melt together stirring constantly.  Once they are all melted together add the chopped pecans and 3/4 of the marshamallows and smooth together...add the remaining marshmallows and take off the heat.\r\n\r\nPut in a buttered 9x9 pan','Xmas square that gramma makes that I like.',6),(151,'Oven Apple Pancake','2 cups thinly sliced and peeled apples\r\n1 tbsp melted butter\r\n1/2 tap cinnamon\r\n1 tbsp white sugar\r\n3 eggs\r\n1/2 cup flour\r\n1/4tsp baking powder\r\n1/8 tsp salt\r\n1/2 cup milk','Place apple slices and butter in an 8&quot; square baking pan.  Toss to coat and sprinkle with half the cinnamon and sigure mixture.  Blend and bake in 425 oven for 10 minutes.  Meanwhile in bowl whisk eggs, flour, baking powder, and salt until smooth.  Gradually blend in milk.  Pour egg mixture evenly over cooked apples, sprinkle with remaining cinnamon and sugar mix.  Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until the batter is firm and golden brown.  Serve immediately plain or with maple syrup or fruit preserves.  Makes 2 to 4 servings.','This is really nice for breakfast or for dinner when you don\'t know what to have.  I think you could even make it for dessert in a nice round pan and sprinkle it with icing sugar.',17),(152,'Baked Vegetable Frittata','2 tbsps unsalted butter\r\n1 onion finely chopped\r\n1 clove garlic minced\r\n1 green pepper diced\r\n1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\r\n1 can tomatoes chopped and drained\r\n5 eggs\r\n/2 cup fresh bread crumbs\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n1/4 tsp pepper\r\n1 tsp worcestershire sauce\r\n2 cups swiss cheese','In skillet melt butter.  Over medium heat, cook onion, garlic until tender; add diced green pepper and parsley and cook for 1 minute longer.Remove from heat and add tomatoes.\r\n\r\nIn large mixing bowl beat eggs until weel mixed.  Stir in bread crumbs, salt, pepper, worcestershire and cheese; gently stir in vegetables.  Pour mixture into buttered 9&quot; round baking dish.  Bake in 350 oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden and mixture firm in centre.  Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.\r\n\r\nMakes 6 servings','I have made this for brunch before.  Nice, tasty...good for dinner too.  You can really put anything you want into a frittata.',17),(153,'Sweet Potato Casserole with Praline Topping','3 cups sweet potatoes, cooked and mashed\r\n1/4 cup sugar\r\n2 tbsp margarine\r\n1 egg\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\nTopping\r\n\r\n1/2 cup brown sugar\r\n2 tbsp flour\r\n2 tbsp margarine, melted\r\n1/4 cup chopped pecans','Whip potatoes while hot. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.  Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with topping and bake at 350 for 20 to 25 minutes.\r\n\r\nServes 8','I made this at Xmas.  The only change I would make is put just 1/2 tsp of vanilla.  1 tsp is just too strong a flavor.',30),(154,'Chocolate Raspberry Layer Bars','1 cup flour\r\n1/4 cup icing sugar\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n\r\nFilling\r\n1/3 cup raspberry jam\r\n1 cup white chocolate chips\r\n4 oz (125 grams) cream cheese, softened\r\n2 tbsp milk\r\n\r\nTopping\r\n\r\n1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips\r\n3 tbsp butter','Base:\r\n\r\nPreheat over to 375.  Spray a 9&quot; square cake pan with cooking spray.  Combine flour and icing sugar.  Cut in buter until mixture is crumbly.  PRess firmly into greased pan.  Bake at 375 for 15-18 minutes or until golden.\r\n\r\nFilling:\r\n\r\nSpread jam on warm crust.  Melt white chocolate.  Beat cream cheese and cream in small mixer bowl.  Add melted chocolate, beating until smooth.  Mix well.  Spread evenly over jam.  Chill to set,a bout 1 hour.\r\n\r\nTopping:\r\n\r\nMelt chocolate and butter together over low heat, stirring until smooth.  Spread over filling and chilluntil set.\r\n','',6),(155,'Magic Chocolate Toffee Bars','1-1/2 cups semi sweet chocolate chips\r\n3/4 cup flaked coconut\r\n3/4 cup Skor toffee bits\r\n1/2 cup sliced almond\r\n1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1/3 cup white sugar\r\n1 can eagle brand','Preheat over to 350.  Spray a 13&quot;x9&quot; cake pan with cooking oil.  Combine chocolate chips, coconut, Skor and almonds.  Set aside.  Combine flour and sugar.  Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.  Press firmly into greased pan.  BAke at 350 for 12 minutes or until light golden.  Pour eagle brand evenly over crust.  Sprinkle with chocolate chip mixture.  Press down firmly.  Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.  Cool; cut into bars.','',6),(156,'Baklava','3-1/4 cup chopped pecans\r\n1/3 cup sugar\r\n1/4 tsp ground cloves\r\n\r\n','','',6),(157,'Chicken with Mushrooms','6 chicken breasts (boneless/skinless)\r\nflour\r\nsalt and pepper\r\n125 gr (4 oz) butter\r\n250 gr (8 oz) mushrooms (I put more)\r\n2 cloves garlic\r\n1 cup water\r\n1.5 cups dry white wine\r\n1 tsp mustard\r\n3 chicken stock cubes (I use the bag of stock)\r\n3/4 cup sour cream\r\n4 egg yolks\r\n1 tsp cornstarch\r\n6 green onions','Pound chicken breasts out lightly.  coat lightly with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.\r\n\r\nHeat butter in frying pan, cook the chicken gently until light golden brown and remove from heat.\r\n\r\nAdd sliced mushrooms and crushed garlic to pan, cook for 3 minutes.  Add water, wine, mustard and chicken stock, stir until combined.  Return chicken to pan, bring to simmering point.  Cover pan and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove chicken from pan.\r\n\r\nRemove pan from heat, gradually add combined sour cream, egg yolks and cornstarch, stir until combined.  Season with salt and pepper.\r\n\r\nReturn pan to heat, stir sauce until it comes to simmering point.  Simmer very slowly for 2 minutes (do not let it boil vigorously).  Return the chicken to the pan.  Simmer further 2 minutes.\r\n\r\nJust before serving sprinkle the top with chopped green onions.\r\n','Yummy!!!  I usually serve this with pasta on the side so that we can eat all the sauce.........',23),(158,'Beef Stroganoff','1 1/2 lbs top round steak\r\n1 clove garlic minced\r\n1 onion finely chopped\r\n1 bouillon cube dissolved in 1/2 cup hot water\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n2 tbsp ketchup\r\n1 tbsp worcestershire sauce\r\n6 drops tabasco\r\n1 10oz pckg sour cream\r\n1 10oz can mushroom pieces','Cut steak into strips and coat with flour. Brown steak pieces in some oil. Fry up onion, garlic and mushrooms. Add broth, ketchup, worcestershire sauce and tabasco. Let simmer for a while, then add sour cream. Serve on egg noodles.','I usually add a couple more sachets of bouillon than called for, and use fresh mushrooms.  ',13),(159,'Thai Green Curry (modified)','2 limes (zest and juice)\r\n6 thigh fillets\r\n1 Tbsp vegetable oil\r\ngreen curry paste (to taste)\r\n1 Tbsp Fish sauce (to taste)\r\n1 can coconut cream (or milk)\r\n1 bunch shallots\r\n1 bunch coriander (cilantro)\r\n2 carrots (in quarters and then chopped)\r\n16 green beans (halved)\r\n','1. Cut the chicken up into bite size pieces.\r\n2. Juice and zest the limes.\r\n3. Marinate the chicken pieces in the lime juice and zest for at least one hour.\r\n4. Fry the curry paste in the oil briefly until it is aromatic.\r\n5. Add the chicken pieces and fry briefy (2 minutes) in the curry paste.\r\n5. Add the coconut cream.\r\n6. Add the fish sauce.\r\n7. Add the carrots.\r\n8. Simmer for 20 minutes.\r\n9. Add the beans and cook for a further five minutes.\r\n10. Chop the coriander and cut the shallots into matchsticks.\r\n11. Take the curry off of the heat and add half the coriander and half of the shallots. Stir brifly to wilt.\r\n12. Serve with jasmine rice with the remaining coriander and shallots as a garnish.','Longo\'s has curry paste in two forms in different aisles.\r\n1. A jar (tasty but no heat).\r\n2. An envelope which we have not tried.\r\n\r\nYou might add a few chopped jalapeno chillies if you use the jar of curry paste.',23),(160,'Morning Glory Muffins','3 eggs\r\n1 cup oil\r\n2 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\n2 cup flour\r\n1-1/4 cups white sugar\r\n2 tsp baking soda\r\n2 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n\r\n2 cups grated carrot\r\n1/2 cup raisins\r\n1/2 cup nuts\r\n1/2 cup coconut\r\n1 apple, peeled and grated','350 for 20 minutes\r\n\r\nBeat eggs and add oil and vanilla.  Stir into flour mixture til batter combined.Spoon into greased muffin tims.  ','Gramma',5),(161,'Swedish Coffee Bread','1 cup warm water\r\n2 tsp sugar\r\n2 pkgs yeast\r\n\r\n3/4 can milk\r\n1/4 cup warm water\r\n1/2 cup white sugar\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n2 eggs beaten\r\n6 cups sifted flour','Mix the warm water, sugar and yeast and let rise.\r\n\r\nAdd the rest of the ingredients','Auntie Inga (gramps sister)',5),(162,'Sour Cream Coffee Cake','1 cup sour cream\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n1-3/4 cups flour\r\n2 tsp baking powder\r\n\r\nTopping\r\n\r\n1/2 cup brown sugar\r\n1/2 cup chopped nuts\r\n2 tbsp cinnamon','350 for 45-50 minutes     9x9 pan\r\n\r\nStir together sour cream and baking soda and let sit in bowl until double in bulk\r\n\r\nCream together the sugar and butter\r\n\r\nAdd the eggs and vanilla.  Sift theflower and baking powder together.  Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream to creamed mix and beat til smooth\r\n\r\nPlace 1/2 batter in pan.  Sprinkle with 1/2 topping, add remaining batter and topping','Auntie Dora',8),(163,'Dinner Rolls Mashed Potatoes','1-1/2 cups hot water\r\n1 cup mashed potatoes\r\n\r\n1 tbsp salt\r\n2/3 cup melted crisco\r\n2 eggs\r\n2 pkgs yeast (prepare as per package)\r\n2/3 cup white sugar\r\napprox. 8 cups flour','Mix water and potatoes together and add sugar, salt and crisco.  Cool, add eggs and yeast.  Add flour.  Knead well into dough.  Let rise for 2 hours.  Knead again and let rise another hour.  Make buns','Stella Weselowski (good friend of grammas)',5),(164,'Carrot-Pinapple Muffins','1 cup grated carrots\r\n2 eggs\r\n1/2 cup vegetable oil\r\n1/2 cup crushed pineapple\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\n3/4 cup white sugar\r\n1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1 tsp baking powder\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n1/2 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n','370  20-25 minutes\r\n\r\nMix all together. (Don\'t let batter rise)','Gramma',5),(165,'Carrot Cake','2 cups flour\r\n2 tsp cinnamon\r\n2 tsp baking soda\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n\r\n3 eggs\r\n1-1/2 cups white sugar\r\n1 cup oil\r\n2 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\n2 cups grated carrots\r\n1 cup shredded coconut\r\n1 cup pecan (walnuts)\r\n1 cup crushed pineapple','350  1 hour    9x13 pan\r\n\r\nMix dry ingredients together.\r\n\r\nBeat the eggs and sugar oil and vanilla together.  Add the dry ingredients.  Add the carrots, coconut, pecans and pineapple.  Mix well.','Bushka recipe',8),(166,'Pound Cake','1 white cake mix\r\n1 instant pudding mix (vanilla)\r\n1/2 cup crisco oil\r\n1 cup water\r\n4 eggs','Loaf pan     350   30 minutes \r\n\r\nMix all ingredients together and bake','Gramma',8),(167,'Raisin Oatmeal Crisps','1-1/2 cups raisins\r\n1 cup soft margarin\r\n1 cup brown sugar\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n3 cups rolled oats','350  8-10 minutes\r\n\r\nCream shortening and sugar.  Add eggs and vanill and beat well.  Combine flour, soda and salt and stir in.  Add oats and raisins.  Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet','Gramma always made these for gramps.  ONe of his favorite cookies.',9),(168,'Mandel Mostar','1 lb butter\r\n3 tbsps white sugar\r\n1 egg\r\n\r\n1 cup ground almonds\r\n2 tbsps cream\r\n1/2 tsp baking powder\r\nflour til thick enough\r\n\r\nraspberry jelly\r\nwhipped cream','350   10 minutes\r\n\r\ncream together butter, sugar and eggs.  Add dry ingredients.  Bake in muffin tins.  When cool and just before serving add raspberry jelly and whipped cream on top.','Gramma Lovquist recipe',10),(169,'Cookie with Date Filling','1/2 cup butter\r\n1/2 cup margarine\r\n1-1/4 cups brown sugar\r\n\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n2 tbsps boiling water\r\n\r\n1/2 tsp vanilla\r\n2 cups pastry flour\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n2 cups rolled oats\r\n\r\nDate Filling\r\n\r\n1/2 lb chopped dates\r\n2 tbsp brown sugar\r\n2 tbsps orange juice\r\n1/2 cup cold water\r\n1/2 orange grated rind\r\n1 tsp lemon juice','325    12 minutes\r\n\r\nCream butter and margarine together with sugar.\r\n\r\nDissolve baking soda in boiling water and add to cream mixture.\r\n\r\nAdd the rest of the ingredients working in rolled oats.\r\n\r\nRefrigerate 1 hour.  Make into balls and press with fork.  Fill with date filling.\r\n\r\nDate Filling\r\n\r\nMix all ingredients (except for juices) together and cook over moderate heat til thick and smooth.  ','Auntie Dora',9),(170,'Pepparkakor','3-1/2 cups pastry flour\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\n1-1/2 tsp ginger\r\n1-1/2 tsp cinnamon\r\n1 tsp cloves\r\n\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n3/4 cup sugar\r\n1 egg\r\n3/4 cup corn syrup','375   approx 12 minutes\r\n\r\nMix dry ingredients together.  Mix butter, sugar, egg, corn syrup.  Add dry ingredients.  Chill dough and then roll paper thin.','Gramma Lovquist recipe\r\n\r\nGramma had cookie cutters that were in the shape of a rabbit, camel, diamon, clubs and some other ones that I can\'t remember and these are the ones that she used for these cookies.  I remember when I was small having a specific order that I ate the cookie in.  Taking the head off first, then the legs etc.......',9),(171,'Chewy Dunking Snaps  (ginger snaps)','3/4 cup margarine\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n1 egg\r\n1/3 cup molasses\r\n1/4tsp salt\r\n2-1/3 cups flur\r\n2 tsp baking soda\r\n1 tsp ginger\r\n1 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/2 tsp cloves','375  12-15 minutes\r\n\r\nMIx well and shape into 1\" balls.  Dip top in sugar.  Bake on ungreased cookie sheet','Stella Weselowski\r\n\r\nGreat cookies to dip in a nice big glass of cold milk.',9),(172,'Piece Makers Shortbread','1 lb butter\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n\r\n3 cups flour','300  keeping white\r\n\r\nCream together butter and sugar.  Add flour.\r\n\r\nWork with a little dough at a time.  Flour board well and roll lightly not quite 1/4\".  Use spatula to put on cookie sheet.\r\n\r\nBake in slow oven.',NULL,9),(173,'Date Squares','1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1 tsp baking powder\r\n1 cup butter\r\n1-1/2 cups oatmeal\r\n1/2 tsp baking soda\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1 cup brown sugar\r\n\r\nDate Filling\r\n\r\n1/2 lb chopped dates\r\n2 tbsp brown sugar\r\n2 tbsp orange juice\r\n1/2 cup cold water\r\n1/2 orange grated rind\r\n1 tsp lemon juice','320   30-35 minutes     13x9 greased pan\r\n\r\nSift flour, baking soda and powder and salt.  Rub in butter.  Add sugar and oatmeal.  MIx well.  Spread in pan 1/2 crumbs.  Cover with cooled date filling.  Spread with remaining crumbs.\r\n\r\nDate Filling\r\n\r\nMix all ingredients together except for the juices.  Cook over moderate heat til thicka nd smooth.  Add juices.  Mix well and cool before spreading.','Stella Klapchuk, one of bushkas and grammas ukranian friends.',6),(174,'Pineapple Squares','Part 1\r\n\r\n1/2 cup butter\r\n2 egg yolks\r\n1 tsp baking powder\r\n1/2 brown sugar\r\n1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\nPart 2\r\n\r\n1 can crushed pineapple\r\n1 tbsp cornstarch\r\n\r\nPart 3\r\n\r\n2 egg whites\r\n1 cup brown sugar\r\n1/3 cup chopped pecans','350    8x8\r\n\r\nPart 1\r\n\r\nCream butter and sugar, add egg yolks and vanilla.  Work in flour and baking powder.  Bake 20 minutes.\r\n\r\nPart 2\r\n\r\nBring crushed pineapple to a boil and thicken with cornstarch.  Spread on shortbread.\r\n\r\nPart 3\r\n\r\nBeat egg whites stiff and add brown sugar gradually.  Beat til thick. Spread over pineapple.  Sprinkle with nuts and return to oven to brown.','Aline Longpre',6),(175,'Four Decker Mocha Dessert','1/2 cup butter\r\n1 cup flour\r\n1/2 cup chopped pecans\r\n\r\n1 8 oz pkg softened cream cheese\r\n1 cup sifted icing sugar\r\n2 4 oz containers frozen whipped topping thawed\r\n1 4 serving pkg instant chocolate pudding mix\r\n1 4 serving pkg insant butterscotch pudding mix\r\n1/4 cup Tia Maria\r\n2-3/4 cups milk\r\n1/2 cup chopped pecans for top','9x13 pan\r\n\r\nIn mixing bowl cut butter into flour until crumbly.  Stir in pecans.  Press evenly over bottom of pan.  Bake 350 for 20min.  Cool\r\n\r\nIn small bowl beatcream cheese on low til fluffy.  Beat in sugar and 1 small container thawed whipped topping.  Spread over crust.  Chill or freeze.\r\n\r\nIn large bowl combine both puddings, milk and Tia Maria.  Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.  Spread over cream cheese layer.  Chill or freeze til firm, several hours or over night.  Top with remaining topping and pecans.\r\n\r\nWhen time to serve let stand 10-15 minutes out of freezer. ','This dessert has also been called \"Sex in a Pan\"  You can take it out and eat some and put it back in the freezer to eat later.',6),(176,'Meatballs in Sauce','1-1/2 lbs ground beef\r\n1/2 lb ground pork\r\n2 eggs \r\n1/2 cup bread crumbs\r\n1/4 cup chopped green onions\r\n1 tsp horseradish\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n1/2 tsp pepper\r\n\r\nSauce\r\n\r\n1/4 cup brown sugar\r\n1 tsp dry mustard\r\n1/2 cup ketchp\r\n1/2 cup chili sauce\r\n1/2 cup water\r\n1/2 cup grape jelly or raspberry\r\n1/2 cup cider vinegar\r\n1 tbsp worcestershire sauce\r\n1/4 tsp tobasco sauce\r\n1 onion finely chopped \r\n1 clove garlic minced\r\n','Meatballs\r\n\r\nMix all ingredients together well and either fry or bake in oven.\r\n\r\nSauce\r\n\r\nMix all ingredients in pot and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.  Add balls and simmer 15 minutes longer.','Auntie Dora\r\n\r\nYou can also take a shortcut and just buy premade meatballs, cook them and put into the sauce and they are just as good.',17),(177,'Wacky Cake','1-1/2 cup all purpose flour\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n3 tbsp cocoa\r\n1 tsp baking powder\r\n1 tsp baking soda\r\npinch salt\r\n1 tbsp vinegar\r\n1 tsp vanilla\r\n5 tbsps shortening melted\r\n1 cup lukewarm water','350    25-30 minutes leave cake in pan to cool\r\n\r\nSift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt into an ungreased 8x8 cake pan.  Make 3 holesin the dry ingredients.  Put vinegar in one, vainlla in another and the melted shortening in the last hole.  Pour lukewarm water over all ingredients.  Stir until smooth.','When I was younger this is one of the cakes that gramma used to let me make because it was made all in the cake pan and there was very little mess.  We made it often.',8),(178,'Bushkas Cabbage Rolls','1 lb bacon diced\r\n2 medium onions diced\r\n1 cup chopped celery\r\n1-1/2 lbs ground pork\r\n1-3/4 cup white rice\r\n\r\n1 can tomato soup\r\n\r\ncabbage','275 for 3 hours\r\n\r\nFry together the bacon and onion.  Add the chopped celery.\r\n\r\nFry the pork until done.  Add to bacon and onions.\r\n\r\nCook the rice and rinse.  Add to the meat mixture.\r\n\r\nSteam the cabbage to separate the leaves.\r\n\r\nMix together tomato juice and one can tomato soup.  Pour on cabbage rolls and bake','This is Bushkas recipe.  We always loved her cabbage rolls.  The only thing that I would do different, that bushka never did, is serve them with sour cream on the side.',17),(179,'yorkshire pudding','7/8 cup flour\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n1/2 cup water\r\n2 eggs',NULL,NULL,5),(180,'Blueberry Oatmeal Square','<h1>Blueberry Oatmeal Squares</h1>\r\n<div id=\"current_rating\" _extended=\"true\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p class=\"recipe_intro\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"servings\">Servings: 24 squares</p>\r\n<h2>Ingredients:</h2>\r\n<div id=\"recipe_nutrition_supplemental\">\r\n<div class=\"related_photo_caption\">\r\n<p><!--<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Blueberry Oatmeal Squares\">--><img alt=\"Blueberry Oatmeal Squares\" src=\"http://www.canadianliving.com/img/photos/biz/blueberrysquare150.jpg\" /><!--</a>-->&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2-1/2 cups (625 mL) rolled oats (not instant)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n1-1/4 cups (300 mL) all-purpose flour&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n1 cup (250 mL) packed brown sugar&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n1 tbsp (15 mL) grated orange rind&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n1/4 tsp (1 mL) salt&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n1 cup (250 mL) cold butter, cubed&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n<strong>Filling:</strong><br />\r\n3 cups (750 mL) fresh blueberries&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n1/2 cup (125 mL) granulated sugar&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n1/3 cup (75 mL) orange juice&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n4 tsp (20 mL) cornstarch&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<div>Filling: In saucepan, bring blueberries, sugar and orange juice to boil; reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 10 minutes. Whisk cornstarch with 2 tbsp (25 mL) water; whisk into blueberries and boil, stirring, until thickened, about 1 minute. Place plastic wrap directly on surface; refrigerate until cooled, about 1 hour.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn large bowl, whisk together oats, flour, sugar, orange rind and sa&lt; with pastry blender, cut in butter until in coarse crumbs. Press half into 8-inch (2 L) square parchment paper&ndash;lined metal cake pan; spread with blueberry filling. Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture, pressing lightly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBake in centre of 350&deg;F (180&deg;C) oven until light golden, about 45 minutes. Let cool on rack before cutting into squares. <em>(Make-ahead: Cover and refrigerate for up to 2 days or overwrap with heavy-duty foil and freeze for up to 2 weeks.) </em></div>',NULL,6),(181,'Broccoli and Cheddar Cheese Soup','<p>1 onion chopped ( I use a large one)</p>\r\n<p>2 tbsp Kraft calorie wise italian dressing (I use olive oil or whatever dressing I have)</p>\r\n<p>1 can (10 fl oz) chicken broth (or one lge carton ready to use)</p>\r\n<p>2&nbsp; broth cans of water (only if you used condensed)</p>\r\n<p>4 cups chopped broccoli (I think I almost double this because we like the soup thick and hearty)</p>\r\n<p>1 cup skim milk (if I add extra broccoli I will sometimes add more too reduce thickness)</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup instand white rice, uncooked</p>\r\n<p>**&nbsp; the recipe doesn\'t call for it but I chop up and add 2 or 3 large granny smith apples to the onions while I am cooking them.</p>\r\n<p>***&nbsp; I also add some type of chipotle, or&nbsp;hot sauce to perk it up a bit after it is all pureed and do it to taste....</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>cheddar cheese for top</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Cook onions in dressing in large saucepan until tender.</p>\r\n<p>Add broth, water and broccoli.&nbsp; Bring to boil; cook 8 to 10 min or until broccoli is really tender.&nbsp; Stir in milk and rice.&nbsp; Reduce heat to medium.&nbsp; Cook 5 min (I usually cook longer)</p>\r\n<p>Pour soup in batches, into blender...or I use the braun it is easier.&nbsp; Blend until smooth.&nbsp; Return to saucepan; cook on low heat until heated through.&nbsp; Top each serving with cheese</p>\r\n<p>Serve with cheese bread if desired.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>If you follow the recipe there are only 140 calories per cup.&nbsp; A nice healthy hearty soup.</p>',26),(182,'Granny Cake','<p>1.5 cups white sugar</p>\r\n<p>2 eggs</p>\r\n<p>2 cups flour</p>\r\n<p>1 tsp baking soda</p>\r\n<p>1 tsp salt</p>\r\n<p>1 lge can crushed pineapple and juice</p>\r\n<p><u>Topping</u></p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup white sugar</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup margarine</p>\r\n<p>1/2 of a 6 oz can regular carnation milk (not 2%)</p>\r\n<p>1 tsp vanilla</p>','<p>Blend all cake ingredients together .&nbsp; Pour into a greased 9x13 pan.&nbsp; Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar on top.&nbsp; Bake at 350 for 35 to 45 minutes</p>\r\n<p>For the topping mix all the ingredients together and boil for 10 minutes.&nbsp; Poke holes in the ccake and pour on top of warm cake.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Got this recipe from Denise Lamontage.&nbsp; Nice and moist and tasty.&nbsp; A crowd pleaser</p>',8),(185,'Asparagus Brie Soup','    * 1/2 pound fresh asparagus, cut into 2-inch pieces\r\n    * 1/2 cup butter\r\n    * 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\r\n    * 3 cups chicken or vegetable broth\r\n    * 1 cup heavy whipping cream\r\n    * 1/2 cup white wine\r\n    * 4 to 6 ounces Brie, rind removed\r\n    * Dash salt and pepper\r\n\r\n  ','In a large saucepan, saute asparagus in butter until tender. Stir in flour until blended. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until golden brown. Gradually add broth, cream and wine or additional broth. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 10-15 minutes.\r\n    Place half of the soup at a time in a blender or food processor; cover and process until smooth. Return to the pan. Cube Brie and add to soup. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Yield: 4 servings. ','This is a recipe that Lyndsay found from my favorite food magazine Taste of Home......It is decadent and ooooohhhhhh so delicious....just don\'t make it if you are on a diet!!',26),(186,'Carrabba\'s Chicken Bryan Recipe and Lemon Butter','Lemon Butter\r\n\r\n4 tbsp butter, divided\r\n1/4 cup finely chopped onion\r\n1/4 cup finely chopped garlic\r\n1/2 cup white wine\r\n1/2 cup lemon juice\r\nsalt and pepper to taste\r\n\r\nChicken Bryan\r\n\r\n4 chicken breast\r\ngoat cheese (enough to put a layer on breast)\r\n3tbps fresh basil leaves, ,medium chop\r\n6-8 sundried tomato pieced julienned\r\ngrill seasoning (something with a little heat to it)\r\n ','Lemon Butter\r\n\r\nMelt 1 tbsp butter and saute onions and garlic until softened.\r\n\r\nAdd white wine and lemon juice, simmer approx 10 minutes until redued by 90%.  Let cool slightly\r\n\r\nAdd remaining butter a little at a time until mixture emulsified.  Do not let the butter get too hot or it will separate.  Season to taste.\r\n\r\nAdd basil and tomatoes to sauce just to warm up just before serving.\r\n\r\n\r\nChicken\r\n\r\nTake goat cheese out and let soften to room temperature.\r\n\r\nSeason the chicken breasts and grill.\r\n\r\nWhen chicken is almost ready place goat cheese on top and let soften as the chicken finishes cooking.\r\n\r\nPlate the chicken and spoon lemon butter sauce on top of the chicken covering the goat cheese.','Had this at a charity event in Destin.  Very tasty and the lemon butter is great on shrimp, kindda like shrimp scampi',23),(187,'Chop Suey Loaf','<p>2 tbsps margarine 1 cup white sugar 2 eggs 1 tsp vanilla 1/4 cup glazed cherries and fruits 2.5 tsps baking powder 1 cup raisins 1 cup milk 2.5 cups flour...enough to make a stiff dough</p>','<p>Mix all ingredients together and let rise in pan 1/2 hour before baking Oven 350 bake for approx. 1 hour</p>',NULL,5),(188,'Bunx with Potato Water','<p>2 pkgs yeast 1 cup lukewarm potato water 2 tsp sugar 1 cup scalded milk 1/2 cup crisco 1 tsp salt 1/2 cup sugar 2 eggs, beaten 6 cups flour</p>','<p>Mix together the yeast, potato water and sugar...dissolve. Set aside Add crisco, salt, sugar to scalded milk and cool to lukewarm. Add yeast mix. Add half flour and eggs. Add remaining flour. Let rise double in bulk about 1.5 hours. Divide into 3 parts. Let rest 10 mins. and shape buns. Let rise. After baked brush with butter.</p>',NULL,5),(189,'Western Beans','<p>6 slices of bacon 2 cups chopped onions 1/2 lb ground chuck black pepper 1.25 tsp salt 2 tbsps molasses (no more) 3 tbsps brown sugar 1 tsp dry mustard 2 cups canned tomatoes drained 56 oz Libbys beans</p>','<p>Cut slices of bacon into three pieces. Brown and remove from fat. In fat saute onions. Add ground chuck and cook til brown. Add remaining ingredients except Libbys beans. Simmer 15 minutes. Add Libbys beans. Place in large covered casserole and bake 2 to 3 hours 250 to 275 oven.</p>',NULL,17),(190,'Never Fail Pie Crust','1 lb. tenderflake\r\n5.5 cups flour (approx.)\r\npinch salt\r\n1 egg\r\n1 tbsp vinegar\r\n1 cup cold water','Mix lard flour and salt together til crumbly.  Beat egg and add to water and vinegar.  Add to flour mixture.  Mix until just mixed...do not over mix or crust will be tough',NULL,10),(191,'Layered Carrot Cake','2 cups flour\r\n2 tsp baking powder\r\n1.5 tsp baking soda\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n2.5 tsp cinnamon\r\n\r\n2 cup sugar\r\n1.5 cups oil\r\n4 large eggs\r\n\r\n2 3/4 cups grated carrots\r\n1 can crushed pineapple (drained)\r\n1 3/4 cups coconut\r\n3/4 cup chopped pecans\r\n\r\nIcing...\r\n\r\n8 oz cream cheese\r\n1/4 lb butter\r\napprox. 1 lb icing sugar\r\n1 tsp vanilla','350 oven\r\n\r\nMix all the dry ingredients together and set aside\r\n\r\nCream the sugar oil and eggs.\r\n\r\nAdd the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.  Then mix in the carrots, pineapple, coconut and pecans....\r\n\r\nplace in 2 9\" round pans\r\n\r\nBake for approx. 45 minutes or until cooked\r\n\r\nIcing....\r\n\r\nCream cream cheese and butter together, add vanilla.  Add icing sugar.\r\n\r\nWhen cake is cool ice.','This is a really yummy carrot cake that I have made....my favorite I think.',8),(192,'Olive Garden Chicken Gnocchi Soup','3-4 chicken breasts, cooked and diced\r\n4 cups chicken stock\r\n2 cups half and half\r\n1 stalk celery, small dice\r\n1 garlic clove chipped\r\n1/2 cup shredded carrots (I do about 1 cup)\r\n1/2 onion diced (I use one large)\r\n1 cup fresh spinach chopped (I use more)\r\n1 tbsp olive oil\r\n1 tsp thyme (I add more once cooked to taste)\r\nsalt and pepper\r\n16 ournces potato gnocchi (I make my own much nicer)\r\n1 tbsp corn starch','1.  Saute the onion, celery, garlic, carrot in oil over meadium heat until onion is translucent\r\n\r\n2.  Add chicken, chicken stock, half and half, salt and pepper, thyme.  Heat to boiling then add gnocchi.  Gently boil for 4 minutes then turn down to simmer for 10 minutes.\r\n\r\n3.  Add spinach and cook for another 2-3 minutes until wilted.\r\n\r\n4.  Heat to boiling and add cornstarch dissolved in 1-2 tbsp water if you want a thicker soup\r\n\r\n5.  Ladle into bowls and serve','I add more veggies to make a healthier thicker soup.',26),(193,'Cinnamon Baked French Toast','<p>1 - 2 loaves cinnamon raisin bread 8 large eggs 2 cups milk 1/2 cup heavy cream&nbsp; 1/2 to full brick cream cheese Streusal Topping (I don\'t think this is required, too sweet but I have made it with this on top) 1/2 cup four 1/2 cup brown sugar 1 tsp cinnamon 1/4 tsp salt 1/2 cup cold butter cut into pieces</p>','<p>grease a 9x13 pan cut the bread into cubes and evenly space in the pan. Cut up the cream cheese and place in between the chunks of bread....this is to your own taste how much you put. In large bowl mix the eggs, milk, cream, Pour evenly over bread. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight or for several hours. Streusel... Mix flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, and salt. Add butter pieces and cut into the dry mixture using a fork or hands. Combine until the mixture resembles sand a few pea sized chunks. Cover and store in fridge. oven 350 Sprinkle crumb mixture over the top. BAke 45-55 minutes or until toast is set and brown Serve with butter and maple syrup</p>','<p>I don\'t think this recipe requires the streusel on top. I have made it both ways and prefer without otherwise it is extremely sweet</p>',36),(194,'Olive Garden Ravioli di Portobello','Filling..\r\n\r\n1 lb Portobello mushrooms (I find cremini just as good and less expensive) finely chopped\r\n1 onion finely chopped \r\n1/4 cup butter\r\nsalt and pepper to taste\r\n\r\nDumplings Wrappers\r\n\r\n1.5 cups cake flour\r\n2 eggs \r\n1/2 tbsp salt\r\n2 tbsps vaking powder\r\n\r\nWhite Sauce...\r\n\r\n2 cups milk\r\n1/4 cup butter\r\n1/4 cup four\r\n\r\nSun Dried tomato Smoked Sauce....\r\n\r\n2 cups white sauce (recipe above)\r\n8 ounces smoked Gouda cheese\r\n2 to 3 sun dried tomatoes (use 3 or more)\r\n\r\nGreen onion\r\ntomato\r\n\r\n','1.  Filling...Melt butter in skillet and saute the onion for approx 5 min or until transparent.  Add mushrooms and stir fry over high heat for about 5 minutes so all the liquid is evaporated.  Reduce heat and cook for another 5 min.  Remove from heat and let minxture cool.  Place mixture inside the dough and create dumplings.  Place dumplings in boiling water and boil for approx. 2 min until done (will float to the top when done).  Melt the remaining butter and pour over the ravioli, mix and serve.\r\n\r\n2.  Dumling Wrapper...Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.  Roll dough on flat surface until dough is 1/4 inch thick.  Make circles of the dough.  With fingertip or brush, spread some water on the edges.  Fill with mushroom mixture.  Fold in half and squeeze gently to make ravioli. \r\n\r\n3.  Sauce.... Heat butter in sauce pan until melted, whisk in flour and cook over medium heat for about 3 min.  Whisk in milk and cook for another 2 min til thickened.  Add 8 oz. Gouds cheese and chopped sun dried tomatoes.  Mix on med low heat until cheese is melted.  Pour over ravioli and top with chopped green onion and tomato\r\n\r\n ','I made these and loved them.  I think you can probably find some type of wrapper to use instead of making your own to make it less time consumming.',14),(195,'Cottage Cheese Pancakes with Strawberry Almond Sauce','1 cup cottage cheese\r\n3 eggs\r\n2 tbsps sugar\r\n1/4 cup milk\r\n1 cup flour\r\n1/2 tsp cinnamon\r\n1/4 tsp salt\r\n2 tbsps butter or margarine\r\n\r\nStrawberry Sauce..\r\n\r\n1/4 cup sliced almonds\r\n2 tbsps butter\r\n3 cups strawberries halved\r\n1/4 cup sugar','Pancakes...\r\n\r\nIn medium bowl mash cottage cheese until almost smooth.  Beat in eggs, sugar and milk just just blended.  Gradually beat in flour until smooth.  Stir in cinnamon, salt and butter.  Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto hot lightly greased griddle.  When underside is lightly browned and top bubbly, turn and lightly brown other side.  Keep warm in oven until finished cooking\r\n\r\nSauce...\r\n\r\nIn medium skillet over medium heat saute almonds in butter until lightly toasted.  Add straberries and sugar.  Cook stirring occassionally just until berries release their juices and the sauce is hot.\r\n\r\nServe over pancakes.',NULL,36),(196,'Blintzes with Strawberry Sour Cream','Crepes...\r\n\r\n4 eggs\r\n1 cup all purpose flour\r\n1 tbsp granulated sugar\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n1/2 cup water\r\n1/4 cup melted butter\r\nbutter for cooking\r\n\r\nFilling...\r\n\r\n1 lb creamed cottage cheese (you want \"dry\" cottage cheese not creamy)\r\n2 eggs\r\n3 tbsps granulated sugar\r\n1 tsp grated lemon peel\r\n1/2 tsp vanilla\r\n\r\nTopping....\r\n\r\n2 cups strawberries \r\n3 tbsps sugar\r\n1 cup sour cream','Crepes:  Beat eggs lightly.  Beat in flour, sugar and salt.  Add milk and water.  Stir in 1/4 cup melted butter.  Allow batter to rest for 1 hour before making crepes.\r\n\r\nHeat 8\" crepe or omelet pan and melt 1 tbsp butter.  Pour about 1/4 cup batter into pan.  swirl until bottom is coated, then pour excess back into bowl.  Cook until crepe is brown then flip out of pan cooking only one side.  Repeat with remaining batter. adding additional butter to pan only is necessary.\r\n\r\nFilling:\r\n\r\nBeat cheese until smooth, add remaining ingredients blend well.\r\n\r\nSpoon a little filling onto cooked side of each crepe.  Fold bottom of crepe over filling, fold over sides then roll up.  Refrigerate or freeze until needed.\r\n\r\nTo cook, melt enough butter to coat bottom of large heavy skillet. Add blintzes, without crowding.  Cook until browned on ech side.  Keep warm in 200 degree oven while cooking remaining blintzes.\r\n\r\nFor the sauce you can either mix all the ingredients together or serve separately.','I love love love cheese blintzes.  I don\'t think you really need the sauce....just sour cream is GREAT!!!',36),(197,'Baked Herb Chicken with Wine','1 whole chicken 3 to 4 lbs\r\n2 tbsps softened butter\r\n3 tbsps dried leaf tarragon\r\n2 tbsps dried leaf thyme\r\n2 tbsps dried leaf summer savory\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n1/8 tsp pepper\r\n2 tbsps olive oil\r\n\r\nHerb Wine Sauce:\r\n\r\n3 tbsps butter\r\n1/4 finely chopped onion\r\n1/2 tsp thyme\r\n1/2 tsp savory\r\n1/4 tsp tarragon\r\n2 tbsps flour\r\n1 cup dry white wine\r\n2/3 cup half and hlaf \r\n1/3 cup condensed undiluted chicken broth\r\ndash pepper','Pat dry chicken.  Heat oven to 450\r\n\r\nCombine 1 tbsp of the butter with 1 tsp each of tarragon, thyme and savory, mix well.  Place mixture inside the chicken.  Close opening with skewers.  Brush chicken with 1 tbsp of butter and sprinkle with remaining herbs.  Sprinkle with 1 tsp salt and 1/8 tsp pepper.\r\n\r\nPlace chicken in a shallow baking dish.  Roast chicken for 30 minutes.  Reduce oven to 350 and drizzle oil over chicken.  Roast for 30 to 45 min longer until meat is cooked.\r\n\r\nSauce:\r\n\r\nHeat butter in a saucepan over medium heat; add onion, thyme, savory and tarragon and saute until onion is beginning to color. Remove from heat and stir in flour.  Gradually stir in the wine, cream and chicken broth.  Add pepper.  Cook, stirring just to the boiling point.  Serve with roasted chicken.\r\n\r\n','A real easy chicken recipe that is very tasty.',23),(198,'Tuna Melts (nanas recipe)','2 hard boiled eggs\r\n7 oz can tuna\r\n1/4 cup finely chopped celery\r\ndash onion salt\r\n1/4 cup mayo\r\n1 cup grated cheddar cheese\r\n2 tbsps chili sauce\r\n1/4 chopped green pepper\r\n\r\nHot dog or hamburger buns','MIx all the ingredients together and place inside of the hotdog or hamburger bun.  Wrap in foil and place in 400 degree oven for approx 15 minutes.','Nana used to make these all the time.  It was the first \"canned tuna\" thing I ever ate and quite liked.',17),(199,'Cream and Mustard Sauce for Scallops','1 tbsp butter\r\n1 tbsp finely chopped onion\r\n2 tbsps red wine vinegar\r\n1 cup cream\r\n1 tbsp dijon mustard\r\nsalt to flavor','melt butter and add onion.  Saute til tender.  Add vinegar and boil until evaporate to 1/2\r\n\r\nAdd the cream, dijon and salt..heat and pour over scallops...','A very nice sauce...could probably be used for other seafood.',24),(200,'Penne with Chicken, Apples and Cranberries','1 tbsp butter\r\n1 lb chicken breasts cut into strips (I use a roasted chicken from the grocery store, saves alot of time and effort)\r\n4 green onions sliced\r\n2 green apples thinly sliced\r\npinch nutmeg\r\nsalt and pepper\r\n2 tbsp cider vinegar (I find always needs more to add a little punch to the sauce)\r\n1.5 cups whipping cream (usually more required)\r\n1.2 cup craisins\r\npenne\r\n1 cup or more grated old cheddar cheese\r\nchopped fresh chives for garnish...','In lge skillet, melt half of the butter, brown chicken strips, transfer to bowl.\r\n\r\nAdd remaining butter.  Add green onions, apple, nutmeg, 3/4 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper. Cook for approx. 3 minutes or until softened (often takes a little longer)Add vinegar, scaping any bits stuck to pan.  Stir in cream and cranberries, bring to boil.  Reduce heat and boil gently stirring often for 3 min or until slightly thickened.\r\n\r\nCook pasta.\r\n\r\nAdd chicken and simmer for 3 min or until chicken fully cooked.  Pour over cooked pasta and sprinkle with cheese.  Season with salt and pepper.  Chives on top for garnish.','Leftover turkey can be used as well.  The cheese is really important.  Grate more than you think you will need.... This recipe was from Auntie Debbie',14),(201,'Slow Cooker Orange Chicken','8 small boneless skinless chicken thighs\r\n3 tbsps flour\r\n1/3 cup orange marmalade\r\n1/3 cup original bbq sauce\r\n2 tbsps soy sauce\r\n1 tbsp grated fresh gingerroot','Toss chicken with flour in slow cooker.\r\n\r\nStir in all remaining ingredients; cover with lid\r\n\r\nCook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.','I have made this and it is pretty good for a slow cooker recipe.... and really easy...can be put together and left cooking during the day',23),(202,'Baked Scallops with Brie','1 lb scallops\r\nbrie\r\nwhite wine\r\nsalt and pepper\r\n4 tbsps olive oil\r\n3 cloves garlic minced\r\ndried thyme','Heat the oven to 450 degree.  You will need several small oven proof ramekins.\r\n\r\nPlace the scallops in a mixing bowl.  Add a quick grinding of the pepper and some salt.  Add a small pinch of thyme.  Mix together and then add olive oil.  Mix again.\r\n\r\nPut the scallops in the baking dishes and pour in just enough wine to come half way up the scallops.\r\n\r\nPlace 1/4\" thick slices of brie on the top of the scallops so that it is about half covered.\r\n\r\nBake in 400 degree oven','I have made these....nice for an appetizer',24),(203,'Mountain Icing..(Boiled icing)','3/4 cup corn syrup\r\n1 egg white \r\n1 tsp vanilla','Bring corn syrup to a boil and add gradually to egg white.  Add vanilla and beat til stiff.',NULL,17),(204,'Angel Food Cake with Apricots (Moms recipe)','Angel food cake cut into 2 or three layers\r\n\r\n1/4 pint whipped cream plus 1 small jar strained apricots (baby food) and rind of whole orange very finely grated.\r\n\r\nIce with:\r\n\r\n1/2 pint of whipped cream plus 2 tsp instant coffee plus 3 tbsps cocoa.','Mom used to make this but haven\'t had it for years.  I seem to remember quite liking it.',NULL,8),(205,'Beer Batter (for fish or onion rings)','2 cups flour\r\n2 tsp baking powder\r\n1 tsp salt\r\n2 eggs 1 bottle beer\r\n1/4 cup oil','mix together and dip fish or onion rings in \r\n\r\nFry in oil',NULL,17),(206,'Cream Pineapple Squares','Crust\r\n2 cups graham crumbs\r\n1/2 cup melted butter\r\n\r\nMiddle:\r\n\r\n1/2 cup soft butter\r\n1.5 cups icing sugar\r\n2 eggs\r\n\r\n1 large tin crushed pineapple drained\r\npint whipping cream\r\n\r\n.5 cup graham crumbs for topping','Mix graham crumbs with butter and press into bottom of 9x13 pan.  Cook for 15 min in 325 oven.  Cool.\r\n\r\nMiddle:  Mix all ingredients together until smooth and light.  Spread over cooled crust.\r\n\r\nBeat cream and mix in drained pineapple.  Place on top.\r\n\r\nSprinkle remaining graham crumbs on top.\r\n\r\nPlace in fridge.\r\n','Gramma used to make these all the time.',6),(207,'Snowballs','Peel and boil fair sized potato.  Dry over heat and mash it well.  Add almond or vanilla flavoring to taste.  Keep adding icing sugar until you have a paste.\r\n\r\nMelt sweetened chocolate in top of double boiler.\r\n\r\nForm little balls of the paste and dip in chocolate then into shredded coconut.\r\n\r\nPut on wax paper and cool before storing.',NULL,NULL,19),(208,'Spanakopita Spinach Pie','1 medium onion chopped\r\n2 green onions chopped\r\n2 tbsp oil\r\n1 - 10 oz pkg frozen chopped spinach\r\n1 - 12 oz low fat cottage cheese\r\n1 - 8 oz light cream cheese softened\r\n1/2 cup feta cheese crumbled\r\n1/2 tsp dried dill weed\r\n1/4 tsp pepper\r\n1 lge egg\r\n1 - 16 oz pkg phyllo\r\n1/2 cup melted butter  \r\n','Cook all onions until gold.  Remove from heat\r\n\r\nDrain spinach til dry and add to onions.  Add cottage cheese cream cheese, feta, dill, pepper and eggs.  Mix well.\r\n\r\nBrush bottom of baking dish with oil.  Use half of phyllo on bottom of pan.  Spread spinach mixture on top of phyllo.  Place remaining phyllo on top.\r\n\r\nBake 350 degrees for 45 minutes.','This recipe came from Paula',17),(209,'Pasta with Gorgonzola','1 lb fresh spinach fetuccini\r\n4 tbsps unsalted butter\r\n2 cups whipping cream\r\n10 oz gorgonzola cheese\r\n4 tbsp parmesan\r\nsalt and pepper\r\n','reduce the cream until 1.5 to 1.75 cups remain and cream has thickened.  Crumble cheese into cream.  DO NOT BOIL.  Add parmesan and pepper (salt if needed)\r\n\r\nAdd butter to sauce just before serving.',NULL,14),(210,'Mushroom and Bacon Risotto','2 tbsps olive oil\r\n1 onion chopped\r\n115 grams portobello mushrooms chopped\r\n225 grams risotto rice\r\n600 ml hot chicken stock\r\n6 slices bacon\r\n1/2 cup white wine\r\n25 gram fresh grated parmesan cheese','Chop bacon and fry til crisp and set aside to drain.\r\n\r\nHeat the oil in heavy based pan and cook til the onion soft.  Add the mushroom and cook another 4 mins.\r\n\r\nAdd the risotto rice and stir well to coat the grains in the oil.  Add the white wine and let boil til gone.  Add the hot chicken broth a little at a time til rice tender.  When completely cooked add the bacon and parmesan.\r\n\r\nPepper to taste','Comfort food....yummmmm',17),(211,'Blueberry White Chocolate Chunk Scones','3 cups flour\r\n1/4 cup plus 2 tbsps Sugar in the Raw divided\r\n1 tbsp baking pwder\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n3/4 cup cold unsalted butter cut into small pieces\r\n3/4 cups plus 2 tbsp milk divided\r\n1 egg beaten\r\n1 tbsp lemon zest\r\n1 cup blueberries\r\n6 squares white chocolate chopped','Oven 375\r\n\r\nMix flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.  Cut butter into flour mixture until resembles coarse crumbs.  Add 3/4 cup milk, egg and zest, stir just until mixture forms dough.  Stir in blueberries and chocolate\r\n\r\nDivide dough in half.  On lightly floured surface, pat each half into 7\" rounds.  Cut each into 8 wedges.  Place on baking sheet.  Brush with remaining milk and sprinkle with remaining sugar.\r\n\r\nBake 25 minutes or until golden brown','I think these are best made with fresh blueberries.  I tried frozen and they were a little moist.  I use the basic recipe, cut back a little on the sugar and use cranberries and more lemon zest.  I don\'t think the sugar on the top is required.  Made these when the Aussies were here and they liked them.',5),(212,'Caramel Popcorn','<p>1 cup butter 2 cups brown sugar 1/2 cup corn syrup 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon baking soda 1 teaspoon vanilla extract 5 quarts popped popcorn</p>','<p>Preheat oven to 250 degrees F (95 degrees C). Place popcorn in a very large bowl. In a medium saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil without stirring 4 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla. Pour in a thin stream over popcorn, stirring to coat. Place in two large shallow baking dishes and bake in preheated oven, stirring every 15 minutes, for 1 hour. Remove from oven and let cool completely before breaking into pieces.</p>','<p>Made this for a Super Bowl Party....really good and buttery.....no need for &quot;Kernels&quot; anymore....:)</p>',19),(213,'Tomato and Camembert (Brie) Tart','<p>Tart Dough: 1 1/2 cup(s) all-purpose flour</p>\r\n<p>6 tablespoon(s)</p>\r\n<p>(3/4 stick) cold unsalted butter , cut into 1/2-inch pieces</p>\r\n<p>1/2 teaspoon(s) salt1</p>\r\n<p>/2 teaspoon(s) coarsely ground pepper</p>\r\n<p>2 tablespoon(s) (add more as needed) extra-virgin olive oil</p>\r\n<p>1 tablespoon(s) water</p>\r\n<p>Tart:</p>\r\n<p>1 tablespoon(s) Dijon mustard</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup(s) grated Gruy&egrave;re cheese</p>\r\n<p>4 plum tomatoes, cut into 1/2-inch slices and seeds removed</p>\r\n<p>6 ounce(s) Camembert cheese, sliced into 1/8-inch strips</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup(s) extra-virgin olive oil</p>\r\n<p>1/4 cup(s) fresh parsley, chopped</p>\r\n<p>1/4 cup(s) fresh basil, chopped 1 teaspoon(s) fresh rosemary, finely chopped</p>\r\n<p>1 tablespoon(s) fresh thyme leaves</p>\r\n<p>1 small bay leaf, finely crumbled</p>\r\n<p>1 clove(s) garlic, minced</p>','<p>1.Make the tart dough: Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, combine the flour, butter, salt, and pepper until mixture resembles coarse meal.</p>\r\n<p>2.Using a fork, mix in 2 tablespoons of the oil and the water just until the bottom of the mixture begins to cling together. If necessary, add an additional tablespoon of oil.</p>\r\n<p>3.Gather into a ball, flatten into a disk, wrap in plastic wrap, and chill for 30 minutes. 4.Bake the tart: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Roll out the chilled dough into a 14-inch circle and place it into a tart pan; set aside.</p>\r\n<p>5.Spread the mustard over the bottom of the tart shell. Sprinkle the Gruy&egrave;re evenly over the mustard and alternately place the tomato and Camembert over the Gruy&egrave;re.</p>\r\n<p>6.In a small bowl, mix the remaining 1/2 cup of extra-virgin olive oil, all of the herbs, and the garlic together and brush two-thirds of the mixture over the tart. Bake on the middle shelf of the oven for 35 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>7.Remove the tart and brush it with the remaining oil. Serve warm.</p>','<p>Made this tart....really nice and tasty. I think there is tooooo much olive oil.....I cut down on it and would cut down more next time.&nbsp; I&nbsp;also used Brie instead of camembert</p>',25),(214,'Bacon, Egg and Toast Cups','3 Tbsps butter melted\r\n6 slices whole-wheat bread\r\n6 full slices of bacon\r\n6 large eggs\r\nsalt and pepper','Preheat oven to 375 degrees.\r\nLightly butter 6 muffin cups.\r\nCut crusts off of bread and take rolling pin and flatten slices of bread.\r\nPress bread into muffin tin and brush with remaining melted butter.\r\n\r\nCook bacon until almost crisp.  Lay 1 slice of bacon in each cup with edge hanging out.  Crack egg over each.  Season with salt and pepper.\r\n\r\nBake until eggs whites are set.  Approx 15-20 minutes.  \r\n\r\nServe immediately.\r\n','The first time I made these I thought they were good but could be improved soooo...I added in the bottom on top of the bacon slice a spoonful of salsa.  I also did them with parmesan or blue cheese sprinkled on the top.\r\n\r\nFor the cooking time..if you are only making 4 or 5 use the middle of the muffin pan and it only takes about 15 minutes to have the yolks just slightly wet.  When I made a full pan of 12 it took about 30 minutes.',36),(215,'Deep Fried Perogies','<p>perogies seasoned bread crumbs egg oil</p>','<p>Boil the perogies until they are just cooked and place on parchement/wax paper to dry. Slightly beat the egg and dip each perogy into egg wash and then into the crumbs and then onto a cookie sheet. You can put them in the fridge now to let the crumbs set. When ready to eat heat the oil, not too hot, and put a few perogies at a time into the oil and fry. Make sure you don\'t over cook or that the oil is too hot or the perogies will just pop open (not good) For a sauce I mixed sour cream and sweet chili sauce and it was very nice but you can make any sauce that you like.</p>','<p>Made these for an appetizer to use up homemade perogies I had. They were really very good. You can deep fry them without the crumbs but I tried it both ways and with crumbs is sooo much better</p>',18),(216,'Shrimp Scampi','<p>1.5 lbs fresh shrimp shelled</p>\r\n<p>2 tbsps olive oil</p>\r\n<p>1 medium onion small dice</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup white wine</p>\r\n<p>3 cloves garlic minced</p>\r\n<p>3 tbsps parsley, finely chopped</p>\r\n<p>1 pinch crushed red pepper</p>\r\n<p>4 oz butter</p>\r\n<p>angel hair pasta</p>','<p>Heat oil in a saute pan and add onion, cook for approx 2 min. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute. Do not brown. Add butter, wine, red pepper, salt and pepper and reduce by half Add shrimp and cook til fully cooked Add pasta to sauce and serve. Sprinkle with parsley.</p>','<p>This is the recipe from Olive Garden. I found it a little too boring the first time so I added a few things. I follow it until they get to reduce it by half. At that point I add my shrimp and cook them then take them out. I like them to pick up that sauce taste. I then reduce the sauce and once that is done I add in a little lemon juice and some cream cheese. When the sauce is finished and the pasta cooked I add the shrimp back into the sauce just to reheat. I also top with some parmesan cheese....everything is better with cheese...:)</p>',14),(217,'Pumpkin Doughnut Muffins','<p>For the batter 10 tablespoons (1 1/4 sticks) unsalted butter, room temperature, plus more for pan 3 cups all-purpose flour (spooned and leveled), plus more for pan</p>\r\n<p>2 1/2 teaspoons baking powder</p>\r\n<p>1/4 teaspoon baking soda</p>\r\n<p>1 teaspoon coarse salt</p>\r\n<p>1/2 teaspoon ground nutmeg</p>\r\n<p>1/4 teaspoon ground allspice</p>\r\n<p>1/3 cup buttermilk</p>\r\n<p>1 1/4 cups pure pumpkin puree (from a 15-ounce can)</p>\r\n<p>3/4 cup light brown sugar</p>\r\n<p>2 large eggs</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the sugar coating</p>\r\n<p>3/4 cup granulated sugar</p>\r\n<p>2 1/2 teaspoons ground cinnamon</p>\r\n<p>1/4 cup (1/2 stick) unsalted butter, melted</p>','<p>1.Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Butter and flour 12 standard muffin cups.</p>\r\n<p>Make batter: In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, and allspice. In a small bowl, whisk together buttermilk and pumpkin puree. In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, scraping down bowl as needed. With mixer on low, add flour mixture in three additions, alternating with two additions pumpkin mixture, and beat to combine.</p>\r\n<p>2.Spoon 1/3 cup batter into each muffin cup and bake until a toothpick inserted in center of a muffin comes out clean, 30 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine granulated sugar and cinnamon. Let muffins cool 10 minutes in pan on a wire rack. Working with one at a time, remove muffins from pan, brush all over with butter, then toss to coat in sugar mixture. Let muffins cool completely on a wire rack.</p>','<p>I&nbsp;didn\'t have buttermilk when I made these so I made my own by using regular milk and vinegar (approx. 1 tsp)</p>\r\n<p>I tried these in Florida.....Gaetan fell in love with them....really good...a nice change from the regular muffins...</p>',5),(218,'Shrimp Scampi','shrimp, shelled raw\r\n2 tbsp olive oil\r\n1 medium onion diced\r\n1/2 cup white wine\r\n3 cloves minced garlic\r\npinch (or a little more) red pepper flakes\r\n4 oz butter\r\nangel hair pasta\r\nchopped parsley\r\n(cream cheese - added this in to make the sauce thicker and creamy.  I found the original a little blah, I also added the juice from half a lemon)','Heat oil in saute pan.  Add onion and saute for 2 minutes.  Add garlic and saute for 1 minutes, do not brown.  Add butter, wine and red pepper,salt and pepper and reduce by half.\r\n\r\nAdd shrimp and cook for 1 - 2 minutes.  Do not overcook or they will be tough.\r\n\r\nCook pasta and toss with sauce.\r\n\r\nTop with fresh parmesan','This is the Olive Garden recipe.  As you can see I made a few changes but we prefer it this way.',24),(219,'Saucy Shrimp from Bonefish Grill','1 oz butter\r\n5 oz shrimp, cleaned\r\n4 kalamata olives (you need to add a few more Approx. 4 per person)\r\n1/4 of lime tomato garlic sauce (below)\r\n2 oz feta cheese, crumbled\r\nfresh parsley\r\n\r\nNice loaf of crispy fresh bread\r\n\r\nLime Tomtato Garlic Sauce (LTGS)\r\n\r\n1/2 cup roughly chopped sundried tomatoes\r\n1/2 cup chopped fresh tomatoes (nicely diced)\r\n1/4 cup lemon juice\r\njuice from 2 limes\r\n1/4 cup chopped garlic\r\n1/2 cup white wine\r\n5 tbls granulated sugar\r\n1 cup heavy cream\r\n2 tsps salt\r\n1 tsp pepper\r\n2 tbsps butter cut into pieces','For the LTG Sauce\r\n\r\nPut everything except the cream, butter and salt and pepper into a saute pan.  Let cook and reduce by half.\r\n\r\nAdd the cream, salt and pepper and let simmer til thickened.  On low heat slowly add the butter until melted.\r\n\r\nTo make saucy shrimp:\r\n\r\n1.  Add utter to saute pan.  Saute shrimp, olives, and sun dried tomatoes until shrimp opaque.\r\n\r\n2.  Add 1/4 of the LTGS.  Toss with the shrimp and remove pan from heat.\r\n\r\n3.  Top with crumbled feta and a pinch of parsley','When I made these I made 1/2 of the LTGS recipe and I used it all so it would be nice and saucy to dip the bread into.  I also added a little more cream to the sauce til I had the flavor I wanted. \r\n\r\nThe recipe calls for tooooo many sundried tomatoes.  I would put half what they are calling for next time but you can put it to taste.',24),(220,'Blue and Pear Salmon','2 salmon filets\r\n3 slices bacon, cooked and chopped\r\n1 onion chopped finely\r\n2 cloves garlic finely chopped\r\n1 pear peeled, cleaned and finely diced\r\n1/2 cup white wine\r\n1/4 cup maple syrup\r\n1 tbsp chopped fresh savory or 1 tsp dreied savory\r\nsalt and pepper to taste\r\n1 - 2 slices of bread crumbled\r\n2 oz blue cheese (or to taste) or Brie,cheddar or gouda whichever you prefer','1.  preheat oven to 375\r\n\r\n2.  Over medium high heat cook bacon then add onion and garlic.  Add pears, wine, maple syrup and savory.  Season generously and let simmer for 5 minutes\r\n\r\n3.  Remove from heat and add bread to absorb liquid.\r\n\r\n4.  On parchment paper place the filet of salmon.  But in half, not all the way through creating a pocket.  Place dressing inside and top with blue cheese.\r\n\r\n5.  Bake for approx. 25 to 30 minutes.','This is really good.  In the recipe they put whole filets on top of each other but I cut each in half and stuffed.  I found the dressing a tad too mild so I will add some lemon zest to the dressing next time and have fresh lemon to squeeze on top.',24),(221,'BLT Bites','<p>16 to 20 cherry tomatoes (try to pick the larger ones)</p>\r\n<p>4 strips bacon, cooked and crumbled</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup mayonnaise</p>\r\n<p>1/3 cup finely chopped green onions</p>\r\n<p>3 tbsps grated parmesan</p>\r\n<p>2 tbsps chopped fresh parsley</p>','<p>1. Cut a think slice off each tomato top. Scoop and discard pulp. Invert the tomatoes on a paper towel to drain.</p>\r\n<p>2. Combine the remaining ingredients. Put into tomatoes.</p>\r\n<p>3. Refigerate for serveral hours</p>','<p>These are ohhh so yummy. I changed the recipe a bit. They called for wayyyyy too much bacon. To fill the tomatoes the easiest way is to put in a plastic bag and pipe into the tomatoes. To keep them from falling over I put them on a plater with cheap white rice. Place saran wrap ontop of the rice otherwise it will stick to the tomatoes</p>',18),(222,'Appetizer Tortilla Pinwheels','<p>1 cup (8 oz) sour cream</p>\r\n<p>1 package (8 oz) cream cheese softened</p>\r\n<p>1 can (4.5 oz) chopped ripe olives</p>\r\n<p>1 can (4 oz) finely chopped green chilies, well drained</p>\r\n<p>1 cup (4 oz) shredded cheddar cheese</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup chopped green onions</p>\r\n<p>garlic powder to taste</p>\r\n<p>seasoned salt to taste</p>\r\n<p>5 flour tortillas (10 inches) room temperature</p>\r\n<p>fresh parsley for garnish</p>\r\n<p>salsa (to serve on the side)</p>','<p>1. In a large bowl beat the first 8 ingredients until well blended.</p>\r\n<p>2. Spread over the tortillas, roll up tightly.</p>\r\n<p>3. Wrap each with plastic wrap, twisting ends, refrigerate for several hours.</p>\r\n<p>4. Unwrap, cut in 1/2 inch slices. Discard the ends. Garnish with parsley.</p>\r\n<p>5. Serve with salsa</p>','<p>These are really quite tasty. After I mixed the ingredients together I put it in the fridge for a little while to firm up a little. You could make these without the olives but they do add a nice flavor</p>',18),(223,'Good Old Fashioned Pancakes','3/4 cup flour\r\n1-3/4 tsps baking powder\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1-1/2 tsps white sugar\r\n1/2 cup and 2 tbsps milk\r\n1 egg\r\n1 tbsps and 1.5 tsps butter melted','1.  In bowl sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.  Make a well in the center and pour in the milk, egg and melted butter. Mix until smooth.\r\n\r\n2.  Heat lightly oiled frying pan.  Use approx. 1/4 cup for each pancake.  Brown on both sides \r\n','This makes just 4 good size pancakes',36),(224,'Lobster Bisque','<p>1/2 lb lobster meat cut into small chunks (I use canned crab meat and shrimp that I cut up)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;2 tbsps minced shallots</p>\r\n<p>2 tbsps chopped green onions</p>\r\n<p>3 cloves garlic crushed</p>\r\n<p>1/4 cup white wine</p>\r\n<p>2 tsps worcestershire sauce</p>\r\n<p>2 tsps tabasco sauce</p>\r\n<p>1 tsp dried thyme</p>\r\n<p>6 tbsps dry sherry</p>\r\n<p>1 tsp paprika</p>\r\n<p>1 cup hot water</p>\r\n<p>1 tsp lobster base</p>\r\n<p>4 oz tomato paste</p>\r\n<p>2 bay leaves</p>\r\n<p>2 cups heavy whipping cream</p>\r\n<p>4 tbsps butter</p>','<p>1. In saute pan heat a little oil and saute shallots, onions, and garlic for one minute.</p>\r\n<p>2. Deglaze the pan with the white wine.</p>\r\n<p>3. Add the worchestershire, tabasco and thyme and saute for another minute.</p>\r\n<p>4. Deglaze the pan with the sherry.</p>\r\n<p>5. Add paprika,hot water and lobster base and combine well.</p>\r\n<p>6. Stir in tomato paste and add the bay leaves.</p>\r\n<p>7. Simmer for 10 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>8. Whisk in heavy cream and add the butter and bring to a boil.</p>\r\n<p>9. Add seafood and heat through.</p>\r\n<p>10. At this point you can either leave it chunky or I puree it.</p>','<p>Too expensive to use lobster so I used crab meat and shrimp and the taste is just as good. I replace the hot water and lobster base with clam juice. I also like to put a little parmesan on top when I serve it. Just adds another little flavor. Servie it with a nice crusty bread....Yummmmmm</p>',26),(225,'Mussels Josephine (Bonefish Grill)','<p>3 doz PEI mussels (2 lbs)</p>\r\n<p>4 oz chopped onion</p>\r\n<p>2 oz chopped garlic</p>\r\n<p>14 oz chopped tomatoes (juice and all)</p>\r\n<p>fresh basil</p>\r\n<p>2 oz sambuca or Pernod</p>\r\n<p>juice of 1/2 lemon parsley for garnish</p>\r\n<p>Lemon Butter Sauce (use 3/4 cup)</p>\r\n<p>1/4 cup butter</p>\r\n<p>2 tbsps minced onions</p>\r\n<p>2 tbsps minced garlic</p>\r\n<p>1/3 cup fresh lemon juice</p>\r\n<p>2 tbsps dry white wine</p>\r\n<p>sea salt pepper to taste</p>\r\n<p>2 tbsps cold butter</p>','<p>1. Coat a hot skillet with melted butter. Add mussels and cover. The steam will cook the mussels. Approx 1-2 minutes. They will open.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;2. Add into the pan onion, garlic, chopped tomatoes.</p>\r\n<p>3. Add sambuca. let the alcohol cook off then add fresh basil, lemon juice and lemon butter. Cook for 45 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>4. Discard any mussels that are not open. Serve in bowl topped with parsley.</p>\r\n<p>Lemon Butter Sauce</p>\r\n<p>1. Melt butter. Remove from heat and let sit until milk solids settle to bottom. Skim the butter on top. Discard sediment.</p>\r\n<p>2. Saute onion and garlic in 2 tbsps of clarified butter until transparent.</p>\r\n<p>3. Stir in lemon juice adn white wine and season with salt and pepper.</p>\r\n<p>4. Simmer 2-3 minutes to reduce liquid.</p>\r\n<p>5. Remove from heat and add in cold butter until sauce is smooth and butter is melted.</p>','<p>I don\'t bother to make the Lemon Butter Sauce. I add the wine, lemon juice, butter to the pan when I cook the mussles.</p>',24),(226,'Mushroom Soup','<p>2 tbsps butter</p>\r\n<p>1 small onion chopped</p>\r\n<p>1 celery stalk chopped</p>\r\n<p>2 cloves garlic chopped</p>\r\n<p>1 lb (500g) portobello mushrooms or cremini</p>\r\n<p>1/4 cup white wine</p>\r\n<p>4 cups chicken stock</p>\r\n<p>1 medium potato</p>\r\n<p>sprig fresh thyme</p>\r\n<p>1 cup milk</p>\r\n<p>salt and pepper to taste</p>','<p>1. In a large saucepan, melt the butter, add the celery and onion. Add carlic to the pan. Cook gently over low for 6-8 min. or until veggies are soft and have no color.</p>\r\n<p>2. Clean the mushroom and remove the stems. Chop mushroom caps.</p>\r\n<p>3. Increase the heat and add the mushrooms, stirring constantly. When mushrooms begin to stick to the pan, add the wine and stock. Bring to boil.</p>\r\n<p>3. Peel and slice the potato, then add to mushrooms with the thyme. Reduce the heat and simmer. Cover and cook for approx. 45 min. or until mushrooms are very soft. Remove the thyme and puree the remaining mixture.</p>\r\n<p>4. Return to clean pan, add milk and season to taste. Reheat and serve.</p>','<p>I use cremini mushrooms. They are cheaper and have a nice flavor. I serve the soup with dollop of sour cream and a sprinkling of parmesan.</p>',26),(227,'Scalloped Potatoes','<p>1 tub (250g) Herb and garlic cream cheese spread</p>\r\n<p>2 cups chicken broth</p>\r\n<p>1 cup milk</p>\r\n<p>2/3 cup bacon, cooked and crumbled</p>\r\n<p>4.5 lbs. Yukon gold potatoes cut in 1/4&quot; slices</p>\r\n<p>1 onion thinly sliced</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup shredded motz cheese</p>\r\n<p>1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese</p>','<p>Perheat oven to 400 degrees</p>\r\n<p>1. Cook cream cheese spread, broth and milk in saucepan on medium heat until cream cheese is melted and mixture comes to boil. Stir constantly with wisk.</p>\r\n<p>2. Reserve 2 tbsps bacon bits. Layer half each of the potatoes, onions and bacon in 13x9 dish. Repeat layers and then add cream cheese sauce. Cover</p>\r\n<p>3. Bake 1.5 hours or until potatoes are tender and top is golden. Uncover and top with shredded cheese and reserved bacon bits for the last 10 minutes</p>',NULL,30),(228,'Watermelon Salad','8 cups lettuce\r\n2 cups seedless watermelon chunks (1 inch)\r\n3/4 cup quartered cucumber slices\r\n1/3 cup thin small red onion slices\r\n1/3 cup poppyseed dressing','combine ingredients in bowl and toss with dressing','I have made another salad like this except it was just watermelon, cucumber, onion and fets with mint on top.  Nice light salad, very refreshing',16),(229,'Apple Pie Bars','1 pkg (250 g) cream cheese\r\n1 cup softened butter\r\n3.25 cups flour, divided\r\n10 granny smith apples, peeled and sliced\r\n1.25 cups granulated sugar\r\n1 tsp cinnamon\r\n3/4 cup icing sugar\r\n1 tbsp water','Heat over 400\r\n\r\n1.  Beat cream cheese and butter until well blended, \r\n\r\n2.  Gradually add 3 cups flour mixing low speed until just blended.\r\n\r\n3.  Shape into 2 balls.  Place 1 ball on large lightly floured sheet of waxed paper and flatten slightly.  Cover with second floured sheet of waxed paper.  Roll out dough to 15.5 x 10.5 rectangle.  Discard top sheet of paper.\r\n\r\n4.  Spray 15x10x1 inch pan with cooking spray, invert over folled out dough.  Flip dough and pan together.  Remove wax paper sheet.  Gently press dough onto bottom of pan.\r\n\r\n5.  Toss apples with remaining flour, sugar, cinnamon.  Spread on bottom on crust.\r\n\r\n6.  Roll out remaining dough ball same as the first.  Carefully flip dough over apples.  Tuck under edges of dough to emclosed apples.  Cut slits in crust to vent.\r\n\r\n7.  Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.  Cool dessert 15 min.  Meanwhile mix icing sugar and water.  Drizzle glaze over dessert.  Cool 30 min before cutting into bars','Sounds like a nice take on apple pie.',7),(230,'Wild Berry-Oatmeal Cheesecake Muffins','1 cup large flake rolled oats\r\n1 cup buttermilk\r\n1 pkg cream cheese softened\r\n1/4 cup sugar\r\n3 tbsp orange zest\r\n1 cup flour\r\n3/4 cup packed brown sugar\r\n1 tsp baking powder\r\n1/2 tsp baking soda\r\n1/2 tsp salt\r\n1 egg, beaten\r\n1/4 cup melted butter\r\n1 cup fresh or frozen mixed berries','oven 350\r\n\r\n1.  Combine oats and buttermilk and let stand 10 minutes\r\n\r\n2.  Beat cream cheese, granulated sugar and zest until well blended, set aside.\r\n\r\n3.  Mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.\r\n\r\n4.  Add egg and butter to oat mixture, stir until well blended.  Add dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.\r\n\r\n5.  Gently stir in berries\r\n\r\n6.  Spoon half the butter evenly into 12 muffin cups lined with giant paper liners, filling each liner half full.\r\n\r\n7.  Top each with 2 tbsps cream cheese filling.  Cover with remaining batter.\r\n\r\n8.  Bake 25 to 27 minutes until toothpick comes out clean',NULL,5),(231,'Potato Smashers','8 new potatoes (1.5 inches)\r\n1/2 cup water\r\n\r\n2 tbsps sun dried tomato and oregano dressing\r\n1/2 cup motz and cheddar mixture\r\n4 slices bacon cooked and crumbled','MIcrowave 8 new potatoesand 1/2 cup water on high for 10 min or until tender\r\n\r\nDrain, place on work surface and flatten to 1/2 inch thickness\r\n\r\nHeat dressing and add potatoes, cook 4 min or until bottoms are golden brown.  Turn and top with cheese and bacon.\r\n\r\nCook 2 min or until cheese is melted',NULL,30),(232,'Baked Reuben Dip','1 jar (32 oz) sauerkraut rinsed and well drained\r\n10 oz sliced deli corned beef, chopped\r\n2 cups shredded sharp cheddar cheese\r\n2 cups shredded swiss chesse\r\n1 cup mayo\r\n1/4 cup Russian salad dressing\r\n1 tsp caraway seeds, optional\r\n\r\nrye crackers or bread for dipping\r\n','In a large bowl, mix the first six ingredients; stir in caraway seeds.  Place in greased 13x9 baking dish.\r\n\r\nBake at 350 for 25 to 30 min or until bubbly\r\n\r\nServe with crackers or bread',NULL,18),(233,'Jalapeno Popper Spread','2 pkgs (8 oz each) cream cheese softened\r\n1 cup mayo\r\n1/2 cup shredded monterey jack cheese\r\n1/4 cup chopped green chilies\r\n1/4 cup canned diced jalapeno peppers\r\n1 cup shredded parmesan cheese\r\n1/2 cup panko bread crumbs\r\n\r\ncorn chips or sweet pepper pieces for dipping','In large bowl beat the first five ingredients until blended. \r\n\r\nSpread into 9 inch pie plate.  Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and top with bread crumbs.\r\n\r\nBake 400 for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned\r\n\r\nServe with peppers and chips ',NULL,18),(234,'Mushroom spinach baked eggs','2tbsps olive oil\r\n1 small onion chopped\r\n1 lb mushrooms sliced\r\n6 cups fresh baby spinach\r\n6 slices bread\r\n6 leg eggs\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n3/4 cup shredded gruyere cheese','1. Heat oil in pan, add onion cook til golden.  Add mushrooms and cook til brown. Add 1/2 tsp salt and pepper to taste.  Add spinach and cooktil wilted.  Take off heat and cool.\r\n\r\n2. 9x13 pan oiled.  Arrange bread slightly overlapped.  Spoon mixture on top.  Can cover and refridge over night.\r\n\r\n3. Preheat 350 . Coach egg onto each piece of bread.  Season salt and pepper.  Pour milk evenly over top and sprinkle with cheese.\r\n\r\nBake til egg whites are set 25-30 min','Have not made this yet but looked really tasty',36),(235,'Homemade condensed milk','1 cup instant skim milk powder\r\n2/3 cup white sugar\r\n3 tbsp s unsalted room temp butter\r\n1/2 tsp vanilla\r\n1/3 cup boiling water\r\n','Combine all ingredients in blender.cover with lid, then whirl until very smooth 1 to 2 min.\r\nIf too thick add more hot water 1 tbsp at a time until desired consistency (caramel sauce)','4/7/2013  - have not tried yet but could be a handy thing to have and much cheaper',7),(236,'Best brownies ever - taste of home','1 cup sugar\r\n1/2 cup packed brown sugar\r\n2/3 cup cubed butter\r\n1/4 cup water\r\n2 tsp instant coffee (optional)\r\n2-3/4 cups (16 oz) semi sweet chocolate chips - divided\r\n4 large eggs\r\n2 tsps vanilla extract\r\n1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1/2 tsp baking soda\r\n1/2 tsp salt','Preheat oven to 325\r\nLine 9x9 pan with parchment\r\n\r\n1.  In saucepan combine, sugar, butter,water,coffe and bring to boil stirring.  Remove from head add 1-3/4 cups choc chips and stir til melted.  Cool slightly.\r\n\r\n2.  In large bowl whisk eggs until foamy( approx 3 mins). Add vanilla.  Gradually whisk in chocolate mixture.  In another bowl mix dry ingredients except extra choc chips.\r\n\r\n3.  Stir dry ingredients into chocolate mixture.  Foldin remaining choc chips.\r\n\r\n4.  Pour into pan and bake for 40-50 minutes ( if found it takes longer) cook until toothpick inserted in center comes out with moists crumbs.  Do not overtake.  Cool in pan.','Delicious ',6),(237,'Best brownies ever - taste of home','1 cup sugar\r\n1/2 cup packed brown sugar\r\n2/3 cup cubed butter\r\n1/4 cup water\r\n2 tsp instant coffee (optional)\r\n2-3/4 cups (16 oz) semi sweet chocolate chips - divided\r\n4 large eggs\r\n2 tsps vanilla extract\r\n1-1/2 cups flour\r\n1/2 tsp baking soda\r\n1/2 tsp salt','Preheat oven to 325\r\nLine 9x9 pan with parchment\r\n\r\n1.  In saucepan combine, sugar, butter,water,coffe and bring to boil stirring.  Remove from head add 1-3/4 cups choc chips and stir til melted.  Cool slightly.\r\n\r\n2.  In large bowl whisk eggs until foamy( approx 3 mins). Add vanilla.  Gradually whisk in chocolate mixture.  In another bowl mix dry ingredients except extra choc chips.\r\n\r\n3.  Stir dry ingredients into chocolate mixture.  Foldin remaining choc chips.\r\n\r\n4.  Pour into pan and bake for 40-50 minutes ( if found it takes longer) cook until toothpick inserted in center comes out with moists crumbs.  Do not overtake.  Cool in pan.','Delicious ',6),(238,'Salted s\'more truffles','1 packet graham crackers crushed\r\n1 cup mini choc chips\r\n1/4 tsp salt\r\n1-1/2 cup marshmallow fluff\r\nChocolate for dipping\r\nSea salt','Crush graham crackers til no big chunks.\r\nMix all ingredients together and roll into balls.\r\nFreeze 15 minutes\r\nDip in chocolate then light sprinkle of sea salt on top',NULL,19),(239,'Sangria','2 bottles of red wine\r\nTriple sec about 1-1.5 cups\r\nSimple syrup ... To your desired sweetness I would say 1/2 cup\r\n7 up .....add some taste and see if the flavor is right...keep adding to desired taste\r\nCut up fruits of your choice, I like lemons, limes, apples more citrucy tasting.','Put wine in jug.  Add triple sec, simple syrup and muddle with fruit.  Put in fridge to cool.  Just before serving add 7 up and ice.','There are no specific portions to this.  Put. Some in give it a taste and adjust til you like it.',22),(240,'Pate chinois aux lentilles','<p>2 petites pommes de terre en quartiers</p>\r\n<div>2 carottes, en tranches</div>\r\n<div>1 chou-fleur, en petits bouquets</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;huile d\'olive</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;3 ou 4 gousses d\'ail</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;1 gros oignon, hache</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;1/2 lb de boeuf hache</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;2 1/2 tasse - 1 boite de 540 ml de lentilles vertes&nbsp;en conserve, rincees et egouttees</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;1 c. a the de sarriette ou de thym seche</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;1 c. a soupe de persil seche</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;sel et poivre du moulin</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;1 1/2 tasse de mars en creme ou en grains</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;1 c. a the de beurre, coupe c?.rn morceaux</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>','<p>&nbsp;Prechauffer le four 350F</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;1h15 min</p>\r\n<div>4 a 6 portions</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;Dans une casserole, cuire les pommes de terre et les carottes environ 20 min.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; Cuire le choufFleur au micro-ondes de 8 a 10 min</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; ( avec 2 c. a soupe d\'eau ou a la vapeur)</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; faire revenir l\' ail et l\'oignon. Ajouter le boeuf.Quand la viande est cuite,ajouter les lentilles, la sarriette et le persil. Saler et poivrer au gout.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Versez la preparation dans un plat allant aufour.</div>\r\n<div>Couvrir avec le mals et terminer avec la puree de legumes.</div>\r\n<div>Couvrir avec de petits morceaux de beurre et cuire an four 30 min a decouvert.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Richard Nadeau</div>','<p>Got this recipe from my sister (gaet\'s sister) Helene, have not tried it yet but it\'s the one that she likes.</p>',13),(241,'Test','Dessert',NULL,'Freeze',1),(242,'Food','Food',NULL,NULL,7);
